        "text": "<p>Owner brings a personal car into the business. Which account is credited?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Car",
            "Vehicle",
            "Capital",
            "Drawings"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Anything the owner brings into the business increases Capital (Credit).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 226,
        "text": "<p>What is the source document for Sales Returns?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit Note",
            "Credit Note",
            "Invoice",
            "Voucher"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset Credit Note is sent to the customer to acknowledge the return.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 227,
        "text": "<p>Which of these is a Nominal Account?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Rent",
            "Cash",
            "Bank",
            "Furniture"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Nominal accounts represent Expenses (like Rent) or Incomes.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 228,
        "text": "<p>What is the formula for Owner's Equity?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset + Liability",
            "Asset - Liability",
            "Liability - Asset",
            "Asset x Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Assets minus Liabilities equals Owner's Equity (Capital).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 229,
        "text": "<p>Salary paid 5,000 TK but 1,000 TK is still due. Total Salary Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4,000 TK",
            "5,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "1,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Under accrual basis: 5,000 TK (Paid) + 1,000 TK (Due) = 6,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 230,
        "text": "<p>Prepaid Insurance is what type of account?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Expense",
            "Liability",
            "Asset",
            "Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Prepaid expenses provide future benefits, so they are Assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 231,
        "text": "<p>Cash sales 10,000 TK. Impact on Equation?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset increase, Equity increase",
            "Asset increase, Liability increase",
            "Asset decrease, Equity increase",
            "Asset decrease, Liability decrease"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash (Asset) increases and Revenue increases Equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 232,
        "text": "<p>Which voucher is used for Credit Purchases?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit Voucher",
            "Credit Voucher",
            "Journal Voucher",
            "Transfer Voucher"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Credit Vouchers are used for recording all types of income and credit purchases.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 233,
