            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "1,40,000 TK",
            "1,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash = Opening + Credit Sales - Closing = 30,000 TK + 1,20,000 TK - 50,000 TK = 1,00,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 241,
        "text": "<p>Probal Traders sold goods worth 50,000 TK at 5% discount on credit. On July 10, half the amount was received at 2% discount. What is the impact of the discount? i. Profit dec 475; ii. Assets dec 475; iii. Equity dec 475.</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i and ii",
            "i and iii",
            "ii and iii",
            "i, ii and iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Receivable = 47,500 TK. Half is 23,750 TK. Cash Discount = 23,750 TK * 2% = 475. Since it's an expense, it reduces profit, assets (receivable), and equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 242,
        "text": "<p>(Based on previous) How much cash was received for that half payment?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "23,275 TK",
            "23,750 TK",
            "24,225 TK",
            "24,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net half: 23,750 TK. Cash: 23,750 TK - (2%) 475 = 23,275 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 243,
