    },
    {
        "id": 266,
        "text": "<p>What can be known by preparing Cash Receipt and Cash Payment Journals?\n\ni. Total cash receipts\n\nii. Total cash payments\n\niii. Total bank overdraft</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash Receipt and Cash Payment journals track all inflows and outflows of cash/bank. Bank overdraft (iii) is a balance typically determined in the Ledger or Bank Reconciliation, not directly as a total from these journals.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 267,
        "text": "<p>Balancing on Jan 1: Cash 1.05L, Bank 1.1L, Furniture 1.15L, Inventory 1.2L, Payable 33k, Due Salary 18k. Total Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,99,000 TK",
            "4,32,000 TK",
            "4,17,000 TK",
            "4,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Assets = Cash + Bank + Furniture + Inventory = 1,05,000 TK + 1,10,000 TK + 1,15,000 TK + 1,20,000 TK = 4,50,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 268,
        "text": "<p>(Based on previous) What is the Opening Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "51,000 TK",
            "2,15,000 TK",
            "3,99,000 TK",
            "4,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital = Total Assets - Total Liabilities = 4,50,000 TK - (33,000 TK + 18,000 TK) = 3,99,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
