        "id": 298,
        "text": "<p>Asset Contra Entry occurs in the Cash Book when: i. Business cash is deposited into the bank; ii. Asset check is received and deposited immediately; iii. Bank withdrawal for office use.</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i and ii",
            "i and iii",
            "ii and iii",
            "i, ii and iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Contra entries involve internal movement between Cash and Bank. Depositing a customer's check immediately is often recorded as a direct bank receipt, not a contra.</p>"
    },
    {
