        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Statement i is a definite inflow (Debit), and statement iii is a definite movement involving the bank recorded on the Credit side. Statement ii is positioned incorrectly for a standard \"payment,\" leading to the selection of i \u0993 iii.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 450,
        "text": "<p>Based on the same Cash Account, which journal entries are correct? i. Cash Debit, Bank Debit, Rent Debit, Capital Credit; ii. Cash Debit, Capital Credit, Rent Credit; iii. Bank Debit, Cash Credit.</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Why (c) is the Correct Option:\nStatement i is incorrect: It suggests Bank and Rent are both Debited along with Cash, which contradicts the ledger where Bank is on the Credit side.\n\nStatement ii is consistent: It correctly identifies the accounts that were Credited (Capital and Rent) against the Cash Debit.\n\nStatement iii is consistent: It correctly identifies that when Cash is Credited, the corresponding Bank account is Debited.\n\nTherefore, the correct journal entries reflected are found in statements ii \u0993 iii.</p>"
    },
