            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 472,
        "text": "<p>What is recorded on the Credit side of a Bank Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest on loan",
            "Withdrawals",
            "Deposits",
            "Bank charges"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>In a Bank Statement (Passbook), deposits increase the balance and are credited.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 473,
        "text": "<p>The Double-Column (Amended) Bank Reconciliation method\u2014\n\ni. Is done using both Cash Book & Bank Statement balances\n\nii. Results in both balances being equal after reconciliation\n\niii. Finds the correct bank balance</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>This method adjusts both books simultaneously to reach the true/corrected balance that should appear on the Balance Sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 474,
        "text": "<p>5,000 TK check deposited, but accountant recorded 500. Amount to add in Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "500",
            "4,500 TK",
            "5,000 TK",
            "5,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>5,000 TK - 500 = 4,500 TK must be added to match the actual bank balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 475,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is recorded on the Credit side of the Bank Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest on bank loan",
            "Withdrawal from bank",
            "Deposit into bank",
            "Bank charges"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>In a Bank Statement (Passbook), a deposit is a credit because it increases the bank's liability to the customer.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 476,
        "text": "<p>Cash Book balance is 50,000 TK. Asset deposit of 5,000 TK was recorded as 500 by the accountant. Effect after correction?\n\ni. Current Assets \u2191\n\nii. Current Liabilities \u2191\n\niii. Bank Balance \u2191</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Correcting the under-recorded deposit (4,500 TK) increases the Bank Balance, which is a Current Asset.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 477,
        "text": "<p>Who prepares the Bank Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Depositor",
            "Investor",
            "Borrower",
            "Bank Authority"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The bank prepares and provides the statement to the account holder.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 478,
        "text": "<p>Cash Book: 20k. Direct Depreciation: 5k, Rejected: 4k, Charge: 200. Bank Statement balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "29,200 TK",
            "29,000 TK",
            "20,800 TK",
            "19,200 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>20,000 TK + 5,000 TK - 4,000 TK - 200 = 20,800 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 479,
        "text": "<p>What does a Debit balance in the Bank Statement indicate?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Fund",
            "Bank Deposit",
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Cash Fund"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset debit in the bank's books means the customer owes money (Overdraft).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 480,
        "text": "<p>Asset Credit Memorandum is issued for\u2014\n\ni. Service charges\n\nii. Interest allowed/granted\n\niii. Collection of Notes Receivable</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset Credit Memo increases the customer's account. Service charges decrease it (Debit Memo), while interest and collections increase it.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 481,
        "text": "<p>Which accounting principle applies to preparing a Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Consistency",
            "Matching"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It discloses all reasons for differences between the two sets of records.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 482,
        "text": "<p>Asset check issued to a creditor but not yet presented is called:</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "In transit",
            "Outstanding check",
            "Advance check",
            "Rejected check"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Also known as \"Bokeya Check\" or \"Unpresented Check.\"</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 483,
        "text": "<p>20,000 TK deposit recorded as 2,000 TK in Cash Book. Amount to adjust in Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000 TK",
            "18,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "22,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>20,000 TK - 2,000 TK = 18,000 TK must be added back to the Cash Book balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 484,
        "text": "<p>Cash Book balance is 80,000 TK. Asset 20,000 TK deposit was recorded as 2,000 TK. Effect on the Financial Statement?\n\ni. Fixed Asset \u2191\n\nii. Current Asset \u2191\n\niii. Bank Balance \u2191</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Under-recording a deposit (by 18,000 TK) means the actual Bank Balance and total Current Assets are higher than what was initially recorded.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 485,
        "text": "<p>350 interest received was wrongly credited as 530 in Cash Book. Amount to add?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "180",
            "350",
            "530",
            "880"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>350 TK (Actual) TK+ 530 TK (to reverse wrong entry) TK= 880 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 486,
        "text": "<p>Which transaction reduces a Bank Overdraft?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Check collection",
            "Check payment",
            "Rejection",
            "Bank charge"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Depositing or collecting a check adds money, reducing the negative balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 487,
        "text": "<p>Full form of Not Sufficient Funds?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Not Satisfying Fund",
            "National Fund",
            "Not Sufficient Funds",
            "New Saving Fund"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Indicates a \"bounced\" check due to lack of money in the account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 488,
        "text": "<p>Who is considered the Client of a bank?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Person depositing money",
            "Person opening and operating an account",
            "Person borrowing money",
            "Bank manager"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The formal account holder is the bank's client.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 489,
        "text": "<p>Cash Book: 20k. Transit: 5k, Outstanding: 3k. Bank balance as per Cash Book?</p>",
