        "explanation": "<p>\u0986\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09a4\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09ac\u09be \u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac\u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09a4\u09be\u09b0 \u09a8\u09bf\u099c\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a8\u0997\u09a6\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u0987\u09df\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b8\u09be\u09a5\u09c7 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0\u09a3\u09c0 \u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u09be\u09a8\u09cb\u09b0 \u099c\u09a8\u09cd\u09af Bank Reconciliation Statement \u09a4\u09c8\u09b0\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 537,
        "text": "<p>For which of the following does the bank issue a Debit Memorandum?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Collection of Note Receivable",
            "Dishonor of deposited check",
            "Deposit by debtor",
            "Interest on bank balance"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>\u09af\u0996\u09a8 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09cb \u099c\u09ae\u09be \u09a6\u09c7\u0993\u09df\u09be \u099a\u09c7\u0995 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0996\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09a8 (Dishonor) \u09b9\u09df, \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09b9\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u099f\u09be\u0995\u09be \u0995\u09ae\u09bf\u09df\u09c7 \u09a6\u09c7\u09df \u098f\u09ac\u0982 \u09a1\u09c7\u09ac\u09bf\u099f \u09ae\u09c7\u09ae\u09cb\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09be\u09ae \u0987\u09b8\u09cd\u09af\u09c1 \u0995\u09b0\u09c7\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 538,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is included in a Credit Memorandum?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Service Charge",
            "Overdraft Interest",
            "Interest Earned",
            "Check Printing Charge"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09a1\u09bf\u099f \u09ae\u09c7\u09ae\u09cb\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09be\u09ae \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09c7 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u0985\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0995\u09be\u0989\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09c7 \u099f\u09be\u0995\u09be \u09ac\u09c3\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u0993\u09df\u09be\u0964 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u09af\u0996\u09a8 \u09b8\u09c1\u09a6 \u09ae\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09c1\u09b0 \u0995\u09b0\u09c7 (Interest Earned), \u09a4\u0996\u09a8 \u098f\u099f\u09bf \u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09a1\u09bf\u099f \u09ae\u09c7\u09ae\u09cb \u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09c7\u09ac\u09c7 \u0997\u09a3\u09cd\u09af \u09b9\u09df\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 539,
        "text": "<p>Debit balance per bank statement is 40,000 TK. Deposited check not yet credited is 5,000 TK. What is the correct balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "35,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK",
            "45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>\u09a1\u09c7\u09ac\u09bf\u099f \u0989\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4 (Overdraft) \u09ea\u09e6,\u09e6\u09e6\u09e6 TK \u099f\u09be\u0995\u09be \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u099c\u09ae\u09be \u09b9\u0993\u09df\u09be \u09eb,\u09e6\u09e6\u09e6 TK \u099f\u09be\u0995\u09be \u09ac\u09be\u09a6 \u09a6\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7 \u09b8\u09a0\u09bf\u0995 \u0989\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09ac\u09c7 \u09e9\u09eb,\u09e6\u09e6\u09e6 TK \u099f\u09be\u0995\u09be (\u09a1\u09c7\u09ac\u09bf\u099f)\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 540,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is considered while preparing Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cash payment to supplier",
            "Cash collection of dues",
            "Bank interest recorded in both books",
            "Outstanding checks"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>\u09af\u09c7 \u09b2\u09c7\u09a8\u09a6\u09c7\u09a8\u0997\u09c1\u09b2\u09cb \u09a8\u0997\u09a6\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u0987 \u0993 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0\u09a3\u09c0\u09b0 \u09ae\u09a7\u09cd\u09af\u09c7 \u09b8\u09ae\u09df\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09a5\u0995\u09cd\u09af\u09c7\u09b0 \u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09a3\u09c7 \u0997\u09b0\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2 \u09b8\u09c3\u09b7\u09cd\u099f\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09c7 (\u09af\u09c7\u09ae\u09a8: \u09ac\u0995\u09c7\u09df\u09be \u09ac\u09be \u0985\u09aa\u09b0\u09bf\u09b6\u09cb\u09a7\u09bf\u09a4 \u099a\u09c7\u0995), \u09b8\u09c7\u0997\u09c1\u09b2\u09cb\u0987 Bank Reconciliation Statement-\u098f \u0986\u09b8\u09c7\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 541,
        "text": "<p>Who prepares the Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Depositor",
            "Auditor",
            "Accounts Receivable",
            "Bank Account"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>\u0986\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09a4\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09ac\u09be \u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09b9\u0995 \u098f\u099f\u09bf \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09c1\u09a4 \u0995\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 542,
        "text": "<p>While preparing Bank Reconciliation Statement, which of the following must be subtracted from the bank balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Outstanding checks",
            "Bank service charge",
            "Dividend collected by bank",
            "Direct deposit by debtor"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995\u09c7\u09b0 \u099c\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u09ac\u0995\u09c7\u09df\u09be \u099a\u09c7\u0995 (Outstanding checks) \u09ac\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09cb\u0997 \u0995\u09b0\u09a4\u09c7 \u09b9\u09df \u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09a3 \u098f\u0997\u09c1\u09b2\u09cb \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u098f\u0996\u09a8\u0993 \u09aa\u09b0\u09bf\u09b6\u09cb\u09a7\u09bf\u09a4 \u09b9\u09df\u09a8\u09bf\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 543,
        "text": "<p>Bank charged 600 TK for services which the customer doesn't know yet. How to show this in Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Subtract 600 from bank balance",
            "Add 1,200 TK to cash balance",
            "Add 600 to bank balance",
            "Subtract 600 from cash balance"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u099a\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099c \u0995\u09be\u099f\u09b2\u09c7 \u09a8\u0997\u09a6\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u0987\u09df\u09c7\u09b0 (Cash balance) \u0989\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u09ac\u09bf\u09df\u09cb\u0997 \u0995\u09b0\u09a4\u09c7 \u09b9\u09df, \u09af\u09c7\u09b9\u09c7\u09a4\u09c1 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u0982\u0995 \u0987\u09a4\u09cb\u09ae\u09a7\u09cd\u09af\u09c7 \u098f\u099f\u09bf \u0995\u09c7\u099f\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09df\u09c7\u099b\u09c7\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 544,
        "text": "<p>Who prepares the Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Authority",
            "Investor",
            "Depositor",
            "Borrower"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>\u0986\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09a4\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 \u09ac\u09be \u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac\u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09c0 (\u098f\u099f\u09bf \u09ac\u09be\u09b0\u09ac\u09be\u09b0 \u0986\u09b8\u09be \u098f\u0995\u099f\u09bf \u0997\u09c1\u09b0\u09c1\u09a4\u09cd\u09ac\u09aa\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u09a3 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09b6\u09cd\u09a8)\u0964</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 545,
        "text": "<p>Reasons for difference between Cash Book and Bank Statement\u2014i) Direct collection by bankii) Direct payment by bankiii) Dishonor of deposited check</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three items cause a timing or information gap between the two books.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 546,
        "text": "<p>Passbook balance: 60,800 TK. Unpresented: 14,800 TK. Dividend: 13,200 TK. Bank charge: 4,000 TK. Cash Book balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "28,800 TK",
            "32,800 TK",
            "36,800 TK",
            "55,200 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Start from Passbook: 60,800 TK\u221214,800 TK(unpresented)+4,000 TK(charge)\u221213,200 TK(dividend)=36,800 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 547,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #72) If Cash Book is 50,000 TK, what is the Passbook balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "59,200 TK",
            "60,800 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "74,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Start from Cash Book: 50,000 TK+14,800 TK+13,200 TK\u22124,000 TK=74,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 548,
        "text": "<p>Who prepares the Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank",
            "Depositor",
            "Accounts Receivable",
            "Bank & Depositor"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The depositor is the one who initiates the reconciliation process.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 549,
        "text": "<p>Reasons for difference\u2014i) Issued check not presentedii) Deposited check collectediii) 3rd party check directly deposited in bank</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>If a check is collected (ii), both books will eventually match. Differences occur when one side hasn't recorded it yet (i and iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 550,
        "text": "<p>What does a Credit balance in the bank column (Cash Book) indicate?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Bank deposit omitted",
            "Bank Deposit",
            "Debit balance"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>In our Cash Book, a Credit means money going out or a negative balance (Overdraft).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 551,
        "text": "<p>What is a check dishonored due to insufficient funds called?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bearer Check",
            "Account Payee",
            "Crossed Check",
            "Not Sufficient Funds Check"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Not Sufficient Funds stands for Not Sufficient Funds.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 552,
        "text": "<p>Interest allowed by the bank is\u2014i) Credited in Passbookii) Debited in Passbookiii) Debited in Cash Book</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest allowed increases balance. Bank Credits (+ liability to them), we Debit (+ asset to us).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 553,
        "text": "<p>Asif Traders' bank statement shows a 10,000 TK Debit balance. What is this for Asif?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Expense",
            "Asset",
            "Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset Debit in the bank's books means an Overdraft, which is a liability for the customer.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 554,
        "text": "<p>Cash Book: 28,000 TK. Unpresented: 2,750 TK. Dividend: 750. What is the total difference amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "750 TK",
            "2,000 TK",
            "2,750 TK",
            "3,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The \"gap\" is the sum of items not yet in both books: 2,750 TK+750=3,500 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 555,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #80) What is the Bank Statement balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "24,500 TK",
            "25,250 TK",
            "31,500 TK",
            "28,750 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Calculation: 28,000 TK(Cash)+2,750 TK(Unpresented)+750(Dividend)=31,500 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 556,
        "text": "<p>Who prepares the Bank Reconciliation Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank",
            "Depositor",
            "Debtor",
            "Creditor"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The account holder (Depositor).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 557,
        "text": "<p>Which type of check cannot be cashed directly over the counter?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Order Check",
            "Bearer Check",
            "Traveler's Check",
            "Crossed Check"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Crossed checks must be deposited into a bank account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 558,
        "text": "<p>What does a Debit balance in a Bank Statement signify?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Fund",
            "Bank Deposit",
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Cash Fund"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Same as #79; bank debit = customer's overdraft.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 559,
        "text": "<p>Under which principle is the Bank Reconciliation Statement prepared?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Consistency",
            "Revenue-Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Bank Reconciliation Statement ensures the true financial position is revealed by explaining the gap between records.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 560,
        "text": "<p>Which of these is a Credit Memorandum?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Service Charge",
            "Not Sufficient Funds Check",
            "Check Printing cost",
            "Bank Interest Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Credit memo = items that increase the bank balance (like interest earned).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 561,
        "text": "<p>Why is a deposit shown as a Credit in the Bank Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank asset decreases",
            "Bank liability increases",
            "Bank expense increases",
            "Bank income decreases"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Customer deposits are money the bank must return, making it their liability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 562,
        "text": "<p>Which will be included in Bank Reconciliation Statement on June 30?i) Check deposited June 27, collected June 29ii) Check issued but not presented yetiii) Check deposited but collected July 3</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i",
            "ii",
            "iii",
            "ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Item (i) is already in both books by June 30. (ii) and (iii) are still \"in-transit\" on the 30th.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 563,
        "text": "<p>For which is a Debit Memorandum issued?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Interest Allowed",
            "Dividend Collection",
            "Collection of Note Receivable.",
            "Bank Service Charge"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Debit memo = items that decrease the bank balance (like service charges).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 564,
        "text": "<p>Which is a reflection of the depositor's bank account?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Deposit Slip",
            "Bank Statement",
            "Fixed Deposit",
            "Current Deposit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The Bank Statement (or Passbook) is a copy of the customer's ledger in the bank's books.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 565,
        "text": "<p>What does a Debit balance in the Bank Statement signify?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Balance",
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Cash Withdrawal",
            "Cash Balance"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>In the bank's books, a Debit means the customer owes them money (Overdraft).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 566,
        "text": "<p>What does the bank deduct for providing services?i. Commissionii. Bank Chargeiii. Interest Allowed</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Commission and charges are deductions. Interest allowed (iii) is an addition to the account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 567,
        "text": "<p>Jan 1 balance: 30,000 TK. Jan 10: 10,000 TK check deposited. Jan 15: That check is dishonored. Balance on Jan 15?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>(30,000 TK+10,000 TK)\u221210,000 TK=30,000 TK. The dishonor cancels out the previous deposit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 568,
        "text": "<p>Due to a check dishonor\u2014i. Accounts Receivable Drii. Accounts Payable Criii. Bank Account Credit</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>You must increase the Receivable (Debit) and decrease the Bank balance (Credit) to record the bounce.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 569,
        "text": "<p>How is a dishonored check recorded in a two-column cash book?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
