            "label": "c",
            "text": "Prepare a Bank Reconciliation Statement for Mishu Traders as of December 31, 2024.",
            "answer": "<div class=\'space-y-2 font-mono'><p class=\'font-semibold underline text-center text-xs'>Bank Reconciliation Statement of Mishu Traders</p><p class=\'text-center text-[10px] text-gray-500'>(As on December 31, 2024)</p><div class=\'overflow-x-auto'><table class=\'w-full text-xs border-collapse border border-gray-300'><thead><tr class=\'bg-gray-100'><th class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-left'>Particulars</th><th class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>Tk.</th><th class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>Tk.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 font-semibold'>Bank Balance as per Cash Book</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>40,000</td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 italic'>Add:</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8'>Direct deposit by debtor (iii)</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>8,000</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8'>Interest allowed by bank (v)</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>2,500</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8'>Issued checks not presented (vi)</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right border-b border-gray-400'>5,500</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr class=\'bg-gray-50'><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8 font-semibold'>Total Additions</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right font-semibold\' style=\'text-decoration: underline;\'>16,000</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>56,000</td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 italic'>Less:</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8'>Payment to creditor not in Cash Book (ii)</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right'>20,000</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 pl-8'>Deposited check not yet collected (iv)</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right border-b border-gray-400'>5,000</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td></tr><tr class=\'bg-amber-50 font-bold'><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'>Bank Balance as per Bank Statement</td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1'></td><td class=\'border border-gray-300 p-1 text-right\' style=\'text-decoration: underline double;\'>31,000</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>"
        }
    ]
}
]
        },
        "4": {
            subjectName: "Accounting 1st Paper",
            chapterName: "Chapter 4 : Trial Balance",
            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 628,
        "text": "<p>Sales Return of 5,000 TK was mistakenly recorded in the Purchase Account. What is the rectifying entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales Return Debit, Purchase Cr",
            "Purchase Debit, Sales Return Cr",
            "Sales Return Debit, Creditor Cr",
            "Purchase Debit, Creditor Credit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>To fix it: Debit the correct account (Sales Return) and Credit the wrong account (Purchase) to remove it.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 629,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is NOT included in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Unused Stationery",
            "Outstanding Rent",
            "Furniture",
            "Unearned Service Revenue"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing stocks (like Unused Stationery/Supplies) are usually excluded unless \"Adjusted Purchase\" is used.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 630,
        "text": "<p>Selling old machinery was credited to the Sales Account instead of Machinery Account. What type of error is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Principle",
            "Compensating",
            "Clerical",
            "Error of Posting"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Recording a Capital receipt (Asset sale) as a Revenue receipt (Sales) is a Violation of Accounting Principles.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 631,
        "text": "<p>Asset Credit balance of 240 was mistakenly written as 2,400 TK in the Debit column. What is the difference in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "240",
            "2,400 TK",
            "2,160 TK",
            "2,640 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Difference = Correct Amount + Wrong Amount (since side changed) = 240+2,400 TK=2,640 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 632,
        "text": "<p>Not included in the Trial Balance:i. Opening Bank Balanceii. Opening Cashiii. Closing Stock</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening cash/bank and Closing stock (normally) are excluded from the Trial Balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 633,
        "text": "<p>Purchase was written as 15,000 TK instead of 20,000 TK, and Sales as 45,000 TK instead of 50,000 TK. The Trial Balance still matched. Why?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Error of Writing",
            "Compensating Error",
            "Principle Error",
            "Error of Omission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>One error (5k less on Debit) was cancelled out by another error (5k less on Credit).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 634,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #6) By how much was the total of the Trial Balance under or over-stated?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,000 TK less",
            "5,000 TK more",
            "35,000 TK less",
            "95,000 TK more"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Both sides were short by 5,000 TK, so the total sum was 5,000 TK less than it should have been.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 635,
        "text": "<p>Which item is excluded from the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Opening Bank Balance",
            "Closing Bank Balance",
            "Opening Stock",
            "Opening Stationery"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening liquid assets (Cash/Bank) are excluded because they are already part of the closing figures.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 636,
        "text": "<p>Errors not detected by a Trial Balance:i. Principle Errorii. Math Errorsiii. Error of Posting to Wrong Account</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Trial Balance cannot detect Principle errors or posting to the wrong account if the amounts match.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 637,
        "text": "<p>Purchase: 45k instead of 50k; Sales: 30k instead of 35k. Trial Balance matches. What error is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Writing",
            "Principle",
            "Compensating",
            "Omission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>(Same logic as #6). One error compensates for the other.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 638,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #10) By how much was the Trial Balance total short or over?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,000 TK less",
            "5,000 TK more",
            "10,000 TK less",
            "10,000 TK more"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Both sides were recorded 5,000 TK short (50k\u221245k and 35k\u221230k).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 639,
        "text": "<p>Which of these is excluded from the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Opening Bank Deposit",
            "Closing Cash in Hand",
            "Rent",
            "Preliminary Expenses"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Cash/Bank are excluded (Closing ones are included).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 640,
        "text": "<p>Machine installation cost of 6,000 TK was mistakenly included in Wages. What error is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Error of Posting",
            "Error of Omission",
            "Compensating Error",
            "Principle Error"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Treating an asset (Machine) cost as an expense (Wages) is a Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 641,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #13) What is the impact of this error on the accounts?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset up",
            "Profit down",
            "Liability down",
            "Capital up"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>By recording it as Wages (Expense) instead of Machine (Asset), the total expenses increased, making Profit decrease.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 642,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance does not detect:i. Principle Errorii. Compensating Erroriii. Error of Omission</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These three types of errors do not disrupt the equality of Debits and Credits.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 643,
        "text": "<p>\"Machine Setup Cost\" was mistakenly Credited to Machine Account. Correcting entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Machine Debit (1x)",
            "Machine Debit (2x)",
            "Setup Cost Debit (1x)",
            "Setup Cost Debit (2x)"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Since it was mistakenly credited, you must Debit it twice: once to cancel the error and once to record the correct entry.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 644,
        "text": "<p>If \"Adjusted Purchase\" is in the Trial Balance, which is EXCLUDED?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Closing Cash",
            "Closing Bank",
            "Opening Stock",
            "Closing Stock"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>When \"Adjusted Purchase\" exists, Closing Stock is included and Opening Stock is excluded.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 645,
        "text": "<p>Preparing a Trial Balance using Ledger balances is part of which accounting stage?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Identifying",
            "Recording",
            "Classifying",
            "Summarizing"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Trial Balance is the first step of the Summarizing phase.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 646,
        "text": "<p>Where is the arithmetical accuracy of accounts verified?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Journal",
            "Ledger",
            "Trial Balance",
            "Worksheet"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>That is the primary purpose of a Trial Balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 647,
        "text": "<p>When one error is cancelled out by another error, it is called?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Principle Error",
            "Omission Error",
            "Posting Error",
            "Compensating Error"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the definition of a Compensating Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 648,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock 90,000 TK, Net Purchase 2,60,000 TK, and Closing Stock 70,000 TK. What is the Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,70,000 TK",
            "1,90,000 TK",
            "2,80,000 TK",
            "3,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Adjusted Purchase = (90,000 TK+2,60,000 TK)\u221270,000 TK=2,80,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 649,
        "text": "<p>Which will affect the Suspense Account?i. Furniture for resale Debit to Furniture Accountii. Repair 5,000 TK Debit to Plant as 500iii. Purchase Return Debit to Purchase Account</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Item (ii) has a math error (5,000 TK vs 500) and (iii) is a wrong side entry. (i) is a principle error that matches.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 650,
        "text": "<p>The purpose of the Trial Balance is\u2014i. Verify math accuracyii. Summarize accountsiii. Determine results</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Trial Balance is for accuracy (i) and summarizing (ii). Final results (iii) are found in Financial Statements.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 651,
        "text": "<p>Furniture bought for office use is Debited to \"Purchase\". What error is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Writing",
            "Compensating",
            "Principle",
            "Posting"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Debiting a revenue account (Purchase) for a capital asset (Furniture) is a Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 652,
        "text": "<p>Which of these is a Credit in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Commission Receivable",
            "Unearned Revenue",
            "Accrued Interest",
            "Debtor"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Unearned Revenue is a liability; liabilities always have a Credit balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 653,
        "text": "<p>Which is correct for Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales + Closing. Stock - Purchase",
            "Opening. Stock + Purchase + Closing. Stock",
            "Opening. Stock + Net Purchase - Closing. Stock",
            "Opening. Stock - Purchase + Closing. Stock"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the standard formula for Adjusted Purchase.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 654,
        "text": "<p>Which is included in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Opening. Cash Fund",
            "Closing. Cash Fund",
            "Opening. Bank Deposit",
            "Closing. Stock (Normal case)"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing liquid assets are included; opening ones are not.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 655,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Rahman, a furniture dealer, bought furniture for 1,00,000 TK and Debited the \"Furniture Account\". Type of error?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Clerical",
            "Principle",
            "Compensating",
            "Omission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>For a dealer, furniture is \"Goods\" (Purchase), not an asset. Debiting Furniture is a Principle error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 656,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #28) What is the impact on the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit 1L more",
            "Credit 1L more",
            "Both sides 1L less",
            "No impact"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Both accounts (Purchase and Furniture) are Debit accounts. The Trial Balance will still match perfectly.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 657,
        "text": "<p>Machine installation cost 50,000 TK included in Wages. Type of error?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Writing",
            "Compensating",
            "Clerical",
            "Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset cost treated as revenue expense = Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 658,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #30) Due to this error\u2014i. Trial Balance will matchii. Assets will decreaseiii. Expenses will decrease</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Trial Balance matches. Assets are lower (since it's not in Machine) and Expenses are higher (so iii is wrong).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 659,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 25k, Purchase 1.5L, Sales 2L, Closing. Stock 30k. Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,25,000 TK",
            "1,45,000 TK",
            "1,75,000 TK",
            "2,05,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>25,000 TK+1,50,000 TK\u221230,000 TK=1,45,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 660,
        "text": "<p>Not detected by Trial Balance:i. Omissionii. Principleiii. Compensating</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>None of these disrupt the Debit/Credit equality.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 661,
        "text": "<p>Machinery purchase 5L shown as Purchase. Type of error?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Compensating",
            "Writing",
            "Omission",
            "Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital expenditure recorded as Revenue expenditure.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 662,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #34) Rectifying entry:i. Machinery Drii. Purchase Criii. Suspense Credit</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>You Debit the Asset and Credit the wrong Expense. Suspense is not needed as it was a principle error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 663,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance acts as a bridge between\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Journal & Cash",
            "Ledger & Financial Statements",
            "Journal & Ledger",
            "Adjusting & Closing"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It uses Ledger balances and provides the data for Financial Statements.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 664,
        "text": "<p>Error due to lack of accounting knowledge?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Omission",
            "Writing",
            "Principle",
            "Compensating"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Principle errors happen when one doesn't distinguish between Capital and Revenue.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 665,
        "text": "<p>Which of these is a Credit in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales Discount",
            "Long-term Investment",
            "Allowance for Bad Debts",
            "Sales Return"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Provisions/Allowances are Credits. Returns and Investments are Debits.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 666,
        "text": "<p>Primary objective of Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit/Loss",
            "Financial Position",
            "Math accuracy of Ledger",
            "Solvency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The core reason is to ensure Debits = Credits mathematically.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 667,
        "text": "<p>Purchase Return mistakenly recorded as Sales. Correcting entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "PR Debit, Accounts Payable Cr",
            "Cash Debit, Sales Cr",
            "Accounts Payable Debit, PR Cr",
            "Sales Debit, PR Credit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>To fix: Debit Sales (to cancel the wrong credit) and Credit Purchase Return (to record correctly).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 668,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following does NOT go to the Credit side of the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bad Debt Provision",
            "Provision for Discount on Receivables",
            "Provision for Discount on Payables",
            "Capital Reserve"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Provisions on Assets (like Receivables) are usually Credits, but Provision for Discount on Receivables is a rare Debit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 669,
        "text": "<p>Furniture purchase Debited to Purchase Account\u2014what type of error is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Clerical",
            "Compensating",
            "Posting",
            "Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Violating the rule between Capital (Asset) and Revenue (Expense) is a Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 670,
        "text": "<p>Asset balance of 28 was shown on the wrong side of the Trial Balance as 98. What is the total difference?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "126",
            "98",
            "70",
            "28"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Difference = 28(Correct)+98(Wrong\u00a0side)=126.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 671,
        "text": "<p>Shown in the Debit column of Trial Balance:i. Asset, Expense, Drawingsii. Cash, Bank Overdraft, Receivableiii. Bank, Receivable, Accrued Income</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Bank Overdraft (ii) is a Credit (Liability), so (ii) is incorrect. Assets, Expenses, and Accrued Incomes are Debits.</p>"
    },
    {
