    {
        "id": 722,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Rahat (Furniture dealer) bought furniture for stock but Debited \"Furniture Account\". Error?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Clerical",
            "Principle",
            "Compensating",
            "Omission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>For a dealer, furniture is an expense (Purchase). Debiting an Asset account is a Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 723,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Rahat is a furniture trader. He purchased furniture worth 3,00,000 TK from 'Star Furniture' at a 10% discount but mistakenly debited the Furniture Account. He took a table worth 3,000 TK for business use and sold half of the purchased goods for 1,50,000 TK, incurring 600 TK in transport costs. \n\nQ: What type of accounting error was committed in Mr. Rahat's books?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Clerical Error",
            "Error of Principle",
            "Compensating Error",
            "Error of Omission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Pur = 270k. Half = 135k. Profit = 150,000 TK\u2212(135,000 TK+600)=14,400 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 724,
        "text": "<p>Which expresses a Debit balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Gen. Reserve",
            "Dis",
            "on Debtors Res.c) Bad Debt",
            "Bad Debt Res."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Bad Debt is an expense (Debit). All reserves listed here are Credits.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 725,
        "text": "<p>What is a Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "An Account",
            "List of Balances",
            "Part of Fin. Stat.",
            "Subsidiary Book"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It is not an account; it is a statement or a list of ledger balances.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 726,
        "text": "<p>Error while transferring from Journal to Ledger is called?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Omission",
            "Writing",
            "Posting",
            "Compensating"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is a \"Clerical Error\" specifically categorized as an Error of Commission/Writing.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 727,
        "text": "<p>Not a Principle Error:i. Machine as Purchaseii. Sales not recordediii. Sales to X put in Y</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>(i) is a principle error. (ii) is omission and (iii) is an error of commission (wrong account).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 728,
        "text": "<p>Machinery purchase written as \"Purchase\". Correcting entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Pur Debit, Cash Cr",
            "Machine Debit, Pur Cr",
            "Machine Debit, Cash Cr",
            "Pur Debit, Machine Credit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Debit the correct Asset and Credit the wrong Expense to fix it.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 729,
        "text": "<p>Which set usually has a Debit balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income, Capital, Asset",
            "Liability, Capital, Exp",
            "Asset, Drawings, Exp",
            "Sales, Drawings, Disc"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Assets, Drawings, and Expenses/Costs always have normal Debit balances.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 730,
        "text": "<p>Which is an example of a Contra-Liability (\u09ac\u09bf\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09a6\u09be\u09af\u09bc)?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bad Debt Prov.",
            "Bad Debt",
            "Disc. on Receivables Prov.",
            "Disc. on Payables Prov."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Provision for Discount on Payables reduces a liability, so it is a Contra-Liability (Debit).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 731,
        "text": "<p>Which sits on the Credit side of the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales Discount",
            "Purchase Discount",
            "Discount Allowed",
            "Trade Discount"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Purchase Discount is an income/reduction in cost, so it is a Credit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 732,
        "text": "<p>Machinery repair 10k shown in Machinery Account. What error?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Writing",
            "Principle",
            "Omission",
            "Compensating"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Treating a Revenue expense (Repair) as a Capital expenditure (Asset) is a Principle Error.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 733,
        "text": "<p>Which is included in the Trial Balance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Opening. Cash",
            "Opening. Bank",
            "Closing. Cash",
            "Closing. Stock"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing liquid assets (Cash/Bank) are included in the Trial Balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 734,
        "text": "<p>Which error affects the Suspense Account?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Error in balancing",
            "Principle Error",
            "Compensating Error",
            "Omission Error"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Math errors or balancing errors create a mismatch, requiring a Suspense Account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 735,
        "text": "<p>Rent received 5k was Debited to Rent Account. What error?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Writing",
            "Principle",
            "Omission",
            "Commission"
        ],
