        "5": {
            subjectName: "Accounting 1st Paper",
            chapterName: "Chapter 5 : Accounting Principles (Out of Short Syllabus)",
            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 840,
        "text": "<p>Which principle requires fixed assets to be shown at purchase price?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Entity",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Historical Cost (\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09bc\u09ae\u09c2\u09b2\u09cd\u09af) principle states assets must be recorded at their original cost.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 841,
        "text": "<p>Which is the top international accounting organization?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "GAAP",
            "FASB",
            "AICPA",
            "SEC"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>FASB (Financial Accounting Standards Board) is the primary body that sets standards.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 842,
        "text": "<p>Which standard covers \"Presentation of Financial Statements\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumillabined  Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "IAS 1",
            "IAS 2",
            "IAS 7",
            "IAS 16"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>IAS 1 dictates how the Balance Sheet and Income Statement are presented.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 843,
        "text": "<p>Which standard covers \"Inventories\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumillabined  Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "IAS 1",
            "IAS 2",
            "IAS 8",
            "IAS 10"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>IAS 2 is the international rule for valuing Inventory (Stock).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 844,
        "text": "<p>What is the full form of GAAP?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumillabined  Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Generally Accepted Accounting Principles",
            "General Accepted Accounting Principles",
            "Generally Accounting Accepted Program",
            "Generally Accpted Accounting Policy"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Generally Accepted Accounting Principles. Note the \"ly\" in Generally and \"s\" in Principles.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 845,
        "text": "<p>What do the \"Three Cs\" of Accounting usually represent?</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost, consumer...",
            "Cost, consistency, conservatism",
            "Cost, consistency, convention",
            "Cost, Commission..."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost, Consistency, and Conservatism are the foundational pillars.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 846,
        "text": "<p>Double Entry system is recognized by\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "IAS",
            "FASB",
            "AICPA",
            "GAAP"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>GAAP (Generally Accepted Accounting Principles) is the framework for Double Entry.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 847,
        "text": "<p>On what basis does the Accounting Cycle repeat?</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Time Period",
            "Going Concern",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Going Concern (\u099a\u09b2\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc) assumes the business continues forever, so the cycle repeats indefinitely.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 848,
        "text": "<p>Basic concepts of accounting are\u2014i. Revenue Recognition, ii. Consistency, iii. Dividend</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Revenue and Consistency are accounting principles. Dividends are a distribution of profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 849,
        "text": "<p>Which concept influences Depreciation?</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Time Period",
            "Entity",
            "Going Concern",
            "Conservatism"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Same as #55. Spreading the cost over the future depends on the Going Concern assumption.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 850,
        "text": "<p>Which accounts are closed at year-end?</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income-Expense",
            "Equity",
            "Liability",
            "Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Time Period principle requires closing Nominal accounts (Income/Expense).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 851,
        "text": "<p>When is revenue recognized according to the Revenue Recognition principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "When order is placed",
            "When cash is received",
            "When goods are delivered",
            "When contract is signed"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Revenue is recognized when it is earned (goods delivered), regardless of when cash is paid.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 852,
        "text": "<p>Why is a life insurance premium for the owner treated as Drawings?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Entity Concept",
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Per the Entity Concept (\u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09be \u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09a3\u09be), the owner's personal expenses are separate from the business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 853,
        "text": "<p>Providing for all possible losses but not anticipating profits is\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Materiality",
            "Conservatism",
            "Matching"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the core definition of Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 854,
        "text": "<p>IASB stands for?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest. Acc. Standard Board",
            "Interest. Audit Standard Board",
            "Standard Boardb) Interest. Audit Standard Boardc) Interest. Acc. Society Board",
            "Interest. Acc. System Board"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>International Accounting Standards Board.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 855,
        "text": "<p>Which concept assumes the business will continue for an indefinite period?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accounting Period",
            "Going Concern",
            "Dual Aspect",
            "Cost Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Going Concern (\u099a\u09b2\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09a8) assumes the business won't close anytime soon.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 856,
        "text": "<p>Why are financial statements prepared at regular intervals (e.g., yearly)?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Materiality",
            "Time Period",
            "Cost Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Time Period (\u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac\u0995\u09be\u09b2) concept breaks the business life into segments like a \"year.\"</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 857,
        "text": "<p>IFRS stands for?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest. Financial Reporting Standards",
            "Interest. Finance Report System",
            "Interest. Financial Record Standards",
            "Interest. Federation of Report Stan"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>International Financial Reporting Standards.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 858,
        "text": "<p>Small items like calculators are treated as expenses rather than assets because of?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Consistency",
            "Materiality",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Matching"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Materiality (\u09ac\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09a4\u09be) allows small, insignificant costs to be written off immediately.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 859,
        "text": "<p>Using the same depreciation method year after year is an example of?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Materiality",
            "Consistency",
            "Conservatism",
            "Going Concern"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Consistency (\u09b8\u09be\u09ae\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09b8\u09cd\u09af\u09a4\u09be) requires using the same methods to allow year-to-year comparison.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 860,
        "text": "<p>If a machine is bought for 50k and its market value becomes 60k, it's still shown at 50k because of?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Matching",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Market fluctuations are ignored under the Historical Cost principle.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 861,
        "text": "<p>Advance Rent is shown as an asset because of which concept?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accrual Concept",
            "Cash Basis",
            "Entity Concept",
            "Dual Aspect"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Under the Accrual Concept (\u09ac\u0995\u09c7\u09af\u09bc\u09be \u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09a3\u09be), we record payments based on the period they benefit.</p>"
    },
    {
