        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The Matching Principle (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3) ensures costs and revenues of the same period are compared.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 864,
        "text": "<p>Recording all potential expenses but ignoring potential income is which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost-Benefit",
            "Conservatism",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Historical Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the \"Play it Safe\" rule: Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 865,
        "text": "<p>Why is Capital considered a liability to the business?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Dual Aspect",
            "Entity Concept",
            "Revenue Recognition"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Per Entity Concept (\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09bf\u0995 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09be), the business is a separate person from the owner.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 866,
        "text": "<p>According to which principle should prepaid expenses be deducted from total expenses?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Revenue Recognition",
            "Matching"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Matching (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3) requires excluding costs that don't belong to the current year.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 867,
        "text": "<p>Fixed assets are recorded based on which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Historical Cost (\u0990\u09a4\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09bf\u0995 \u09ae\u09c2\u09b2\u09cd\u09af) says record assets at their actual purchase price.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 868,
        "text": "<p>Income Statement is prepared according to which principle/concept?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Revenue Principle",
            "Conservatism",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Accounting Period"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The Accounting Period (\u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac\u0995\u09be\u09b2) concept requires calculating profit for a specific time.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 869,
        "text": "<p>Presenting assets at purchase price is established on which concept?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Accrual",
            "Accounting Period"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Again, Historical Cost prevents revaluing assets based on market whims.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 870,
        "text": "<p>What is the full form of FASB?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Financial Accounting Standard Board",
            "Financial Accounting Standards Board",
            "Financing Accounting Standards Boards",
            "Financial Account Standard Boards"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Financial Accounting Standards Board. Check the \"s\" in Standards.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 871,
        "text": "<p>Showing Accounts Receivable at Net Realizable Value is influenced by?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Consistency",
            "Conservatism",
            "Historical Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism ensures we don't overstate our assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 872,
        "text": "<p>What is the full form of IASC?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest. Auditing Standards Committee",
