            "Historical Cost",
            "Revenue Recognition",
            "Conservatism",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard application of Conservatism.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 876,
        "text": "<p>Unpaid salary 5,000 TK (Expense) and unused stationery 700 (Asset) skipped. Impact on Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "700 less",
            "4,300 TK more",
            "5,000 TK more",
            "5,700 TK less"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit is inflated by the skipped expense (5,000 TK) and deflated by skipped asset (700). Net = 4,300 TK more.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 877,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #37) These adjustments are necessary due to which concept?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accrual",
            "Matching",
            "Revenue",
            "Historical Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Matching (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3) says you must include all costs and assets of that specific period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 878,
        "text": "<p>GAAP stands for?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
