        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Generally Accepted Accounting Principles.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 879,
        "text": "<p>Every transaction affects at least two accounts because of?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Entity Concept",
            "Dual Aspect",
            "Matching Principle",
            "Cost Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Dual Aspect (\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c8\u09a4 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09be) is the foundation of Double Entry.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 880,
        "text": "<p>Financial statements must contain all relevant information to satisfy?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Consistency",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Materiality",
            "Conservatism"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Full Disclosure (\u09aa\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u09a3 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b6) means nothing important should be hidden.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 881,
        "text": "<p>Recording transactions in \"TK\" is due to which concept?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Money Measurement",
