        "explanation": "<p>Since the business is a Going Concern, future benefits are treated as assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 889,
        "text": "<p>Accounts are kept in the name of the business due to\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Historical Cost",
            "Conservatism",
            "Entity Concept",
            "Going Concern"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Business Entity (\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09bf\u0995 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09be) separates owner and business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 890,
        "text": "<p>Which accounts are closed at the end of the year?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income & Expense",
            "Equity",
            "Liability",
            "Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Nominal (\u09a8\u09be\u09ae\u09bf\u0995) accounts (Income/Expense) are closed to the Profit & Loss Account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 891,
        "text": "<p>Bad Debt (\u0985\u09a8\u09be\u09a6\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u0993\u09a8\u09be) is adjusted based on?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Going Concern",
            "Time Period",
            "Cost Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be): We anticipate future losses (Bad Debt) to avoid overstating assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 892,
        "text": "<p>Charging expenses against revenue is done per\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Matching Principle",
            "Cost Principle",
            "Revenue Recog.",
            "Realization"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the classic definition of the Matching Principle (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 893,
        "text": "<p>Kamal & Sons uses different depreciation methods every year. Which rule is violated?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost",
            "Matching",
            "Going Concern",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Consistency (\u09b8\u09be\u09ae\u099e\u09cd\u099c\u09b8\u09cd\u09af\u09a4\u09be) requires using the same method every year for comparison.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 894,
        "text": "<p>Current assets are valued based on which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism: We value them at cost or market price, whichever is lower.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 895,
        "text": "<p>Adjusting entries are based on which concepts?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
