        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Dual Aspect (\u09a6\u09cd\u09ac\u09c8\u09a4 \u09ab\u09b2\u09be\u09ab\u09b2) is the basis of Double Entry.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 899,
        "text": "<p>Stock valued at \"Cost or Market price, whichever is lower\" is due to?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost Principle",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Conservatism",
            "Realization"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard application of Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 900,
        "text": "<p>\"Stationery is an expense, not an asset\"\u2014follows which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Materiality",
            "Conservatism",
            "Cost-Benefit",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Materiality (\u09ac\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09a4\u09be): Small items aren't worth tracking as assets; we expense them.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 901,
        "text": "<p>Concept where owner and business are separate?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Dual Aspect",
            "Time Period",
            "Business Entity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Business Entity (\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 902,
        "text": "<p>Cost Principle (\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09bc\u09ae\u09c2\u09b2\u09cd\u09af \u09a8\u09c0\u09a4\u09bf) is applicable for which assets?</p>",
