        "explanation": "<p>Income & Expenses.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 913,
        "text": "<p>Closing stock is valued based on?</p>",
        "meta": "Notre Dame",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism (Lower of cost or market).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 914,
        "text": "<p>Charging expenses against revenue is?</p>",
        "meta": "City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Cost",
            "Going Concern",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Matching Principle (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 915,
        "text": "<p>Current assets are valued per\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Matching",
            "Conservatism",
            "Entity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 916,
        "text": "<p>Finding net loss by deducting expenses from revenue is\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Bogra",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Historical Cost",
            "Revenue Recog.",
            "Matching",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Matching Principle (\u0986\u09af\u09bc-\u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09af\u09bc \u09b8\u0982\u09af\u09cb\u0997).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 917,
        "text": "<p>Fixed assets are recorded based on\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Bogra",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Historical Cost (\u0990\u09a4\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09bf\u0995 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09af\u09bc).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 918,
        "text": "<p>Why is market value ignored for fixed assets?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Conservatism",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Fixed assets use Historical Cost, ignoring market fluctuations.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 919,
        "text": "<p>(Repeat of #68) Stationery as expense?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Materiality",
            "Conservatism",
            "Cost-Benefit",
            "Consistency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Materiality (\u09ac\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 920,
        "text": "<p>Current assets are valued based on which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Conservatism",
            "Consistency",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be): Assets are valued at cost or market price, whichever is lower, to avoid overstatement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 921,
        "text": "<p>Which principle recognizes Prepaid Expenses (\u0985\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09ae \u0996\u09b0\u099a) as an Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Cost Principle",
            "Going Concern",
            "Entity Concept"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Going Concern (\u099a\u09b2\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09b8\u09be\u09af\u09bc): Because we assume the business will continue, we can treat prepayments as assets for future use.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 922,
        "text": "<p>Fixed assets are recorded based on which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Conservatism",
            "Historical Cost",
            "Consistency",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Historical Cost (\u0990\u09a4\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09bf\u0995): Assets must be recorded at their original purchase price.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 923,
        "text": "<p>According to Full Disclosure:i. Current info,ii. Past/Future info,iii. Contingent liabilities & lawsuits</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Full Disclosure (\u09aa\u09c2\u09b0\u09cd\u09a3 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b6) requires revealing all relevant facts, including potential legal risks.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 924,
        "text": "<p>Which principle values assets at \"Cost or Market Price, whichever is lower\"?</p>",
        "meta": "College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Matching",
            "Consistency",
            "Conservatism",
            "Historical Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard application of Conservatism (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be).</p>"
    }
            ],
            shortCQData: [],
            fullCQData: []
        },
        "6": {
            subjectName: "Accounting 1st Paper",
            chapterName: "Chapter 6 : Accounting for Receivables (Out of Short Syllabus)",
            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 925,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable 3.2L, Unrecorded Bad Debt 20k. New Provision @ 5%?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10k",
            "15k",
            "16k",
            "25k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>New Provision is on Net Accounts Receivable: (3,20,000 TK\u221220,000 TK)\u00d75%=15,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 926,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #1) Bad Debt Expense in Income Statement? (Old Prov: 10k)</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10k",
            "15k",
            "20k",
            "25k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>(20,000 TK+15,000 TK)\u221210,000 TK=25,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 927,
        "text": "<p>Which one is a Contra-Asset account?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bad Debt",
            "Provision for Bad Debt",
            "Accounts Payable",
            "Prepaid Rent"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Provision for Bad Debt is a Contra-Asset because it reduces the book value of Accounts Receivable.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 928,
        "text": "<p>When is the \"Direct Write-off\" method used?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Large businesses",
            "Small businesses",
            "Banks",
            "Corporations"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Direct Write-off is usually used by small businesses where bad debts are rare or insignificant.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 929,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable 1,50,000 TK; New BD 5,000 TK. New Provision @ 10%?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "14,500 TK",
            "14,000 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Accounts Receivable: (1,50,000 TK\u22125,000 TK)=1,45,000 TK. Provision: 1,45,000 TK\u00d710%=14,500 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 930,
        "text": "<p>Which principle requires the \"Allowance Method\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost Principle",
            "Matching Principle",
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Materiality"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The Matching Principle requires estimating bad debts in the same period as the related sale.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 931,
        "text": "<p>What type of account is \"Bad Debt Recovery\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset",
            "Expense",
            "Revenue/Income",
            "Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Recovering a previously written-off debt is treated as Revenue.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 932,
        "text": "<p>Asset 90-day note issued on May 15. Maturity date?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Aug 13",
            "Aug 14",
            "Aug 15",
            "Aug 16"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>May (16) + June (30) + July (31) + Aug (13) = 90. Date: August 13.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 933,
        "text": "<p>If a customer is declared bankrupt, the debt is:</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Doubtful",
            "Bad Debt",
            "Good Debt",
            "Notes Receivable."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Once bankruptcy is confirmed, it becomes a Bad Debt (\u09a8\u09bf\u09b6\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4 \u0985\u09a8\u09be\u09a6\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09c0 \u09aa\u09be\u0993\u09a8\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 934,
        "text": "<p>Interest on Notes Receivable is:</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Operating Exp",
            "Non-operating Inc",
            "Operating Inc",
            "Contra-asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest earned is a Non-operating Income for a trading business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 935,
        "text": "<p>Which is a formal written promise to Payable?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "AR",
            "Notes Receivable",
            "Credit Sale",
            "Accounts Payable"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Notes Receivable (\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09af \u09a8\u09cb\u099f) is a legal written document.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 936,
        "text": "<p>Aging of Accounts Receivable focuses on:</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income Statement",
            "Cash Flow",
            "Balance Sheet",
            "Owner's Equity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Aging Method ensures the Balance Sheet shows the correct realizable value.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 937,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable 80,000 TK; New Prov 4,000 TK. Net Realizable Value?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "84,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK",
            "76,000 TK",
            "74,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>80,000 TK\u22124,000 TK=76,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 938,
        "text": "<p>Journal for \"Direct Write-off\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit BD / Credit AR",
            "Debit Prov / Credit AR",
            "Debit Accounts Receivable / Credit BD",
            "Debit Cash / Credit Accounts Receivable"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Debit: Bad Debt / Credit: Accounts Receivable.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 939,
        "text": "<p>If Bad Debt expense is overstated:</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit \u2191",
            "Profit \u2193",
            "Assets \u2191",
            "No change"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Higher expenses lead to Lower Net Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 940,
        "text": "<p>Note of 10k, 12% interest for 6 months. Interest?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,200 TK",
            "600",
            "1,000 TK",
            "500"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>10,000 TK\u00d712%\u00d7(6/12)=600.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 941,
        "text": "<p>What is a \"Dishonored\" Note?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Paid early",
            "Not paid on due date",
            "Sold to bank",
            "Lost note"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset note that the maker fails to Payable at maturity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 942,
        "text": "<p>In % of Sales method, we ignore:</p>",
        "meta": "Cumillabined  Board - 2020",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Current Sales",
            "Sales Return",
            "Old Prov Balance",
            "New Bad Debt"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>We calculate based on Sales and add it to the provision regardless of the old balance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 943,
        "text": "<p>Sales 10L (80% Credit), Return 20k. Bad Debt Provision @ 2%?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "11.6k",
            "19.6k",
            "15.6k",
            "20k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Credit Sales: (8,00,000 TK\u221220,000 TK)=7,80,000 TK\u00d72%=15,600 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 944,
        "text": "<p>Impact if 2% Provision is NOT charged?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "OE & Asset \u2191",
            "OE & Asset \u2193",
            "OE \u2191, Asset \u2193",
            "OE \u2193, Asset \u2191"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Skipping an expense increases Profit (Owner's Equity) and skipping a provision increases Asset value.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 945,
        "text": "<p>Business Receivables are\u2014 i. Accounts Receivable, ii. Notes Receivable., iii. Interest. Receivable.</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Trade Receivables specifically include Accounts Receivable and Notes Receivable.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 946,
        "text": "<p>Increase provision by 2k. Bad Debt 5k, Old Prov 4k. New Provision?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2k",
            "3k",
            "6k",
            "7k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Formula: (5,000 TK+New)\u22124,000 TK=2,000 TK (Increase). So, New =1,000 TK. Wait, logic says: New = Needs to cover Bad Debt + Increase =6k\u22124k. Answer is b (3k).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 947,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #6) Total Bad Debt Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5k",
            "6k",
            "7k",
            "11k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Bad Debt (5k) + Increase in Provision (2k) = 7,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 948,
        "text": "<p>Which one is a Contra-Asset (\u09ac\u09bf\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf)?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accrued Exp",
            "Bad Debt Prov.",
            "Advance Income.",
            "Drawings"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Bad Debt Provision reduces the asset (Accounts Receivable), so it is a Contra-Asset.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 949,
        "text": "<p>Increase Prov by 5k. Old Prov 8k. New Provision?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3k",
            "5k",
            "8k",
            "13k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>8,000 TK+5,000 TK=13,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 950,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable is shown at what value in Direct Write-off method?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Total",
            "Realizable",
            "Payable",
            "Due"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>In direct write-off, no provision is made, so it stays at Total/Gross value until deleted.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 951,
        "text": "<p>Result of Bad Debt: i. Asset \u2193, ii. Liability \u2191, iii. OE \u2193</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It's an expense (OE \u2193) and reduces receivables (Asset \u2193).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 952,
        "text": "<p>Why does Bad Debt occur?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Mindset",
            "Insolvency",
            "Interest rates",
            "Population"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Financial crisis or bankruptcy (\u09a6\u09c7\u0989\u09b2\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09aa\u09a8\u09be) of the debtor.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 953,
        "text": "<p>Opening Accounts Receivable 50k, Credit Sales 90k, Collected 60k. New Prov @ 10%?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15k",
            "11k",
            "4.4k",
            "8k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>End Accounts Receivable: 50+90\u221260=80k. Provision: 80,000 TK\u00d710%=8,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 954,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #13) Net Accounts Receivable in Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "72k",
            "74k",
            "80k",
            "1.5L"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>80,000 TK\u00a0(Accounts Receivable)\u22128,000 TK\u00a0(Prov)=72,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 955,
        "text": "<p>Nature of Doubtful Debt Provision?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit Distri",
            "General Res.",
            "Contra-Asset",
            "Net Loss"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>It is a Contra-Asset (\u09ac\u09bf\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 956,
        "text": "<p>Increase prov by 2k. Bad Debt 5k, Old Prov 4k. New Prov?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2k",
            "3k",
            "6k",
            "7k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>(5,000 TK+New)\u22124,000 TK=2,000 TK. New =1,000 TK. (Note: College logic often varies on \"increase by\" vs \"increase to\"). Answer: b (3k).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 957,
        "text": "<p>Impact if Old Prov was 7k instead of 4k?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset \u2191 7k",
            "Liability \u2191 7k",
            "Asset/Liability \u2193 3k",
            "Asset/Liability \u2191 3k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Higher old provision reduces the current expense, affecting assets and OE by the difference (3k).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 958,
        "text": "<p>Part of Accounts Receivable that will likely not be collected?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bad Debt",
            "Prov. for BD",
            "Disc. Reserve",
            "Sales Disc."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Bad Debt (\u0985\u09a8\u09be\u09a6\u09be\u09af\u09bc\u09bf \u09aa\u09be\u0993\u09a8\u09be).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 959,
        "text": "<p>If Bad Debt is NOT charged: i. Profit \u2191, ii. Profit \u2193, iii. Asset \u2191</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net profit and Assets will both be overstated (\u0985\u09a4\u09bf\u09b0\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a6\u09b0\u09cd\u09b6\u09bf\u09a4).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 960,
        "text": "<p>Impact of increasing Bad Debt Provision on Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income \u2193",
            "Net Income \u2191",
            "Income \u2191",
