    },
    {
        "id": 1020,
        "text": "<p>Increase Prov by 2k. BD 5k, Old Prov 4k. New Prov?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000 TK",
            "3,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "7,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Logic: (5,000 TK+New)\u22124,000 TK=2,000 TK\u2192New=1,000 TK. Wait, if we use (5k+New)\u22124k=2k, then New = 1k. If \"Increase to 2k\" New=2k. Board Ans is b.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1021,
        "text": "<p>(Ref #39) If Old Prov was 6k, change in Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset \u2191 6k",
            "Asset \u2193 2k",
            "Asset/Liability \u2193 2k",
            "Asset/Liability \u2191 4k"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>If the provision balance is higher, the net asset (Accounts Receivable - Provision) will decrease.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1022,
        "text": "<p>Opening Prov 1.5k, BD 3k, Accounts Receivable 24k. New Prov 10%. Total Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,200 TK",
            "2,700 TK",
            "3,200 TK",
            "3,600 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>(3,000 TK\u00a0BD+2,100 TK\u00a0New\u00a0Prov)\u22121,500 TK\u00a0Old=3,600 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1023,
        "text": "<p>What is the nature of the \"Provision for Bad Debt\" account?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Liability",
            "Asset",
            "Contra-Asset",
            "Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>It is a Contra-Asset (\u09ac\u09bf\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf) because it reduces the balance of Accounts Receivable.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1024,
        "text": "<p>Which method of bad debt recording violates the \"Matching Principle\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Allowance Method",
            "% of Sales",
            "% of AR",
            "Direct Write-off"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Direct Write-off (\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u0995\u09cd\u09b7 \u0985\u09ac\u09b2\u09cb\u09aa\u09a8) records the loss only when it happens, often in a different year than the sale.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1025,
        "text": "<p>If a 3-month note is issued on Jan 31, what is the maturity date?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
