        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Accounts Receivable (\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09af \u09b9\u09bf\u09b8\u09be\u09ac) arises directly from the core business of selling goods/services.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1027,
        "text": "<p>What happens when a Bill of Exchange is \"Discounted\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Paid at maturity",
            "Sold to a bank",
            "Cancelled",
            "Renewed"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Discounting (\u09ac\u09be\u099f\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u0995\u09b0\u09a3) means selling the note to a bank for immediate cash at a lower value.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1028,
        "text": "<p>Journal for creating a Bad Debt Provision?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
