        "explanation": "<p>Credit Sales (\u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09c7 \u09ac\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09bc) is the primary origin of Accounts Receivable.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1031,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable is created from: (i) Credit Sales (ii) Credit Service (iii) Accrued Interest</p>",
        "meta": "Jashores  Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three result in money being owed to the business.</p>"
    },
    {
