            "Rent Expense",
            "Rent Payable",
            "Rent Received",
            "Prepaid Rent"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>As the asset (Prepaid Rent) is used up, it must be reduced by crediting it.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1156,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Capital Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Proceeds from temporary asset sale",
            "Revenue from goods sale",
            "Profit on sale of fixed asset",
            "Additional capital brought in"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit made above the book value when selling a fixed asset is considered capital income.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1157,
        "text": "<p>Which accounting system records revenues and expenses related to the current year?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cash basis",
            "Accrual basis",
            "Accrual & Advance basis",
            "Cash & Accrual basis"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The accrual basis records transactions when they occur, regardless of the timing of cash flows.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1158,
        "text": "<p>What is the reversing entry for Accrued Interest on Loan?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
