        "9": {
            subjectName: "Accounting 1st Paper",
            chapterName: "Chapter 9 : Financial Statements",
            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 1258,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is NOT shown in the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "General Reserve",
            "Special Reserve",
            "Secret Reserve",
            "Capital Reserve"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Secret Reserves are hidden and not disclosed on the face of financial statements.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1259,
        "text": "<p>If Profit on Sales is 20 TK\\%TK, what is the profit percentage on Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "16.67 TK\\%TK",
            "20 TK\\%TK",
            "25 TK\\%TK",
            "33.33 TK\\%TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>If Sales = 100 TK and Profit = 20 TK, Cost = 80 TK. Profit on Cost = (20 TK/80) \\times 100 = 25\\%TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1260,
        "text": "<p>To determine Net Purchase, what should be deducted from Purchase?\n\ni. Purchase Discount\n\nii. Carriage Inward\n\niii. Purchase Return</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Purchase returns and discounts reduce the total purchase amount. Carriage inward is an addition, not a deduction.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1261,
        "text": "<p>Closing stock cost 40,000 TK, market value 30,000 TK. Includes 5,000 TK fire-damaged goods. Final Closing Stock value?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "40,000 TK",
            "35,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Follow \"Lower of Cost or Market\": 30,000 TK is base. Subtract damaged goods: 30,000 TK - 5,000 TK = 25,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1262,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stem above (Q8), what is the amount of Current Assets? (Insurance covers 40 TK\\%TK of 5,000 TK loss)</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "40,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "27,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Assets = Closing Stock (25,000 TK) + Insurance Claim Receivable (5,000 TK \\times 40\\% = 2,000 TK) = 27,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1263,
        "text": "<p>If Bad Debt is not charged\u2014\n\ni. Net Profit overstated\n\nii. Net Profit understated\n\niii. Asset value overstated</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Omitting an expense makes profit look higher (overstated) and prevents accounts receivable from decreasing (asset overstated).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1264,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance: 15 TK\\%TK Investment (31 TK-03 TK-2024 TK) 50,000 TK. Interest received 1,500 TK. Total interest for the year?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,500 TK",
            "4,125 TK",
            "5,625 TK",
            "7,125 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest for 9 TK months: (50,000 TK \\times 15\\% \\times 9/12 TK) = 5,625 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1265,
        "text": "<p>Non-operating expenses include\u2014\n\ni. Interest on Investment\n\nii. Interest on Loan\n\niii. Miscellaneous Expenses</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest on loan is a financing (non-operating) cost. Interest on investment is income, not expense.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1266,
        "text": "<p>Elements of financial position are\u2014\n\ni. Assets\n\nii. Liabilities\n\niii. Owner's Equity</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These three components make up the basic accounting equation: Assets = Liabilities + Owner's Equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1267,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold is 5,00,000 TK. Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales. What is the total Sales amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,25,000 TK",
            "6,00,000 TK",
            "5,17,500 TK",
            "5,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>If Sales is 100 TK\\%TK and Profit 20 TK\\%TK, Cost of Goods Sold is 80 TK\\%TK. Sales = (5,00,000 TK / 80) \\times 100 = 6,25,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1268,
        "text": "<p>To increase Net Profit rate while Gross Profit rate is fixed\u2014\n\ni. Increase sales\n\nii. Decrease operating expenses\n\niii. Increase non-operating income</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net profit depends on what happens after Gross Profit. Cutting costs (ii) or adding other income (iii) works.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1269,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock + Net Purchase + Direct Expenses - Closing Stock = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost of Goods Sold",
            "Adjusted Purchase",
            "Cost of Production",
            "Total Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the standard formula for Cost of Goods Sold (\u09ac\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09aa\u09a3\u09cd\u09af\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09af\u09bc).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1270,
        "text": "<p>Operating expenses are\u2014\n\ni. Office Rent\n\nii. Advertisement\n\niii. Interest on Loan</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Office rent and ads are part of daily operations. Loan interest is a non-operating financing cost.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1271,
        "text": "<p>Opening 22 TKkTK, Purchase 1.35 TKLTK, Wages 10 TKkTK, Sales 3.75 TKLTK, Closing 36 TKkTK. Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,08,000 TK",
            "2,44,000 TK",
            "2,54,000 TK",
            "2,66,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 22 TKk+1.35L+10k-36k = 1,31,000 TK. Gross Profit = Sales (3.75 TKLTK) - Cost of Goods Sold (1.31 TKLTK) = 2,44,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1272,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stem above (Q18), what is the Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,09,000 TK",
            "1,21,000 TK",
            "1,31,000 TK",
            "2,03,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = Opening (22,000 TK) + Purchase (1,35,000 TK) + Wages (10,000 TK) - Closing (36,000 TK) = 1,31,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1273,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is Non-operating Income?\n\ni. Interest Received\n\nii. Discount Received\n\niii. Profit on Sale of Asset</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest and profit on asset sales are non-operational. Discount received is an operating item related to purchases.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1274,
        "text": "<p>Gross Profit - Operating Expenses = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Net Profit",
            "Gross Profit",
            "Operating Profit",
            "Net Profit after Tax"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Operating Profit is derived by subtracting operating expenses (admin & selling) from Gross Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1275,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold 2,00,000 TK; Gross Profit 1,00,000 TK. What is the amount of Sales?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "2,50,000 TK",
            "3,00,000 TK",
            "3,30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales = Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit = 2,00,000 TK + 1,00,000 TK = 3,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1276,
        "text": "<p>Gross Profit 1,50,000 TK; Operating Expense 1,00,000 TK; Interest on Loan 20,000 TK; Discount Receivable. 30,000 TK. Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "80,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit = (Gross Profit 1,50,000 TK - Opening Expense 1,00,000 TK) + Non-Opening Income 30,000 TK - Non-Opening Expense 20,000 TK = 60,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1277,
        "text": "<p>Who has the claim over Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debtor",
            "Owner",
            "Bank",
            "Government"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit belongs to the owner(s) and is added to the Owner's Equity in the Balance Sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1278,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Payable Opening 5,000 TK; Closing 8,000 TK; Purchase Return 2,000 TK; Paid to Creditors 20,000 TK. Credit Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "18,000 TK",
            "19,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK",
            "21,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Credit Purchase = (Closing 8k + Paid 20k + Return 2k) - Opening 5k = 25,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1279,
        "text": "<p>Stock Cost 1,00,000 TK; Market 8,000 TK less than cost. Includes Unused Stationery 2,000 TK. Final Stock Value?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "90,000 TK",
            "92,000 TK",
            "94,000 TK",
            "98,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Lower of Cost/Market = 92,000 TK. Subtract non-stock items: 92,000 TK - 2,000 TK = 90,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1280,
        "text": "<p>If Market Value is 5,000 TK HIGHER than cost, in the Balance Sheet\u2014\n\ni. Assets \u2191\n\nii. Net Profit \u2191\n\niii. Equity \u2191</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Following the prudence concept, we usually use cost if it's lower. However, if market value is correctly used/rises, it inflates assets and profits.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1281,
        "text": "<p>Net Sales 3,90,000 TK; Gross Profit rate 40%; Net Profit is 30% of Gross Profit. Indirect Expenses?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,09,200 TK",
            "1,12,000 TK",
            "2,34,000 TK",
            "2,73,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = 3,90k * 40% = 1,56,000 TK. NP = 1,56k * 30% = 46,800 TK. Indirect Expense = 1,56,000 TK - 46,800 TK = 1,09,200 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1282,
        "text": "<p>What type of asset is \"Preliminary Expenses\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fixed Asset",
            "Current Asset",
            "Fictitious Asset",
            "Intangible Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Preliminary expenses are fictitious assets (\u0985\u09b2\u09c0\u09c7\u0995 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a6) as they have no real resale value and are written off over time.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1283,
        "text": "<p>If VAT Received > VAT Paid, the difference is called\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Current Asset",
            "Current Liability",
            "Revenue Income",
            "Revenue Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Excess VAT collected from customers over VAT paid to suppliers is a liability (VAT Payable) to the government.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1284,
        "text": "<p>Sales 50,000 TK; Opening Expense 3,200 TK; Cost of Goods Sold 30,000 TK; Discount Receivable. 2,000 TK. Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "16,800 TK",
            "18,800 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "22,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = Sales (50,000 TK) - Cost of Goods Sold (30,000 TK) = 20,000 TK (Other items are for Net Profit).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1285,
        "text": "<p>Sales - Cost of Goods Sold - Operating Expenses = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Gross Profit/Loss",
            "Concept Profit",
            "Operating Profit/Loss",
            "Estimated Profit"
