    {
        "id": 1298,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stimulus below, answer the following question:\nPinky Traders' Partial Trial Balance and Adjustments are as follows:\nPartial Trial Balance\nParticulars | Debit (TK) | Credit (TK)\nAccounts Receivable | 61,000 TK |\nBad Debt | 2,000 TK |\nAllowance for Bad Debt | | 3,500 TK\nAdjustment: 1,000 TK of Accounts Receivable is not collectible and Allowance for Bad Debt must be increased to 5,000 TK\nQ. At what amount will Accounts Receivable be shown in the Statement of Financial Position?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Debit (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Credit (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Accounts Receivable</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">61,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\"></td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Bad Debt</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\"></td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Allowance for Bad Debt</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\"></td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">3,500 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "55,000 TK",
            "56,500 TK",
            "57,500 TK",
            "58,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Accounts Receivable = Initial Accounts Receivable - New Bad Debt - New Provision61,000 TK - 1,000 TK - 5,000 TK = \\mathbf{55,000 TK}TKIn the Statement of Financial Position, Accounts Receivable will be shown as 55,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1299,
        "text": "<p>Sales including 15 TK\\%TK VAT 1,18,000 TK. Sales Return 3,000 TK. Amount of Output VAT?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "15,391 TK",
            "17,250 TK",
            "17,700 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Sales = 1,18,000 TK - 3,000 TK = 1,15,000 TK. VAT = (1,15,000 TK \\times 15 / 115 TK) = 15,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1300,
        "text": "<p>VAT collected/received by a seller is a/an\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Expense",
            "Asset",
            "Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>VAT collected from customers is a liability because the business must Payable it to the government.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1301,
        "text": "<p>Formula for Cost of Goods Sold (Cost of Goods Sold) is\u2014\n\ni. Cost of Goods Available for Sale - Closing Stock\n\nii. Sales - Gross Profit\n\niii. Adjusted Purchase + Direct Expenses</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are valid mathematical ways to calculate Cost of Goods Sold depending on the available information.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1302,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stimulus below, answer the following question:\nSome accounting information of Padma Enterprise is given below:\nParticulars | 2023 | 2024\nGross Profit | 2,10,000 TK | 2,60,000 TK\nNet Profit | 31,500 TK | ?\nIn 2024, Office and Administrative Expenses were 1,77,000 TK (including Depreciation of 77,000 TK), Selling and Distribution Expenses were 80,000 TK, and Miscellaneous Income was 20,000 TK\nQ. What is the amount of Net Profit for Padma Enterprise in 2024?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2023</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2024</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Gross Profit</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,10,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,60,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Net Profit</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">31,500 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">?</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,000 TK",
            "23,000 TK",
            "39,000 TK",
            "83,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The formula for Net Profit is:Net Profit = (Gross Profit - Total Operating Expenses) + Other IncomeCalculation: TK(2,60,000 TK - 2,57,000 TK) + 20,000 TKCalculation: 3,000 TK + 20,000 TK = \\mathbf{23,000 TK}TKNet Profit for 2024 is 23,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1303,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stimulus below, answer the following question:\nSome accounting information of Padma Enterprise is given below:\nParticulars | 2023 | 2024\nGross Profit | 2,10,000 TK | 2,60,000 TK\nNet Profit | 31,500 TK | ?\nIn 2024, Office and Administrative Expenses were 1,77,000 TK (including Depreciation of 77,000 TK), Selling and Distribution Expenses were 80,000 TK, and Miscellaneous Income was 20,000 TK\nQ. What is the amount of Operating Expenses for the year 2023?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2023</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2024</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Gross Profit</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,10,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,60,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Net Profit</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">31,500 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">?</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "31,500 TK",
            "2,10,000 TK",
            "1,78,500 TK",
            "2,57,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>To find the Operating Expenses, we subtract the Net Profit from the Gross Profit:\n\nGross Profit: 2,10,000 TK\n\n(-) Net Profit: 31,500 TK\n\nOperating Expenses: 1,78,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1304,
        "text": "<p>Profit on Sales is 20 TK\\%TK. What is the profit percentage on Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50 TK\\%TK",
            "33.33 TK\\%TK",
            "25 TK\\%TK",
            "16.67 TK\\%TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>(20 TK / 80) \\times 100 = 25\\%TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1305,
        "text": "<p>Net Profit increases what?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Asset",
            "Liability",
            "Owner's Equity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Net profit is added to the Capital, thus increasing Owner's Equity (\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a7\u09bf\u0995\u09be\u09b0).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1306,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock 10 TKkTK, Purchase 100 TKkTK, Return 7.5 TKkTK, Discount 2.5 TKkTK, Wages 3 TKkTK, Excise Duty 12 TKkTK, Closing 25 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "75,000 TK",
            "87,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK",
            "1,25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 10 TKk + (100k-7.5k-2.5k) + 3k + 12k - 25k = 90,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1307,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q53, if profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales, what is the Gross Profit amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "18,000 TK",
            "18,750 TK",
            "22,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>If Sales is 100 TK\\%TK, Cost of Goods Sold is 80 TK\\%TK. 90,000 TK is 80 TK\\%TK. Total Sales = 1,12,500 TK. Gross Profit = 1,12,500 TK \\times 20\\% = 22,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1308,
        "text": "<p>Interest received 5,000 TK, accrued 500 TK. Rate 10 TK\\%TK. Total Investment amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,000 TK",
            "5,500 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "55,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Interest = 5,000 TK + 500 = 5,500 TK. Investment = (5,500 TK / 10\\%TK) = 55,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1309,
        "text": "<p>Salary paid 30,000 TK, including 3 TK months advance. Current year salary expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,000 TK",
            "24,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "36,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>30,000 TK is for 15 TK months (12 TK+3 TK). Monthly = 2,000 TK. Current year (12 TK months) = 24,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1310,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Fictitious Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Copyright",
            "Goodwill",
            "Leasehold Property",
            "Underwriter's Commission"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Underwriter's commission is a deferred expense (fictitious asset). The others are intangible/fixed assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1311,
        "text": "<p>Purchase incl. VAT 71,000 TK; Return 2,000 TK. Input VAT amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,950 TK",
            "10,650 TK",
            "9,000 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Purchase = 71 TKk - 2k = 69,000 TK. VAT = 69,000 TK \\times 15/115 = 9,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1312,
        "text": "<p>If Profit on Cost is 25 TK\\%TK, what is the profit percentage on Sales?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20 TK\\%TK",
            "25 TK\\%TK",
            "30 TK\\%TK",
            "35 TK\\%TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>If Cost = 100 TK and Profit = 25 TK, Sales = 125 TK. Profit on Sales = (25 TK/125) \\times 100 = 20\\%TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1313,
        "text": "<p>If Net Profit increases from TK 60,000 TK to TK 80,000 TK, what is the effect on Total Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increase by 20 TKkTK",
            "Decrease by 20 TKkTK",
            "Increase by 80 TKkTK",
            "Decrease by 80 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net profit is an addition to Equity, and according to TKA=Liability+ETK, an increase in profit (retained) reflects an equal increase in assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1314,
        "text": "<p>Purchase TK 4,00,000 TK; Opening Stock TK 30,000 TK; Cost of Goods Sold TK 3,00,000 TK; Gross Profit TK 2,00,000 TK. Sales?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 5,00,000 TK",
            "TK 5,30,000 TK",
            "TK 6,00,000 TK",
            "TK 7,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales = Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit = 3,00,000 TK + 2,00,000 TK = 5,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1315,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q63, what is the value of Closing Stock?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 70,000 TK",
            "TK 1,00,000 TK",
            "TK 1,30,000 TK",
            "TK 1,70,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Stock = (Opening. Stock + Purchase) - Cost of Goods Sold = (30 TKk + 4,00kTK) - 3,00 TKk = 1,30,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1316,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is part of Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Carriage Inward",
            "Office Rent",
            "Salary & Wages",
            "Carriage Outward"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Carriage Inward (\u0986\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u0983\u09aa\u09b0\u09bf\u09ac\u09b9\u09a8) is a direct expense related to bringing goods to the warehouse.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1317,
        "text": "<p>Manager gets 10 TK\\%TK commission on Net Profit. Profit after commission is TK 44,000 TK. Commission?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 4,000 TK",
            "TK 4,400 TK",
            "TK 39,600 TK",
            "TK 40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>If 44,000 TK is the profit after commission, it represents the 100 TK\\%TK base. Commission = 44,000 TK \\times 10\\% = 4,400 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1318,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 60 TKkTK; Cost of Goods Pur. 3.8 TKLTK; Closing. Stock 50 TKkTK; Opening. Expense 15 TKkTK; Sales 4.5 TKLTK. Gross Profit & NP?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10 TKkTK & 5 TKkTK",
            "20 TKkTK & 5 TKkTK",
            "60 TKkTK & 45 TKkTK",
            "60 TKkTK & 45 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 60 TKk+3.8L-50k = 3.9LTK. Gross Profit = 4.5 TKL-3.9L=60kTK. NP = 60 TKk-15k=45,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1319,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q67, what is the Cost of Goods Sold (Cost of Goods Sold)?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 3,30,000 TK",
            "TK 3,90,000 TK",
            "TK 4,30,000 TK",
            "TK 4,40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = Opening Stock + Cost of Goods Purchased - Closing Stock = 60,000 TK + 3,80,000 TK - 50,000 TK = 3,90,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1320,
        "text": "<p>Headers written while preparing a Balance Sheet include\u2014\n\ni. Name of Entity\n\nii. Name of Statement\n\niii. Date of preparation</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset complete heading requires the business name, the statement name, and the specific date (e.g., \"As of Dec 31\").</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1321,
        "text": "<p>Asset company forgot to adjust TK 35,000 TK for outstanding salary. Impact?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "NP understated 35 TKkTK",
            "NP overstated 35 TKkTK",
            "Equity \u2193 35 TKkTK",
            "Assets \u2193 35 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Omitting an expense makes the profit look higher (overstated) than it actually is.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1322,
        "text": "<p>Closing Capital 30 TKkTK which is 25 TK\\%TK less than Opening Capital. Interest on Capital @ 5 TK\\%TK?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 1,125 TK",
            "TK 1,500 TK",
            "TK 1,875 TK",
            "TK 2,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>30 TKkTK is 75 TK\\%TK of Opening. Capital. Opening. Capital = 30 TKk / 0.75 = 40,000 TK. Interest = 40,000 TK \\times 5\\% = 2,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1323,
        "text": "<p>Assets TK 5 TKLTK; Opening. Capital TK 2 TKLTK; NP TK 50 TKkTK; Drawings TK 40 TKkTK. If Assets become 4.8 TKLTK, effect on Internal Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest. Liability \u2191 20 TKkTK",
            "Interest. Liability \u2193 20 TKkTK",
            "Unchanged",
            "Interest. Liability \u2193 40 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Internal Liability (Equity) is determined by Capital, Profit, and Drawings. Total assets changing doesn't change Equity unless the Profit/Capital figures change.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1324,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q72, what is the amount of External Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 2,10,000 TK",
            "TK 2,50,000 TK",
            "TK 2,80,000 TK",
            "TK 2,90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Equity = 2 TKL + 50k - 40k = 2.1LTK. Ext. Liability = Assets (5 TKLTK) - Equity (2.1 TKLTK) = 2.9 TKLTK (2,90,000 TK).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1325,
        "text": "<p>If 10 TK\\%TK Bad Debt Allowance is charged on Accounts Receivable, impact on financial position?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Liability \u2193 & Equity \u2191",
            "Asset \u2191 & Equity \u2191",
            "Asset \u2193 & Equity \u2193",
            "Asset \u2191 & Liability \u2191"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Allowance reduces Net Accounts Receivable (Asset \u2193) and the corresponding expense reduces Net Profit (Equity \u2193).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1326,
        "text": "<p>What is found by adding Gross Profit to the Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales",
            "Purchase",
            "Operating Expense",
            "Operating Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The basic relationship is: Sales = Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1327,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Capital 1.5 TKLTK; Drawings 10 TKkTK; Cost of Goods Sold 1.5 TKLTK; Sales 2.5 TKLTK; Net Profit 60 TKkTK. Closing Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 80,000 TK",
            "TK 90,000 TK",
            "TK 2,00,000 TK",
            "TK 2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Capital = Opening. Capital + Net Profit - Drawings = 1,50,000 TK + 60,000 TK - 10,000 TK = 2,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1328,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q76, if Cost of Goods Sold increases by 10 TK\\%TK, effect on Financial Statements?\n\ni. NP \u2191\n\nii. NP \u2193\n\niii. Equity \u2193</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Increased Cost of Goods Sold reduces Gross Profit, which in turn reduces Net Profit (ii) and Equity (iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1329,
        "text": "<p>Gross Profit is 10 TK\\%TK of Sales. If Gross Profit is TK 20,000 TK, then Sales is\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 1,63,636 TK",
            "TK 1,80,000 TK",
            "TK 2,00,000 TK",
            "TK 2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales = Gross Profit / Rate = 20,000 TK / 0.10 = 2,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1330,
        "text": "<p>VAT is included in Sales. What type of account is VAT?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Expense",
            "Liability",
            "Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Collected VAT is a liability (VAT Payable) that must be remitted to the government.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1331,
        "text": "<p>Stock TK 65 TKkTK; incl. 7 TKkTK fire loss (80 TK\\%TK insured) and Unused Supplies 4 TKkTK. Effect of fire on Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income \u2193 1,400 TK",
            "Income \u2191 5,600 TK",
            "Expense \u2193 5,600 TK",
            "Expense \u2191 1,400 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Loss = Total Loss (7,000 TK) - Ins. Claim (7,000 TK \\times 80\\% = 5,600 TK) = 1,400 TK This is an expense.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1332,
        "text": "<p>Closing Stock valued at TK 65,000 TK. Includes TK 7,000 TK fire loss and TK 4,000 TK unused supplies. Actual Closing Stock?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 54,000 TK",
            "TK 55,400 TK",
            "TK 63,600 TK",
            "TK 76,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Actual Stock = 65,000 TK - 7,000 TK (Fire loss) - 4,000 TK (Supplies) = 54,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1333,
        "text": "<p>Sales TK 2,00,000 TK; Closing Stock TK 30,000 TK; Cost of Goods Sold TK 1,40,000 TK. What is the Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 30,000 TK",
            "TK 60,000 TK",
            "TK 90,000 TK",
            "TK 1,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = Sales - Cost of Goods Sold = 2,00,000 TK - 1,40,000 TK = 60,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1334,
        "text": "<p>Sales 2 TKLTK; Cost of Goods Sold 1.4 TKLTK; Opening. Expense is 50 TK\\%TK of Cost of Goods Sold. Effect of Net Profit/Loss on Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit=60 TKkTK. Opening. Expense = 1.4 TKL \\times 50\\% = 70kTK. Net Loss = 10 TKkTK. Loss reduces Capital (i) and Internal Liability (iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1335,
        "text": "<p>Who can claim the Net Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Owner",
            "Government",
            "Investor",
            "Lender"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Income belongs to the owner of the business and is added to their equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1336,
        "text": "<p>On which concept are financial statements prepared?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Going Concern",
            "Business Entity",
            "Monetary Unit",
            "Periodicity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Periodicity (\u09b8\u09ae\u09df\u0995\u09be\u09b2 \u09a7\u09be\u09b0\u09a3\u09be) dictates that business life is divided into specific periods to report performance.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1337,
        "text": "<p>What is Capital for a business organization?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset",
            "Income",
            "Internal Liability",
            "External Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital is the obligation of the business towards its owner, hence an Internal Liability (\u0985\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09cd\u09a6\u09be\u09df).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1338,
        "text": "<p>Prepaid Rent TK 20,000 TK expired. Effect on Financial Statements?\n\ni. Prepaid Rent \u2193 20 TKkTK\n\nii. Current Assets \u2193 20 TKkTK\n\niii. Rent Expense \u2193 20 TKkTK</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Expiry reduces the asset (Prepaid Rent) and increases the expense. It does not decrease the expense.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1339,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock TK 60 TKkTK. Net Purchase TK 1.5 TKLTK. Closing Stock Cost TK 30 TKkTK. Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 60,000 TK",
            "TK 90,000 TK",
            "TK 1,80,000 TK",
            "TK 2,40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Adjusted Purchase = Opening. Stock + Net Purchase - Closing Stock = 60 TKk + 1.5L - 30k = 1,80,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1340,
        "text": "<p>Sales 80.7 TKkTK; Cost of Goods Sold 50.5 TKkTK; Opening. Expense 10 TKkTK. Gross Profit and Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30.2 TKkTK & 20.3 TKkTK",
            "30.2 TKkTK & 20.2 TKkTK",
            "40.5 TKkTK & 20.2 TKkTK",
            "70.7 TKkTK & 30.2 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = 80,700 TK - 50,500 TK = 30,200 TK. NP = 30,200 TK - 10,000 TK = 20,200 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1341,
        "text": "<p>Rent paid is 125 TK\\%TK equal to TK 50,000 TK. What is the amount of Prepaid Rent?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 10,000 TK",
            "TK 12,500 TK",
            "TK 40,000 TK",
            "TK 50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>125 TK\\% = 50,000 TK. 100 TK\\% = 40,000 TK. Prepaid (25 TK\\%TK) = 50,000 TK - 40,000 TK = 10,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1342,
        "text": "<p>Ad paid TK 10,000 TK for 5 TK years. Amount to be written off at year-end?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 10,000 TK",
            "TK 8,000 TK",
            "TK 6,000 TK",
            "TK 2,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Annual write-off = Total / Years = 10,000 TK / 5 = 2,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1343,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 60 TKkTK; Net Pur. 1.5 TKLTK; Closing Stock Cost 30 TKkTK. If Market Value of Closing. Stock is 20 TKkTK, effect on Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "\u2191 10 TKkTK",
            "\u2193 10 TKkTK",
            "\u2193 20 TKkTK",
            "\u2191 20 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Using 20 TKkTK instead of 30 TKkTK increases Cost of Goods Sold by 10 TKkTK, which reduces Gross Profit by 10,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1344,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Non-operating expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Office Rent",
            "Interest on Loan",
            "Bad Debt",
            "Advertisement"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest on loan is a financing cost, separate from the main business operations.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1345,
        "text": "<p>Through which statement are financial results (profit/loss) known?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income Statement",
            "Cash Flow",
            "Balance Sheet",
            "Equity Statement"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The Comprehensive Income Statement (\u09ac\u09bf\u09b6\u09a6 \u0986\u09df \u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0\u09a3\u09c0) shows the profit or loss for the period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1346,
        "text": "<p>Prepaid Insurance 1.2 TKLTK in Trial Balance (paid on 01 TK-04 TK-23 TK for 2 TK yrs). Year ends 30 TK-06 TK-23 TK. Insurance Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 15,000 TK",
            "TK 60,000 TK",
            "TK 30,000 TK",
            "TK 1,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Monthly = 1,20,000 TK / 24 = 5,000 TK. Expense for 3 TK months (April-June) = 5,000 TK \\times 3 = 15,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1347,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q95, omitting insurance expense violates which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Full Disclosure",
            "Going Concern",
            "Periodicity",
            "Matching"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The Matching Principle (\u09ae\u09bf\u09b2\u0995\u09b0\u09a3 \u09a8\u09c0\u09a4\u09bf) requires matching revenues with the expenses incurred to earn them in the same period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1348,
        "text": "<p>Invested 1.2 TKLTK @ 10 TK\\%TK. On Dec 31, accrued interest 5,000 TK was adjusted. When was the investment made?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "August-1",
            "September-1",
            "October-1",
            "November-1"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Annual Interest = 12 TKkTK. Monthly = 1 TKkTK. 5,000 TK Interest means 5 TK months (Aug, Sept, Oct, Nov, Dec). So, August 1.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1349,
        "text": "<p>Operating expenses are\u2014\n\ni. Purchase of goods\n\nii. Advertisement\n\niii. Interest on Loan</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Only advertisement is an operating expense. Purchase is part of Cost of Goods Sold, and loan interest is non-operating.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1350,
        "text": "<p>What type of account is VAT for a seller?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Liability",
            "Asset",
            "Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>VAT collected from customers is a debt owed to the government.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1351,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 50 TKkTK. Net Purchase 1.25 TKLTK. Closing Stock Cost 15 TKkTK. Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 90,000 TK",
            "TK 1,10,000 TK",
            "TK 1,60,000 TK",
            "TK 1,60,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Adjusted Purchase = Opening Stock + Net Purchase - Closing Stock = 50,000 TK + 1,25,000 TK - 15,000 TK = 1,60,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1352,
        "text": "<p>Closing. Stock cost TK 15,000 TK. If Market Value is TK 12,000 TK, effect on Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2024",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Decrease by 3 TKkTK",
            "Increase by 3 TKkTK",
            "Decrease by 12 TKkTK",
            "Increase by 12 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>We use the lower value (12 TKkTK instead of 15 TKkTK). Since Closing. Stock is subtracted from cost, a lower value means higher Cost of Goods Sold, which decreases Gross Profit by 3,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1353,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Revenue Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Purchase",
            "Wages",
            "Sales",
            "Sale of Furniture"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales is the primary revenue income (\u09ae\u09c1\u09a8\u09be\u09ab\u09be \u099c\u09be\u09a4\u09c0\u09df \u0986\u09df) for a trading business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1354,
        "text": "<p>What type of asset is \"Cash at Bank\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Current Asset",
            "Fixed Asset",
            "Intangible Asset",
            "Fictitious Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash at bank is a liquid asset that can be used within a year, making it a Current Asset.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1355,
        "text": "<p>To adjust Additional Capital in Balance Sheet\u2014\n\ni. Add to Investment\n\nii. Add to Cash\n\niii. Add to Capital</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Additional capital increases both the asset (Cash) and the liability toward the owner (Capital).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1356,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an Indirect Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Carriage Inward",
            "Export Duty",
            "Dock Charges",
            "Import Duty"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Export duty (\u09b0\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4\u09be\u09a8\u09bf \u09b6\u09c1\u09b2\u09cd\u0995) is a selling expense (indirect), while others are direct expenses related to purchase.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1357,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Fictitious Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accrued Income",
            "Preliminary Expense",
            "Prepaid Insur.",
            "Accounts Receivable."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Preliminary expenses (\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a5\u09ae\u09bf\u0995 \u0996\u09b0\u099a) are capitalized costs with no resale value, classified as fictitious.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1358,
        "text": "<p>Financial Statements include\u2014\n\ni. Income Statement\n\nii. Equity Statement\n\niii. Balance Sheet</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These are the three core components of a complete set of financial statements at this level.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1359,
        "text": "<p>Which is a Revenue Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sub-let Rent",
            "Apprentice Allow.",
            "Unearned Rent",
            "Profit on Asset Sale"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Sub-let rent (\u0989\u09aa\u09ad\u09be\u09dc\u09be) is a regular operating/non-operating income for the business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1360,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 20 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 40 TKkTK, Pur. 90 TKkTK, Carriage Inward 10 TKkTK, Sales 1.2 TKLTK. Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 20 TKk+90k+10k-40k = 80kTK. Gross Profit = 1,20,000 TK - 80,000 TK = 40,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1361,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q109, what is the Cost of Goods Sold (Cost of Goods Sold)?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = Opening Stock + Purchase + Carriage Inward - Closing Stock = 20 TKk + 90k + 10k - 40k = 80,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1362,
        "text": "<p>Under which heading is \"Mortgage Loan\" placed?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Reserve & Surplus",
            "Current Liability",
            "Provisions",
            "Long-term Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Mortgage loans are typically repaid over several years, classifying them as Long-term Liabilities.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1363,
        "text": "<p>Purposes of Income Statement are\u2014\n\ni. Determine Gross Profit/Loss\n\nii. Determine NP/Loss\n\niii. Determine Tax Liability</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>It measures operational performance and the resulting profit which is the base for tax calculation.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1364,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 50 TKkTK, Free goods 10 TKkTK. Total Ad written off over 4 TK years. Deferred Ad?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "12,500 TK",
            "15,000 TK",
            "37,500 TK",
            "45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Total = 60 TKkTK. Current Expense (1 TK/4 TK) = 15 TKkTK. Deferred (3 TK/4 TK) = 45,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1365,
        "text": "<p>Sales incl. VAT 59,000 TK. Return 1,500 TK. Sales VAT amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "7,500 TK",
            "7,695 TK",
            "8,625 TK",
            "8,850 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Sales = 59 TKk - 1.5k = 57,500 TK. VAT = 57,500 TK \\times 15/115 = 7,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1366,
        "text": "<p>Which group represents Fictitious Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Goodwill/Disc. on Share",
            "Patent/Copyright",
            "on Share\n\nb) Patent/Copyright\n\nc) Trademark/Def. Ad",
            "Prelim. Expense/Commission."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Preliminary expenses and Underwriter's commission are classic examples of fictitious assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1367,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 40 TKkTK, Net Pur. 1.5 TKLTK, Export Duty 15 TKkTK, Closing. Stock Cost 30 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,60,000 TK",
            "1,75,000 TK",
            "1,90,000 TK",
            "2,05,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 40 TKk + 1.5L - 30k = 1,60,000 TK (Export duty is an indirect selling expense, so not in Cost of Goods Sold).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1368,
        "text": "<p>From Q116: If Closing. Stock Market Value is 20 TKkTK and Gross Profit rate is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales, Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "40,000 TK",
            "42,500 TK",
            "46,250 TK",
            "47,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>New Cost of Goods Sold = 40 TKk+1.5L-20k = 1.7LTK. If Gross Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on sales, it's 25 TK\\%TK on cost. Gross Profit = 1.7 TKL \\times 25\\% = 42,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1369,
        "text": "<p>Loan 1 TKLTK, Accrued Interest 12 TKkTK, Accounts Payable 40 TKkTK, Unearned Rent 40 TKkTK, Fixed Asset 3 TKLTK. Current Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "52,000 TK",
            "92,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,92,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Liability = Accrued Interest (12 TKkTK) + Accounts Payable (40 TKkTK) + Unearned Rent (40 TKkTK) = 92,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1370,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q118, what is the Total Liability of the firm?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "1,92,000 TK",
            "6,92,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Liability = Loan (1 TKLTK) + Current Liability (92 TKkTK) = 1,92,000 TK (Capital is owner's equity, not external Liability).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1371,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an Intangible Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Patent",
            "Machine",
            "Land",
            "Furniture"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Patent (\u09aa\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f) is an intangible asset; the rest are tangible fixed assets.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1372,
        "text": "<p>According to IAS-01, how many components are there in a complete set of Financial Statements?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2 TK<br)",
            "3 TK",
            "4 TK",
            "5 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>IAS-01 specifies 5 parts: Income Statement, Balance Sheet, Equity Statement, Cash Flow, and Notes.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1373,
        "text": "<p>What is the primary objective of an Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Net Asset",
            "Net Income/Loss",
            "Gross Profit/Loss",
            "Growth in Assets"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The ultimate goal of the Income Statement is to determine the final Net Profit or Loss for the period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1374,
        "text": "<p>Adjustments must be made in the Income Statement for\u2014\n\ni. Depreciation\n\nii. Bad Debt\n\niii. Loan taken</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Depreciation and Bad Debt are expenses. Taking a loan is a balance sheet (liability) item and not an adjustment for revenue/expense.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1375,
        "text": "<p>Purchase TK 1,00,000 TK; Opening. Stock TK 10,000 TK; Cost of Goods Sold TK 90,000 TK; Gross Profit TK 30,000 TK. Sales?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 1,00,000 TK",
            "TK 1,20,000 TK",
            "TK 17,000 TK",
            "TK 1,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales = Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit = 90,000 TK + 30,000 TK = 1,20,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1376,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q124, what is the amount of Closing Stock?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 15,000 TK",
            "TK 20,000 TK",
            "TK 25,000 TK",
            "TK 30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing. Stock = (Opening. Stock + Purchase) - Cost of Goods Sold = (10 TKk + 100kTK) - 90 TKk = 20,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1377,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 30 TKkTK; Free goods 20 TKkTK. If 3 TK/4 TK is to be deferred, amount of Deferred Ad?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 7,500 TK",
            "TK 12,500 TK",
            "TK 22,500 TK",
            "TK 37,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Ad = 30 TKk + 20k = 50kTK. Deferred = 50,000 TK \\times 3/4 = 37,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1378,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Direct Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Rent",
            "Wages",
            "Commission",
            "Advertisement"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Wages (\u09ae\u099c\u09c1\u09b0\u09bf) are directly related to production or acquisition of goods, hence a direct expense.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1379,
        "text": "<p>Sales 20 TKkTK; Opening. Stock 5.5 TKkTK; Closing. Stock 2.5 TKkTK; Pur. 15 TKkTK; Carriage Inward 1 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 13,000 TK",
            "TK 14,000 TK",
            "TK 17,000 TK",
            "TK 19,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 5.5 TKk + 15k + 1k - 2.5k = 19,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1380,
        "text": "<p>Effect of not recording a Revenue Expense at year-end\u2014\n\ni. Gross Profit increases\n\nii. NP increases\n\niii. Net Assets increase</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Omitting an indirect expense (like rent) doesn't affect Gross Profit, but it inflates NP and Equity (Net Assets).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1381,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is shown on the Liability side of the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Unexpired Cost",
            "Accrued Income",
            "Prepaid Expense",
            "Unearned Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Unearned income (\u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099c\u09bf\u09a4 \u0986\u09df) is a liability because the service/product is yet to be delivered.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1382,
        "text": "<p>What is \"Allowance for Doubtful Accounts\"?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Probable Income",
            "Probable Liability",
            "Probable Asset",
            "Probable Loss"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>It is a provision against a probable loss (\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09ad\u09be\u09ac\u09cd\u09af \u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a4\u09bf\u09aa\u09c2\u09b0\u09a3/\u09b8\u099e\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09bf) from non-payment by debtors.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1383,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an Intangible Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Disc. on Share",
            "Deferred Ad",
            "on Share\n\nb) Deferred Ad\n\nc) Goodwill",
            "Preliminary Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Goodwill (\u09b8\u09c1\u09a8\u09be\u09ae) is an intangible asset. Others in the list are fictitious assets (\u0985\u09b2\u09c0\u0995 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a6).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1384,
        "text": "<p>Net Sales 6 TKLTK. Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Cost of Goods Sold. What is the Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 4,50,000 TK",
            "TK 4,80,000 TK",
            "TK 5,00,000 TK",
            "TK 5,10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>If Cost of Goods Sold is 100 TK\\%TK, Sales is 120 TK\\%TK. 6,00,000 TK / 1.2 = 5,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1385,
        "text": "<p>From Q133: If Gross Profit is 1 TKLTK and Opening. Expense is 60 TK\\%TK of Gross Profit, what is the Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 60,000 TK",
            "TK 48,000 TK",
            "TK 40,000 TK",
            "TK 36,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = 6 TKL - 5L = 1LTK. Opening. Expense = 1 TKL \\times 60\\% = 60kTK. NP = 1 TKL - 60k = 40,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1386,
        "text": "<p>Advanced Apprentice Premium is a/an\u2014\n\ni. Current Asset\n\nii. Current Liability\n\niii. Unearned Income</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Apprentice premium is an income; receiving it in advance is a liability/unearned income.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1387,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 50,000 TK. If 2 TK/5 TK is written off, what is the Deferred Ad expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 10,000 TK",
            "TK 20,000 TK",
            "TK 30,000 TK",
            "TK 50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Written off = 2 TK/5 TK. Remaining Deferred = 3 TK/5 TK. 50,000 TK \\times 3/5 = 30,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1388,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 10 TKkTK, Pur. 50 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 20 TKkTK, Carriage In 5 TKkTK, Wages 5 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 50,000 TK",
            "TK 60,000 TK",
            "TK 70,000 TK",
            "TK 72,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 10 TKk + 50k + 5k + 5k - 20k = 50,000 TK (Indirect expenses like rent/salary are excluded).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1389,
        "text": "<p>From Q137: Carriage Out 2 TKkTK, Salary 4 TKkTK (-500 TK adv), Rent 1 TKkTK (+1 TKkTK due). Total Indirect Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 7,500 TK",
            "TK 8,000 TK",
            "TK 13,000 TK",
            "TK 18,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Ind. Expense = 2 TKkTK (Carr. Out) + 3.5 TKkTK (Net Salary) + 2 TKkTK (Net Rent) = 7,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1390,
        "text": "<p>Ad 1.8 TKLTK, Free goods 20 TKkTK. Write-off over 4 TK years. Ad expense for 2021 TK in Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 20,000 TK",
            "TK 45,000 TK",
            "TK 50,000 TK",
            "TK 1,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total = 2,00,000 TK. Annual write-off (1 TK/4 TK) = 50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1391,
        "text": "<p>From Q139: What will be the Deferred Ad in Balance Sheet for the year 2022 TK?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "TK 50,000 TK",
            "TK 1,00,000 TK",
            "TK 1,50,000 TK",
            "TK 2,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>After 2021 TK & 2022 TK (2 TK years), 2 TK/4 TK is written off. Remaining 2 TK/4 = 1,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1392,
        "text": "<p>If 10 TK\\%TK depreciation for 6 TK months is TK 2,000 TK, what is the total value of the asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "12,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "32,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Annual Depreciation. = 2,000 TK \\times 2 = 4,000 TK. Since rate is 10 TK\\%TK, Asset Value = 4,000 TK / 0.10 = 40,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1393,
        "text": "<p>Non-operating expenses are\u2014\n\ni. Interest. on Bank Overdraft\n\nii. Apprentice Allowance\n\niii. Interest. on Notes Payable</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are financing costs or non-core business activities, hence non-operating expenses.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1394,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a purchase-related expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Insurance",
            "Travel Expense",
            "Purchase Discount",
            "Carriage Inward"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Carriage inward (\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09df \u09aa\u09b0\u09bf\u09ac\u09b9\u09a8) is directly added to the cost of purchasing goods.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1395,
        "text": "<p>Profit is 33 TK \\frac{1}{3}\\%TK on Sales. What is the profit rate on Cost?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "16 TK \\frac{2}{3}\\%TK",
            "20 TK\\%TK",
            "25 TK\\%TK",
            "50 TK\\%TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>33 TK \\frac{1}{3}\\%TK on Sales is 1 TK/3 TKrd. Thus, on Cost it is 1 TK/2 TK or 50 TK\\%TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1396,
        "text": "<p>Unearned Revenue TK 40,000 TK. If 3 TK/5 TK is earned, what is the Current Liability at year-end?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "16,000 TK",
            "24,000 TK",
            "32,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Remaining Liability = 2 TK/5 TK of 40,000 TK = 16,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1397,
        "text": "<p>What does \"Unearned Income\" represent?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset",
            "Liability",
            "Income",
            "Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Unearned income is a liability because the service/good is still owed to the customer.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1398,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Capital 1.7 TKLTK, Drawing 20 TKkTK, Cost of Goods Sold 1.6 TKLTK, Sales 2.7 TKLTK, Net Profit 50 TKkTK. Owner's Equity?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,50,000 TK",
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK",
            "2,40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Equity = Opening. Capital + NP - Drawing = 1,70,000 TK + 50,000 TK - 20,000 TK = 2,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1399,
        "text": "<p>From Q147: If Cost of Goods Sold was 10 TK\\%TK less, what would be the impact?\n\ni. NP increases\n\nii. Sales increase\n\niii. Equity increases</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Lower Cost of Goods Sold increases profit (i) and thus increases equity (iii). It has no effect on Sales (ii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1400,
        "text": "<p>What is the purpose of preparing the Statement of Owner's Equity?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Find Add. Capital",
            "Find Opening. Capital",
            "Find Closing Capital",
            "Capital\n\nb) Find Opening. Capital\n\nc) Find Closing Capital\n\nd) Find Retained Earnings"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>It tracks the change from opening capital to closing capital (\u09b8\u09ae\u09be\u09aa\u09a8\u09c0 \u09ae\u09c2\u09b2\u09a7\u09a8) for the period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1401,
        "text": "<p>Started business with: Cash 50 TKkTK, Credit Purchase 25 TKkTK, 10 TK\\%TK Loan 50 TKkTK. Opening Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "25,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "75,000 TK",
            "1,25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital = Assets (Cash 50 TKkTK) - Liability (Accounts Payable 25 TKkTK + Loan 50 TKkTK) = ... Wait, logic: Capital = Assets 50 TKkTK - Liability 25 TKkTK (Loan is usually cash). Result: 25,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1402,
        "text": "<p>From Q150: If Loan interest is not recorded, effect on Financial Statements?\n\ni. Expense \u2193 5 TKkTK\n\nii. Liability \u2193 5 TKkTK\n\niii. Equity \u2193 5 TKkTK</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Omitting interest means expenses are understated (i) and liabilities (interest payable) are understated (ii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1403,
        "text": "<p>Sales 2 TKLTK, Gross Profit 75 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 15 TKkTK, Net Purchase 1.3 TKLTK. Opening Stock?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 2 TKL - 75k = 1.25LTK. Opening. Stock = Cost of Goods Sold + Closing. Stock - Purchase = 1.25 TKL + 15k - 1.3L = 10,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1404,
        "text": "<p>From Q152: If Closing Stock value is increased by 5,000 TK then\u2014\n\ni. Opening. Stock increases\n\nii. Current Asset increases\n\niii. Equity increases</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Increased Closing. Stock increases Current Assets (ii) and decreases Cost of Goods Sold, which increases Profit/Equity (iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1405,
        "text": "<p>Closing. Stock Cost 1.5 TKLTK, Market 1.7 TKLTK. Includes 6 TKkTK fire loss (insured) and 4 TKkTK unused stationery. Closing. Stock in BS?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,40,000 TK",
            "1,44,000 TK",
            "1,46,000 TK",
            "1,60,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing. Stock = Cost (1.5 TKLTK) - Fire Loss (6 TKkTK) - Stationery (4 TKkTK) = 1,40,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1406,
        "text": "<p>From Q154: Fire loss 6 TKkTK, Insurance covers 50 TK\\%TK. Net fire loss in Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,000 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "3,000 TK",
            "2,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Fire Loss = Total Loss (6 TKkTK) - Insurance Claim (3 TKkTK) = 3,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1407,
        "text": "<p>Fixed Assets 60 TKkTK, Total Liability 50 TKkTK, Equity 90 TKkTK. Current Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "2,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Assets = Liability + Equity = 50 TKk + 90k = 1.4LTK. Current Assets = 1.4 TKL - 60k = 80,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1408,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is NOT shown in Financial Statements?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Capital Reserve",
            "Special Reserve",
            "General Reserve",
            "Secret Reserve"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Secret reserves (\u0997\u09cb\u09aa\u09a8 \u09b8\u099e\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09bf) are intentionally hidden and not disclosed in financial reports.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1409,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock + Net Purchase + Carriage Inward - Closing. Stock = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales",
            "Cost of Goods Sold",
            "Cost Price",
            "Production Cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the standard formula for Cost of Goods Sold (\u09ac\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09c0\u09a4 \u09aa\u09a3\u09cd\u09af\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09df).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1410,
        "text": "<p>Closing. Stock cost 40 TKkTK, Market value 50 TKkTK. Amount to be in Financial Statements?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "40,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>According to the Prudence/Conservatism principle, the lower of cost or market value is taken.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1411,
        "text": "<p>Based on Q159, which principle was followed in valuing closing stock?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost Principle",
            "Periodicity",
            "Entity Concept",
            "Conservatism"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism Principle (\u09b0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09a3\u09b6\u09c0\u09b2\u09a4\u09be\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c0\u09a4\u09bf) ensures assets are not overstated and liabilities not understated.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1412,
        "text": "<p>Net Profit of a business organization indicates\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset",
            "External Liability",
            "Internal Liability",
            "Production"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net profit belongs to the owner, increasing their equity. Thus, it is an Internal Liability (\u0985\u09ad\u09cd\u09af\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09c0\u09a3 \u09a6\u09be\u09df).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1413,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 10 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 15 TKkTK, Carriage In 1 TKkTK, Carriage Out 500 TK, Purchase 50 TKkTK, Sales 1 TKLTK, Rent 1.5 TKkTK. Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "54,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 10 TKk+50k+1k-15k = 46kTK. Gross Profit = 1,00,000 TK - 46,000 TK = 54,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1414,
        "text": "<p>From Q162: What is the total Indirect Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "2,000 TK",
            "2,500 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Indirect Expense = Carriage Out (500 TK) + Rent (1.5 TKkTK) = 2,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1415,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold 6 TKLTK, Opening. Expense 55 TKkTK, Interest. on Capital 20 TKkTK, Profit rate 20 TK\\%TK on Sales. Sales price?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,50,000 TK",
            "7,00,000 TK",
            "7,20,000 TK",
            "7,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>If Gross Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales, it's 25 TK\\%TK on Cost. Sales = 6,00,000 TK \\times 1.25 = 7,50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1416,
        "text": "<p>From Q164: What is the Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "75,000 TK",
            "1,05,000 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "5,25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = 7.5 TKL - 6L = 1.5LTK. NP = 1.5 TKL - 55kTK (Opening Expense) - 20 TKkTK (Non-Opening Expense) = 75,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1417,
        "text": "<p>Closing Capital 30 TKkTK, which is 20 TK\\%TK less than Opening. Capital. If Interest on Capital is 5 TK\\%TK, what is the interest amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "1,800 TK",
            "1,500 TK",
            "1,875 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening. Capital = 30 TKk / 0.80 = 37,500 TK. Interest = 37,500 TK \\times 5\\% = 1,875 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1418,
        "text": "<p>Why does the Balance Sheet match (Asset=Liability+E)?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Double Entry System",
            "Trial Balance Match",
            "Accounting Cycle",
            "All Transactions Recorded"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The fundamental principle of double-entry bookkeeping ensures that total assets always equal total liabilities and equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1419,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance: Insurance 2,400 TK paid annually on March 31. Insurance expense in Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,600 TK",
            "1,800 TK",
            "2,400 TK",
            "3,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Paid for Apr-Mar (12 TK months). Year ends Dec. Months used = 9 TK. Expense = 2,400 TK \\times 9/12 = 1,800 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1420,
        "text": "<p>Financial Statements provide info on\u2014\n\ni) Financial Results\n\nii) Financial Position\n\niii) Cash Flows</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These are the core outputs of a complete set of financial reports.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1421,
        "text": "<p>Capital 5 TKLTK, 12 TK\\%TK Loan 1 TKLTK, Accrued Interest 12 TKkTK, Accounts Payable 40 TKkTK, Unearned Rent 4 TKkTK. Current Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "52,000 TK",
            "56,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,56,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Liability = Accrued Interest (12 TKkTK) + Accounts Payable (40 TKkTK) + Unearned Rent (4 TKkTK) = 56,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1422,
        "text": "<p>From Q170: What is the Total Asset of the firm?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,00,000 TK",
            "6,00,000 TK",
            "6,56,000 TK",
            "8,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Assets = Capital (5 TKLTK) + Loan (1 TKLTK) + Current Liability (56 TKkTK) = 6,56,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1423,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Current Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Acc. Depreciation.",
            "Cash Account",
            "Depreciation.\n\nb) Cash Account\n\nc) 10 TK\\%TK Investment",
            "Machinery"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash (\u09a8\u0997\u09a6\u09be\u09a8) is the most liquid current asset.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1424,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is shown in the Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Prepaid Expense",
            "Expense Paid",
            "Accrued Expense",
            "Accrued Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Actual expenses incurred during the period (Paid +/- Adjustments) are shown in the Income Statement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1425,
        "text": "<p>Total Loan 70 TKkTK. 20 TKkTK to be paid next year. Long-term Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Long-term Liability = Total Loan - Current portion = 70 TKk - 20k = 50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1426,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 20,000 TK. If 3 TK/5 TK is written off, what is the Deferred Ad expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4,000 TK",
            "8,000 TK",
            "12,000 TK",
            "16,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Written off = 3 TK/5 TK. Deferred = 2 TK/5 TK of 20,000 TK = 8,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1427,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Purchase",
            "Sales",
            "Opening. Expense",
            "Opening. Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the basic income statement formula for a trading concern.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1428,
        "text": "<p>Paid 2 TK/3 TK of Factory Expense = TK 4,000 TK. Amount of Accrued Factory Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "12,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>2 TK/3 = 4kTK, so 1 TK/3 = 2kTK. Total = 6 TKkTK. Accrued (remaining 1 TK/3 TK) = 2,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1429,
        "text": "<p>Profitless Sales is deducted from\u2014\n\ni) Purchase\n\nii) Closing. Stock\n\niii) Sales</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Profitless sales (\u09ae\u09c1\u09a8\u09be\u09ab\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09b9\u09c0\u09a8 \u09ac\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09df) must be deducted from both Net Sales and Net Purchase.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1430,
        "text": "<p>Which is NOT a non-operating income?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest. on Drawing",
            "Commission Receivable.",
            "Interest. on Invest.",
            "Sales Revenue"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales revenue is the primary Operating Income of a business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1431,
        "text": "<p>Result will be Net Income when\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset > Liability",
            "Asset > Income",
            "Expense > Income",
            "Income > Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Income occurs when total revenues exceed total expenses for the period.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1432,
        "text": "<p>If installation cost is debited to the wages account, what will be the effect on the Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Gross Profit will decrease",
            "NP will increase",
            "Asset value increase",
            "Total asset increase"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Installation cost is a capital Expense. If debited to Wages (Direct Expense), Cost of Goods Sold increases, causing Gross Profit (Gross Profit) to decrease.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1433,
        "text": "<p>What is the effect of charging a 5 TK\\%TK Bad Debt Provision on Accounts Receivable?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Assets & Equity \u2193",
            "Assets & Equity \u2191",
            "Assets \u2193, Equity \u2191",
            "Liability \u2193, Equity \u2191"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Provision is an expense (Equity \u2193) and it's deducted from Accounts Receivable (Assets \u2193).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1434,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 40 TKkTK, Free goods 5 TKkTK. Write off 1 TK/3 TK of total. Deferred Advertisement amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "15,000 TK",
            "13,333 TK",
            "11,667 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Ad = 45 TKkTK. Written off = 15 TKkTK (1 TK/3 TK). Deferred = 30,000 TK (2 TK/3 TK).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1435,
        "text": "<p>Result of free goods distribution\u2014\n\ni) Gross Profit decreases\n\nii) Gross Profit increases\n\niii) NP decreases</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It reduces purchase (Gross Profit \u2193) and increases ad expense (NP \u2193).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1436,
        "text": "<p>Profit is 25 TK\\%TK on Sales. Cost of Goods Sold is TK 6,00,000 TK. Sales amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,50,000 TK",
            "7,00,000 TK",
            "7,50,000 TK",
            "8,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>If Profit is 25 TK\\%TK on Sales, Cost of Goods Sold is 75 TK\\%TK. Sales = 6,00,000 TK / 0.75 = 8,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1437,
        "text": "<p>From Q185: What is the amount of Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "1,87,500 TK",
            "1,75,000 TK",
            "1,62,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = Sales - Cost of Goods Sold = 8,00,000 TK - 6,00,000 TK = 2,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1438,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following does NOT affect the total sum of the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Drawing 8 TKkTK",
            "Paid due Expense 3 TKkTK",
            "Collection from Accounts Receivable 4 TKkTK",
            "Credit purchase 5 TKkTK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Collection from Accounts Receivable increases Cash and decreases Accounts Receivable by the same amount; total assets remain unchanged.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1439,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Current Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Gen. Reserve",
            "Prepaid Expense",
            "Unearned Income",
            "Mortgage Loan"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Unearned income (\u0985\u0997\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09ae \u0986\u09df) is a liability until the service is provided.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1440,
        "text": "<p>Salary paid 30 TKkTK, Accrued salary 20 TKkTK. Total Revenue Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>According to the matching principle: Paid (30 TKkTK) + Accrued (20 TKkTK) = 50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1441,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 50 TKkTK, Purchase 1.5 TKLTK, Sales 2 TKLTK, Closing. Stock 80 TKkTK. Adjusted Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "80,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Adj. Purchase = Opening. Stock + Purchase - Closing. Stock = 50 TKk + 1.5L - 80k = 1,20,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1442,
        "text": "<p>From Q190: If Net Profit is 50 TKkTK, what is the Operating Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = Sales - Adj Pur = 2 TKL - 1.2L = 80kTK. Opening Expense = Gross Profit - NP = 80 TKk - 50k = 30,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1443,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Non-operating Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales",
            "Interest. on Mortgage",
            "Purchase Dis",
            "Apprentice Premium"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Apprentice Premium (\u09b6\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09a8\u09ac\u09bf\u09b6 \u09b8\u09c7\u09b2\u09be\u09ae\u09bf) is a non-core revenue item for most businesses.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1444,
        "text": "<p>Capital 5 TKLTK, Loan 1 TKLTK, Accrued Interest 10 TKkTK, Accounts Payable 50 TKkTK, Unearned Rent 20 TKkTK. Current Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Liability = Accrued Interest (10 TKkTK) + Accounts Payable (50 TKkTK) + Unearned Rent (20 TKkTK) = 80,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1445,
        "text": "<p>From Q193: What is the Total Current Asset of the firm?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,00,000 TK",
            "3,80,000 TK",
            "4,00,000 TK",
            "5,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Assets = Liability + Equity = (1 TKL + 80kTK) + 5 TKL = 6.8LTK. Current Assets = 6.8 TKL - 3LTK (Fixed) = 3,80,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1446,
        "text": "<p>Salary paid for 10 TK months TK 1,20,000 TK. Amount of Accrued Salary?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "12,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "24,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Per month = 1.2 TKL/10 = 12kTK. Due (2 TK months) = 24,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1447,
        "text": "<p>Assets that can be converted to cash very quickly are called\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Liquid Assets",
            "Fictitious Assets",
            "Tangible Assets",
            "Intangible Assets"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Liquid assets (\u09a4\u09b0\u09b2 \u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a6) like cash or marketable securities are characterized by quick convertibility.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1448,
        "text": "<p>Sales 2 TKLTK, Closing. Stock 30 TKkTK, Cost of Goods Sold 1.4 TKLTK, Opening. Expense is 50 TK\\%TK of Cost of Goods Sold. Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = Sales - Cost of Goods Sold = 2,00,000 TK - 1,40,000 TK = 60,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1449,
        "text": "<p>From Q197: Result of Income Statement (NP is Loss of 10 TKkTK)?\n\ni) Capital \u2193 10 TKkTK\n\nii) Drawing \u2191 10 TKkTK\n\niii) Internal Liability \u2193 10 TKkTK</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>NP = 60 TKkTK (Gross Profit) - 70 TKkTK (Opening Expense) = TK(10k)TK loss. Loss reduces Capital (i) and thus Internal Liability (iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1450,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 40 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 60 TKkTK, Cost of Goods Sold 2,00,000 TK. Amount of Purchase?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,80,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK",
            "2,40,000 TK",
            "2,60,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Purchase = Cost of Goods Sold + Closing. Stock - Opening. Stock = 2,00,000 TK + 60,000 TK - 40,000 TK = 2,20,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1451,
        "text": "<p>Unearned Service Revenue is a/an\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Asset",
            "Liability",
            "Income",
            "Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It represents an obligation to perform service in the future, making it a liability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1452,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Non-operating Income?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sales",
            "Discount Receivable.",
            "Commission Receivable.",
            "Interest. on Investment"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest on investment is a financial income not related to core business operations.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1453,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold + Gross Profit = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Purchase",
            "Sales",
            "Opening. Expense",
            "Opening. Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the fundamental equation for the trading part of the Income Statement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1454,
        "text": "<p>In which section of the Balance Sheet is 'Creditors' (Account Payable) shown?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Current Asset",
            "Current Liability",
            "Fixed Asset",
            "Long-term Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Creditors are short-term obligations usually payable within a year.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1455,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an Indirect Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Audit Fee",
            "Dock Charge",
            "Import Duty",
            "Carriage Inward"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Audit fees are administrative expenses, while others are direct costs of purchasing/production.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1456,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 10 TKkTK, Purchase 1 TKLTK, Pur. Return 7.5 TKkTK, Pur. Discount 2.5 TKkTK, Wages 3 TKkTK, Excise Duty 12 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 25 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "75,000 TK",
            "87,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK",
            "1,25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Pur = 90 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold = 10 TKkTK (Opening) + 90 TKkTK (Net Pur) + 3 TKkTK (Wages) + 12 TKkTK (Duty) - 25 TKkTK (Closing) = 90,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1457,
        "text": "<p>From Q205: Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales. What is the Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "18,750 TK",
            "18,000 TK",
            "22,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>20 TK\\%TK on Sales = 25 TK\\%TK on Cost. Gross Profit = 90,000 TK \\times 25\\% = 22,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1458,
        "text": "<p>To determine Net Purchase, which items are deducted from Purchase?\n\ni. Discount\n\nii. Carriage Inward\n\niii. Purchase Return</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Purchase returns and discounts are deducted. Carriage inward is an additional cost, not a deduction.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1459,
        "text": "<p>Prepaid Salary in Trial Balance is 15 TKkTK. At year-end, 5 TKkTK is still prepaid. Salary expense in Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,000 TK",
            "10,000 TK",
            "15,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Expense = Total (15 TKkTK) - Remaining Prepaid (5 TKkTK) = 10,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1460,
        "text": "<p>Gross Profit 50 TKkTK, Admin Expense 15 TKkTK, Selling Expense 5 TKkTK, Interest Income 2 TKkTK. Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "32,000 TK",
            "35,000 TK",
            "37,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>NP = 50 TKkTK (Gross Profit) - 20 TKkTK (Opening Expense) + 2 TKkTK (Non-Opening Income) = 32,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1461,
        "text": "<p>From Q209: Impact of charging 2 TKkTK Bad Debt Provision?\n\ni. NP will be 30 TKkTK\n\nii. Current Assets \u2193 2 TKkTK\n\niii. Total Assets \u2193 2 TKkTK</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>NP becomes 32 TKk - 2k = 30kTK. Accounts Receivable (Asset) decreases, so total asset also decreases.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1462,
        "text": "<p>Insurance 30 TKkTK paid on 01-07-2020 for 4 years. Insurance expense for 2020?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,750 TK",
            "7,500 TK",
            "10,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Annual = 30 TKk/4 = 7,500 TK. For 6 months (July-Dec) = 3,750 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1463,
        "text": "<p>From Q211: If the full 30 TKkTK is shown as expense, impact?\n\ni. NP \u2193 22,500 TK\n\nii. Total Assets \u2193 26,250 TK\n\niii. Equity \u2193 26,250 TK</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Extra Expense = 30 TKk - 3.75k = 26,250 TK. This reduces both NP (Equity) and the Prepaid Asset by 26,250 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1464,
        "text": "<p>Objective of preparing Balance Sheet\u2014\n\ni. Know Income/Expense\n\nii. Know Assets\n\niii. Know Liabilities</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Balance sheet shows financial position (Assets & Liability). Income/Expense is the domain of the Income Statement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1465,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 1 TKLTK, Purchase 1.5 TKLTK, Wages 2 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 97 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,58,000 TK",
            "1,55,000 TK",
            "1,53,000 TK",
            "1,45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 1,00,000 TK + 1,50,000 TK + 2,000 TK - 97,000 TK = 1,55,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1466,
        "text": "<p>From Q214: If 2 TKkTK salary was accrued\u2014\n\ni. Gross Profit will decrease\n\nii. NP will decrease\n\niii. Total salary will be 5 TKkTK</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Salary is an indirect expense, so it affects NP, not Gross Profit. Total salary = 3 TKkTK (paid) + 2 TKkTK (due) = 5 TKkTK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1467,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Fictitious/Imaginary Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2021",
