        "options": [
            "Sales \u2191",
            "NP \u2191",
            "Opening. Expense \u2191",
            "Gross Profit \u2191"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Increase in expenses reduces net profit, which in turn reduces owner's equity/capital.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1489,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Provision 3.5 TKkTK. Accounts Receivable 1.75 TKLTK, New Bad Debt 15 TKkTK. Charge 12 TK\\%TK New Provision. Total Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "20,580 TK",
            "30,700 TK",
            "39,420 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>New Prov = TK(1.75L - 15k) \\times 12\\% = 19.2kTK. Expense = 15 TKk + 19.2k - 3.5k = 30,700 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1490,
        "text": "<p>From Q238: Impact of Bad Debt adjustment?\n\ni. NP \u2193\n\nii. Accounts Receivable \u2193\n\niii. Equity \u2193</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2021",
