        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Unsettled claims are \"Contingent Liabilities\" and are only shown in footnotes, not the main table.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1529,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Capital 1.5 TKLTK, Drawing 10 TKkTK, Cost of Goods Sold 1.5 TKLTK, Sales 2.5 TKLTK, NP 60 TKkTK. Owner's Equity?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,50,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK",
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "2,10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>OE = Opening. Capital + NP - Drawing = 1.5 TKL + 60k - 10k = 2,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1530,
        "text": "<p>From Q278: If Cost of Goods Sold was 10% less, what would be the impact?\n\ni. NP \u2191\n\nii. NP \u2193\n\niii. OE \u2191</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Lower Cost of Goods Sold increases Net Profit, which directly increases Owner's Equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1531,
        "text": "<p>Machine 60 TKkTK, Carriage 5 TKkTK, Installation 3 TKkTK. Depreciation 10%. Sold for 72 TKkTK. Revenue Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,000 TK",
            "6,500 TK",
            "6,800 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Cost = 68 TKkTK. Depreciation (10%) = 6,800 TK (Depreciation is a revenue expense).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1532,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Dalton purchased a machine for 60,000 TK. Transport and installation costs were 5,000 TK and 3,000 TK respectively. At the end of the year, 10% depreciation was charged. Due to a defect, the machine was sold for 72,000 TK. \n\nQ: What is the amount of Revenue Expenditure?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6,000 TK",
            "6,500 TK",
            "6,800 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>GAAP (Generally Accepted Accounting Principles) ensures consistency and comparability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1533,
        "text": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold 1,00,000 TK. Profit is 20 TK\\%TK on Sales. What is the Sales amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,16,667 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "1,25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>20 TK\\%TK on Sales = 25 TK\\%TK on Cost. Sales = 1,00,000 TK \\times 1.25 = 1,25,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1534,
        "text": "<p>Ad Expense 40 TKkTK, Free goods 10 TKkTK. To be written off over 4 years. Current year's expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK",
            "12,500 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Ad = 50,000 TK. Expense = 50,000 TK / 4 = 12,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1535,
        "text": "<p>From Q283: Amount of Deferred Advertisement at the end of the current year?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "12,500 TK",
            "25,000 TK",
            "37,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Deferred = Total (50 TKkTK) - Expense (12.5 TKkTK) = 37,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1536,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance Stationery 7 TKkTK, Opening. Stock incl. 1 TKkTK, Closing. Stock 2 TKkTK. Stationery expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "8,000 TK",
            "7,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "5,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Expense = 7,000 TK (Trial Balance) - 1,000 TK (Already in Opening. Stock) - 1,000 TK (Used from Closing. Stock) \u2192 actual used = 1 TKk + 7k - 2k = 6,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1537,
        "text": "<p>From Q285: Unused stationery in the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,000 TK",
            "2,000 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "5,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Unused/Closing stationery is an asset. Here it is 2,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1538,
        "text": "<p>Salary in Trial Balance is 14,000 TK. Monthly salary is 1,500 TK. How much is Salaries Payable in the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Commerce Board - 2018",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "1,500 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "14,000 TK",
            "18,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Annual Salary should be (1,500 TK \\times 12 TK) = 18,000 TK. Paid is 14,000 TK. Payable = 18,000 TK - 14,000 TK = 4,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1539,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a purchase-related expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Commerce Board - 2018",
        "type": "college",
