        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Commission = 45,250 TK \\times 5\\% = 2,262.5 TK \\approx 2,263 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1544,
        "text": "<p>If unrecorded bad debts in 2015 are TK 4,000 TK (from a base of 60,000 TK debtors) and the policy is to maintain a 5% Bad Debt Provision and a 2% Discount Provision, what is the Provision for Discount?</p>",
        "meta": "All Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,200 TK",
            "1,160 TK",
            "1,080 TK",
            "1,064 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Provision for discount is calculated on \"Good Debtors\" (Net Debtors after deducting both new bad debts and the new bad debt provision).\n\nTK(56,000 TK - 2,800 TK) \\times 2\\% = 1,064 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1545,
