        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Buying a machine (Asset) on credit (Liability) on the last day means no depreciation is charged yet, so it only affects the Balance Sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1611,
        "text": "<p>Understating (writing less) Closing Stock results in:\n\ni. Decrease in Current Assets\n\nii. Decrease in Fixed Assets\n\niii. Decrease in Owner's Equity</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Low closing stock reduces assets (i) and increases Cost of Goods Sold, which lowers profit and consequently lowers Equity (iii).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1612,
        "text": "<p>Ad expense was TK 50,000 TK. Free product distribution TK 20,000 TK is unrecorded. If 3/4 of total ad expense is deferred, what is the amount of Deferred Advertisement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
