        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>If received VAT > paid VAT, the difference is a liability payable to the government.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1617,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Masum's Assets 4,00,000 TK; Capital 3,00,000 TK; Cash Drawings 30,000 TK; Product Drawings 20,000 TK. What is the Internal Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "2,50,000 TK",
            "3,00,000 TK",
            "3,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Internal Liability (Closing Capital) = 3,00,000 TK - (30,000 TK + 20,000 TK) = 2,50,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1618,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Masum is a businessman. His total assets are TK 4,00,000 TK and capital is TK 3,00,000 TK. Drawings consist of Cash TK 30,000 TK and Goods TK 20,000 TK. If the cash drawings were TK 50,000 TK instead, what would be the impact on External Liabilities?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increase by 20,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 20,000 TK",
            "Increase by 50,000 TK",
            "No impact / (d as provided: Decrease by 50,000 TK)"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Drawings affect the Accounting Equation by decreasing Assets (Cash/Goods) and decreasing Owner's Equity (Internal Liability). They have no impact on External Liabilities (debts to third parties).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1619,
        "text": "<p>Impact of including Furniture Purchase in Operating Expenses:\n\ni. Owner's Equity decreases\n\nii. Assets decrease\n\niii. External Liabilities decrease</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Overstating expenses lowers profit/equity, and failing to record the asset lowers the asset total.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1620,
        "text": "<p>Future Provisions are created for:\n\ni. Asset replacement\n\nii. Liability payment\n\niii. Increasing working capital</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i",
            "ii",
            "iii",
            "ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Provisions are specific set-asides for known future obligations or liabilities.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1621,
        "text": "<p>If Accrued Interest is not adjusted:\n\ni. Liability decreases\n\nii. Owner's Equity decreases\n\niii. Assets decrease</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Accrued Interest (Income) not recorded means Assets and Equity (Profit) are both understated.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1622,
        "text": "<p>Closing stock valued at 1,00,000 TK. 25,000 TK worth of goods destroyed by fire. Insurance agreed to Payable 20,000 TK. Abnormal Loss?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK",
            "75,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Abnormal Loss = Total Loss (25,000 TK) - Insurance Claim (20,000 TK) = 5,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1623,
        "text": "<p>(Referring to the stem above) What amount will be debited in the Closing Stock adjustment entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "75,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,25,000 TK",
            "1,45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Closing Stock = 1,00,000 TK - 25,000 TK = 75,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1624,
        "text": "<p>Where is a Contingent Liability placed on the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit side",
            "Credit side",
            "Both sides",
            "None of the above"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Contingent Liabilities are not included in the main table; they are shown as a \"Footnote\" below the Balance Sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1625,
        "text": "<p>Opening Receivables 70,000 TK; Credit Sales 80,000 TK; Old Provision 3,000 TK; Bad Debt 5,000 TK. New Provision 10%. Net Receivables?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "67,500 TK",
            "1,27,500 TK",
            "1,30,500 TK",
            "1,33,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Debtors = 70,000 TK+80,000 TK-5,000 TK = 1,45,000 TK. New Prov = 14,500 TK. Net = 1,45,000 TK - 14,500 TK = 1,30,500 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1626,
        "text": "<p>Provision for Bad Debt is a result of which accounting principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost Concept",
            "Conservatism",
            "Realization",
            "Full Disclosure"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Conservatism (Prudence) dictates that we should provide for all possible losses but not anticipate profits.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1627,
        "text": "<p>Which increase will lead to an increase in business capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Expense",
            "Drawing",
            "Income",
            "Interest. on Capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Income/Profit directly increases the owner's capital.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1628,
        "text": "<p>Non-operating incomes are\u2014\n\ni. Interest. on Invest\n\nii. Sales\n\niii. Apprentice Prem</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales is an operating income. Interest on investment and apprentice premium are non-operating.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1629,
        "text": "<p>Considered in Cost of Goods Sold calculation\u2014\n\ni. Opening Stock, Pur, Wages\n\nii. Closing Stock, Ship Rent, Duty\n\niii. Sales Disc, Return, Carriage Out</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales-related items (iii) are not part of Cost of Goods Sold; they are operating expenses or deductions from sales.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1630,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Stock 10 TKkTK, Pur 1.05 TKLTK, Closing. Stock 15 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "90,000 TK",
            "95,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,15,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 10,000 TK + 1,05,000 TK - 15,000 TK = 1,00,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1631,
        "text": "<p>From Q345: If Closing. Stock market value is 10 TKkTK, impact on Gross Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5 TKkTK \u2191",
            "5 TKkTK \u2193",
            "10 TKkTK \u2193",
            "10 TKkTK \u2191"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Value reduced from 15 TKkTK to 10 TKkTK. 5 TKkTK reduction in stock reduces Gross Profit by 5,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1632,
        "text": "<p>Operating Profit is calculated by\u2014</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Gross Profit - Opening Expense - NonOp Expense",
            "Gross Profit + Opening Income - Opening Expense",
            "Gross Profit - Net Expense",
            "Opening Income - Opening Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Operating Profit = Gross Profit + Other Operating Income - Operating Expenses.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1633,
        "text": "<p>Commission 4% on Profit. Profit after commission 4,000 TK. Commission?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "150.50 TK",
            "153.85 TK",
            "160 TK",
            "166.67 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>4,000 TK \\times 4\\% = 160 TK. (Since 4,000 TK is already the 'after' amount, simple percentage applies).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1634,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance Ad 80 TKkTK. Unrecorded free goods 10 TKkTK. Total Ad expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "80,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Ad = 80,000 TK (Trial Balance) + 10,000 TK (Free goods) = 90,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1635,
        "text": "<p>From Q349: If total Ad is 90 TKkTK to be written off over 3 yrs, 2013 expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "26,667 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "53,333 TK",
            "60,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Expense = 90,000 TK / 3 = 30,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1636,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock 35 TKkTK, Pur 85 TKkTK, Sales 1.5 TKLTK. Gross Profit Rate 30%. Closing. Stock value?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "45,000 TK",
            "1,05,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 1.5 TKL \\times 70\\% = 1.05LTK. Closing. Stock = (35 TKk + 85kTK) - 1.05 TKL = 15,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1637,
        "text": "<p>Prov to be reduced by 2 TKkTK. Trial Balance Prov 6 TKkTK. New Prov?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>New Prov = 6,000 TK - 2,000 TK = 4,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1638,
        "text": "<p>Opening Capital 2 TKLTK, Closing Capital 3 TKLTK, Drawing 20 TKkTK, Addl Capital 50 TKkTK. Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "70,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>NP = (3 TKL + 20kTK) - (2 TKL + 50kTK) = 3.2 TKL - 2.5L = 70,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1639,
        "text": "<p>From Q353: If an additional 20 TKkTK was drawn, impact on Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "40 TKkTK \u2191",
            "20 TKkTK \u2191",
            "20 TKkTK \u2193",
            "40 TKkTK \u2193"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>In single entry, Drawings \u2191 leads to Net Profit \u2191 because TKProfit = (Ending + Drawing) - (Opening + Addl)TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1640,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock 10 TKkTK, Pur 50 TKkTK, Closing Stock 20 TKkTK, Pur Carriage 5 TKkTK, Wages 5 TKkTK. Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "72,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Cost of Goods Sold = 10 TKk + 50k + 5k + 5k - 20k = 50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1641,
        "text": "<p>From Q355: Sales Carr 2 TKkTK, Salary 4 TKkTK (-500 TK), Rent 1 TKkTK (+1 TKkTK). Indirect Expense?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "7,500 TK",
            "8,000 TK",
            "13,000 TK",
            "18,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Ind. Expense = 2 TKk + 3.5k + 2k = 7,500 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1642,
        "text": "<p>Opening Stock + Net Pur + Direct Expense - Closing Stock = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cost of Goods Sold",
            "Unsold Stock",
            "Pro",
            "Cost\n\nd) Gross Profit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the standard formula for Cost of Goods Sold.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1643,
        "text": "<p>Which is an element of the Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Drawing",
            "Accrued Wages",
            "Dock Charge",
            "Prepaid Ins"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Dock charge is an expense (Direct). Others are balance sheet/OE items.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1644,
        "text": "<p>Net Sales \u2013 Gross Profit = ?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Total Pur",
            "Opening Profit",
            "Net Profit",
            "Cost of Goods Sold"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Fundamental formula: Sales - Cost of Goods Sold = Gross Profit; therefore, Sales - Gross Profit = Cost of Goods Sold.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1645,
        "text": "<p>Gross Profit 50 TKkTK, Admin Expense 15 TKkTK, Selling Expense 5 TKkTK, Interest Income 2 TKkTK. Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur  Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "32,000 TK",
            "35,000 TK",
            "37,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>NP = 50 TKk - (15k + 5k) + 2k = 32,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1646,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Rakin's Gross Profit is TK 50,000 TK, Admin expenses TK 15,000 TK, and Selling expenses TK 5,000 TK. Interest income is TK 2,000 TK. If he wants to increase Net Profit while keeping Gross Profit constant:\n\ni. Admin expenses must be decreased\n\nii. Selling expenses must be reduced\n\niii. Sales must be increased</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>To increase Net Profit without changing Gross Profit, operating expenses must be reduced. Increasing sales would change the Gross Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1647,
        "text": "<p>What decreases due to Net Loss?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Assets",
            "Liability",
            "Equity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Net loss is deducted from capital, reducing Equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1648,
        "text": "<p>Particulars | TK\nNon-Current Assets | 2,00,000 TK\nAccounts Receivable | 50,000 TK\nAccounts Payable | 80,000 TK\nBank Overdraft | 5,000 TK\nCash in Hand | 10,000 TK\nOwner's Equity | ?\nQ. Calculate the Owner's Equity.</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">TK</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Non-Current Assets</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">2,00,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Accounts Receivable</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">50,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Accounts Payable</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">80,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Bank Overdraft</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">5,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Cash in Hand</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">10,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Owner&#x27;s Equity</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">?</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,75,000 TK",
            "2,35,000 TK",
            "2,60,000 TK",
            "3,45,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Owner's Equity = 2,60,000 TK - 85,000 TK = \\mathbf{1,75,000 TK \\text{ TK}}TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1649,
        "text": "<p>Started with TK 80,000 TK cash. Drawings TK 20,000 TK. Net Income TK 32,000 TK. Total Assets at year-end?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "60,000 TK",
            "92,000 TK",
            "1,12,000 TK",
            "1,32,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Assets = Capital (80,000 TK + 32,000 TK - 20,000 TK) = 92,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1650,
        "text": "<p>Owner's Equity is affected by:\n\ni. Personal drawings\n\nii. Business income\n\niii. Unpaid expenses</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Drawings, income, and accrued expenses (via net profit) all affect equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1651,
        "text": "<p>Interest on Drawings is:</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Owner's Expense, Biz Income",
            "Owner's Expense, Biz Expense",
            "Biz Income, Owner's Income",
            "Owner's Income, Biz Expense"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>It is an expense for the owner but an income for the business.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1652,
        "text": "<p>What strengthens the financial position of a business?\n\ni. Reserves\n\nii. Provisions\n\niii. Secret Reserves</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i",
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All types of reserves and provisions act as a financial cushion for future needs or risks.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1653,
        "text": "<p>Assets that can be very easily converted into cash are called?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fictitious Asset",
            "Liquid Asset",
            "Intangible Asset",
            "Fixed Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Liquid assets (like cash or bank balance) can be used or converted almost immediately.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1654,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following increases External Liabilities?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Credit Purchase",
            "Depreciation",
            "Income Tax payment",
            "Payment of Bills Payable"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Buying on credit creates a debt to a supplier, which is an external liability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1655,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an Internal Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Capital",
            "Creditors",
            "Outstanding Salary",
            "Bank Loan"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital represents the business's debt to its owner, making it an internal liability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1656,
        "text": "<p>The Statement of Financial Position is prepared using ledger balances to show:\n\ni. Net Profit\n\nii. Financial Position\n\niii. Gross Profit</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i",
            "ii",
            "iii",
            "ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The Balance Sheet's sole purpose is to reflect the financial position (Assets, Liabilities, Equity).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1657,
        "text": "<p>What is Income received in advance?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Current Asset",
            "Current Liability",
            "Long-term Liability",
            "Contingent Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It is an obligation to provide goods or services in the future, thus a Current Liability.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1658,
        "text": "<p>Which one is a Current Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bills Receivable",
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Capital",
            "Cash in Hand"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Bank overdraft is a short-term obligation to the bank that must be repaid within a year.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1659,
        "text": "<p>Read the following stimulus and answer the question:\nThe following information was taken from the account books of Nasir Traders for the financial year ended December 31, 2014:\nOpening Inventory | 20,000 TK\nPurchases | 28,000 TK\nSales | 18,000 TK\nTransportation Cost | 7,000 TK\nClosing Inventory | 7,000 TK\nLater it was found that 5,000 TK misappropriated by the cashier had not been recorded.\nQ. What is the amount of Adjusted Purchases?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Opening Inventory</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Purchases</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">28,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Sales</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">18,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Transportation Cost</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">7,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Closing Inventory</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">7,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK",
            "41,000 TK",
            "48,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Stock (\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09b0\u09ae\u09cd\u09ad\u09bf\u0995 \u09ae\u099c\u09c1\u09a6): 20,000 TK(+) Purchase (\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09af\u09bc): 28,000 TK(-) Closing Stock (\u09b8\u09ae\u09be\u09aa\u09a8\u09c0 \u09ae\u099c\u09c1\u09a6): (7,000 TK)TK\\text{Adjusted Purchase} = 20,000 TK + 28,000 TK - 7,000 TK = \\mathbf{41,000 TK \\text{ TK}}TKNote: Transportation Cost (\u09aa\u09b0\u09bf\u09ac\u09b9\u09a8 \u09ac\u09cd\u09af\u09af\u09bc) is a direct expense used to calculate the Cost of Goods Sold, but it is typically excluded from the specific \"Adjusted Purchase\" formula unless specified as \"Adjusted Net Purchase.\"</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1660,
        "text": "<p>\"Read the following stimulus and answer the question:\nThe following information was taken from the account books of Nasir Traders for the financial year ended December 31, 2014:\nOpening Inventory | 20,000 TK\nPurchases | 28,000 TK\nSales | 18,000 TK\nTransportation Cost | 7,000 TK\nClosing Inventory | 7,000 TK\nLater it was found that 5,000 TK misappropriated by the cashier had not been recorded.\nQ. What will be the amount of Cost of Goods Sold for Nasir Traders?\"</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Opening Inventory</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Purchases</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">28,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Sales</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">18,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Transportation Cost</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">7,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Closing Inventory</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">7,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Assets & Equity shown higher",
            "Equity decreases by 5,000 TK",
            "Liability increases",
            "Assets & Equity decrease"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>When cash is stolen but not recorded in the accounts, the following happens:\n\nAssets (\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09aa\u09a4\u09cd\u09a4\u09bf): The \"Cash\" shown in the books will be 5,000 TK higher than the actual cash available. Therefore, assets are overstated (\u09ac\u09c7\u09b6\u09bf \u09a6\u09c7\u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09cb \u09b9\u09ac\u09c7).\n\nNet Profit & Owner's Equity (\u09ae\u09be\u09b2\u09bf\u0995\u09be\u09a8\u09be\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09a4\u09cd\u09ac): Since the theft is an expense/loss that wasn't subtracted, the Net Profit stays incorrectly high. This inflated profit is added to the Capital, making the Owner's Equity overstated (\u09ac\u09c7\u09b6\u09bf \u09a6\u09c7\u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09cb \u09b9\u09ac\u09c7).\n\nSummary of Impact:\nBook Values: Higher than reality.\n\nActual Values: Lower than the books.\n\nSo, the displayed Assets and Owner's Equity will appear higher than the actual (real) Assets and Owner's Equity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1661,
        "text": "<p>Service Income 1,50,000 TK; Unearned Service Income 20,000 TK. TK 10,000 TK Service Income is unrecorded. Total Service Income in Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,30,000 TK",
            "1,40,000 TK",
            "1,60,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Income = 1,50,000 TK (trial balance) + 10,000 TK (adjustment) = 1,60,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1662,
        "text": "<p>(Referring to stem above) If 1/5 of Unearned Income is earned, what is the Unearned Income in the Balance Sheet?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "16,000 TK",
            "20,000 TK",
            "24,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Remaining Unearned = 20,000 TK - (20,000 TK \\times \\frac{1}{5}) = 16,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1663,
        "text": "<p>Building 50,000 TK; Furniture 20,000 TK; Debtors 30,000 TK; Stock 20,000 TK; Cash 10,000 TK; Creditors 40,000 TK. What is the amount of Current Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Assets = Debtors (30,000 TK) + Stock (20,000 TK) + Cash (10,000 TK) = 60,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1664,
        "text": "<p>(Referring to stem above) If TK 5,000 TK is paid to creditors, what is the impact on Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increase by 5,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 5,000 TK",
            "Increase by 10,000 TK",
            "No impact"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Paying a liability decreases an asset (Cash) and a liability (Creditors). It does not affect Capital (Equity).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1665,
        "text": "<p>Prepaid Insurance 30,000 TK on 31-12-2014. Policy taken 1-1-2013 for 4 years. What is the insurance expense for 2014?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "7,500 TK",
            "10,000 TK",
            "15,000 TK",
            "30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Total period 4 years. Expense per year = 40,000 TK (implied total) TK/ 4 = 10,000 TK. Or 1/3 of the 30,000 TK balance since 3 years remain.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1666,
        "text": "<p>If the whole 30,000 TK is shown as 2014 expense, what is the impact on Balance Sheet assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Decrease by 10,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 20,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 22,500 TK",
            "Decrease by 30,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Only 10,000 TK should be expensed. Expensing 30,000 TK removes the 20,000 TK asset portion, thus decreasing assets by 20,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1667,
        "text": "<p>10% Mortgage Loan TK 5,00,000 TK is:\n\ni. Long-term liability\n\nii. External liability\n\niii. Current liability</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Mortgage loans are external and long-term debts.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1668,
        "text": "<p>Adjustment entry for unrecorded free product distribution (6,000 TK) for promotion?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Ad Debit, Cash Credit",
            "Promo Debit, Purchase Credit",
            "Ad Debit, Purchase Credit",
            "Promo Debit, Cash Credit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Free distribution is an Advertising expense, and it reduces the total Purchases.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1669,
        "text": "<p>If 1/3 of Ad (24,000 TK + 6,000 TK) is deferred, how is the revenue portion recorded?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debit Income Stmt 6,000 TK",
            "Show 8,000 TK in Balance Sheet",
            "Debit Income Stmt 20,000 TK",
            "Show 30,000 TK in Balance Sheet"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Ad = 30,000 TK. Revenue Expense (2/3) = 20,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1670,
        "text": "<p>Debtors 40,000 TK; Provision 4,000 TK; Credit Sales 1,62,000 TK; Unrecorded Bad Debt 2,000 TK. New provision 5%. Closing Debtors amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,90,000 TK",
            "1,91,900 TK",
            "2,00,000 TK",
            "2,02,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Debtors = 40,000 TK + 1,62,000 TK = 2,02,000 TK. After unrecorded bad debt = 2,02,000 TK - 2,000 TK = 2,00,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1671,
        "text": "<p>What type of account is a Suspense Account?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhethet Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fixed",
            "Temporary",
            "Current",
            "Nominal"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset Suspense Account is a temporary account used to balance the Trial Balance until errors are found.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1672,
        "text": "<p>What does Net Profit indicate for an organization?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Internal Liability",
            "External Liability",
            "Current Asset",
            "Long-term Asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit belongs to the owner and is added to Capital, representing a debt of the business to the owner (Internal Liability).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1673,
        "text": "<p>If the new Provision for Bad Debts is not recorded at all:\n\ni. Net Profit will increase\n\nii. Owner's Equity will increase\n\niii. Current Assets will increase</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Not recording an expense (provision) keeps profits and equity higher, and not deducting it from Debtors keeps Current Assets higher.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1674,
        "text": "<p>Accounts Receivable (Dec 31) was 4,00,000 TK. Unrecorded Bad Debt 40,000 TK. If a 5% provision is kept on Receivables, what is the New Provision?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "18,000 TK",
            "40,000 TK",
            "58,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>New Provision = TK(4,00,000 TK - 40,000 TK) \\times 5\\% = 18,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1675,
        "text": "<p>Based on the previous data:\n\ni. Assets decrease by 58,000 TK\n\nii. Net Profit decreases by 58,000 TK\n\niii. Net Profit increases by 58,000 TK</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Total effect = Bad Debt (40,000 TK) + New Provision (18,000 TK) = 58,000 TK. This reduces both assets and profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1676,
        "text": "<p>Closing Stock cost is 45,000 TK and Market Value 55,000 TK. What amount goes to Cost of Goods Sold calculation?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "55,000 TK",
            "45,000 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>According to the principle of \"Cost or Market Value, whichever is lower,\" 45,000 TK is used.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1677,
        "text": "<p>Why is 55,000 TK (Market Value) not shown in the Financial Position?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Shows more income",
            "Potential income cannot be shown",
            "Shows more equity",
            "Income cannot be shown low"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The Conservatism principle states we cannot record unrealized/potential gains.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1678,
        "text": "<p>10 TK\\%TK Mortgage Loan 5,00,000 TK. 3 TK/10 TK portion to be paid next year. What is the Long-term Liability?</p>",
        "meta": "St. Joseph",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "1,50,000 TK",
            "5,00,000 TK",
            "3,50,000 TK",
            "6,00,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Liability = 5,00,000 TK \\times 3/10 = 1,50,000 TK. Long-term = 5,00,000 TK - 1,50,000 TK = 3,50,000 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1679,
        "text": "<p>Manager gets 4 TK\\%TK commission on Net Profit after charging commission. Profit is 4,000 TK. Commission?</p>",
        "meta": "St. Joseph",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "150.50 TK",
            "153.85 TK",
            "160 TK",
            "166.67 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Formula: (Profit TK\\timesTK rate) / (100 TK + rate). So, (4,000 TK \\times 4 TK) / 104 TK = 153.85 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1680,
        "text": "<p>Trial Balance: 15 TK\\%TK Invest. (31 TK-03 TK-2023 TK) 50,000 TK; Interest 1,500 TK. Total interest for the year?</p>",
        "meta": "Munshi Abdur Rouf",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "1,500 TK",
            "4,125 TK",
            "5,625 TK",
            "7,125 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>50,000 TK \\times 15\\% \\times 9/12 = 5,625 TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1681,
        "text": "<p>Non-operating incomes are\u2014\n\ni. Discount Received\n\nii. Apprentice Premium\n\niii. Sub-let Rent</p>",
        "meta": "Viqarunnisa",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
