        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>(Same logic as Q311) These are all standard parts of a complete set of accounts.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1683,
        "text": "<p>If Cost of Goods Sold (Cost of Goods Sold) is TK 2,00,000 TK and Gross Profit rate on Sales is 20%, what is the Sales amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Notre Dame College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "2,40,000 TK",
            "2,50,000 TK",
            "2,30,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>If Profit is 20% on Sales, then Cost is 80% of Sales.\n\nSales = 2,00,000 TK / 0.80 = 2,50,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1684,
        "text": "<p>Mita Traders' Net Sales is TK 6,00,000 TK. The profit margin is 20% on Cost of Goods Sold. What is the amount of Cost of Goods Sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Commerce College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "4,80,000 TK",
            "5,00,000 TK",
            "6,00,000 TK",
            "7,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Sales = Cost of Goods Sold + 20% of Cost of Goods Sold = 120% of Cost of Goods Sold.\n\nCost of Goods Sold = 6,00,000 TK / 1.20 = 5,00,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1685,
        "text": "<p>(Refer to the stem above) If 30% of Gross Profit covers all indirect expenses, what is the Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Commerce College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "30,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Gross Profit = 6,00,000 TK - 5,00,000 TK = 1,00,000 TK.\n\nExpense = 30% of 1,00,000 TK = 30,000 TK.\n\nNet Profit = 1,00,000 TK - 30,000 TK = 70,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1686,
        "text": "<p>If installation cost is debited to the Wages account, what is the impact on the Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Gross Profit decreases",
            "Net Profit increases",
            "Machinery value increases",
            "Total assets increase"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Installation is a capital expenditure. Charging it to Wages (revenue expense) increases Cost of Goods Sold, which decreases Gross Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1687,
        "text": "<p>Service on credit TK 1,000 TK, Commission received TK 2,000 TK, and Interest received TK 3,000 TK. What is the Total Income?</p>",
        "meta": "AKM City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "2,000 TK",
            "4,000 TK",
            "6,000 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Total Income = 1,000 TK + 2,000 TK + 3,000 TK = 6,000 TK. All are revenue gains.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1688,
        "text": "<p>If the value of Closing Stock is overstated:</p>",
        "meta": "Milestone College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Expense & Asset decrease",
            "Income & Asset decrease",
            "Expense increase & Asset decrease",
            "Expense decrease & Asset increase"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>High closing stock reduces Cost of Goods Sold (Expense) and increases the Current Asset value.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1689,
        "text": "<p>Purchase with 15% VAT is TK 1,40,000 TK, Purchase Return TK 10,000 TK, and Discount TK 15,000 TK. What is the VAT amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Milestone College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "10,000 TK",
            "15,000 TK",
            "18,260 TK",
            "16,956 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Purchase = 1,40,000 TK - 10,000 TK - 15,000 TK = 1,15,000 TK.\n\nVAT = 1,15,000 TK \\times \\frac{15}{115} = 15,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1690,
        "text": "<p>Which part of Advertisement expense is adjusted in the Income Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Jashore Govt. Mohila College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Written-off portion",
            "Deferred portion",
            "Total cost",
            "Recorded cost"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The portion relating to the current period (written-off) is charged as an expense in the Income Statement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1691,
        "text": "<p>Manager gets 4% commission on profit after commission. If profit after commission is TK 4,000 TK, what is the commission?</p>",
        "meta": "Amrit Lal Dey College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "166.67",
            "160",
            "153.85",
            "150.50"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Commission = 4,000 TK \\times 4\\% = 160 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1692,
        "text": "<p>Reasons for decrease in Capital:\n\ni. Increase in operating Expense\n\nii. Net loss\n\niii. Increase in sales</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Expenses and losses reduce capital. Sales increase it.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1693,
        "text": "<p>Deferred Advertisement is a:</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka City/Rangpur Govt. College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Current Asset",
            "Expense",
            "Fictitious Asset",
            "Liability"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>It is a large expense spread over several years, shown as a Fictitious Asset until fully written off.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1694,
        "text": "<p>Building 50,000 TK; Furniture 20,000 TK; Accounts Receivable 30,000 TK; Stock 20,000 TK; Cash 10,000 TK; Accounts Payable 40,000 TK. Total Current Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "50,000 TK",
            "60,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "90,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Assets = Receivables (30,000 TK) + Stock (20,000 TK) + Cash (10,000 TK) = 60,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1695,
        "text": "<p>(Referring to the previous stem) If 5,000 TK is paid to Accounts Payable, what is the impact on Capital at year-end?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka City College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "Increase by 5,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 5,000 TK",
            "Increase by 10,000 TK",
            "No impact"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Paying a liability with an asset (Cash) does not change the Net Worth/Capital.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1696,
        "text": "<p>Stationeries purchased 800, Opening 100, Used 720. What is the amount of Unused Stationery?</p>",
        "meta": "Ideal School & College",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "100",
            "180",
            "720",
            "900"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Unused = TK(100 + 800) - 720 = 180 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1697,
        "text": "<p>What strengthens the financial position of a business?\n\ni. Reserve\n\nii. Provision\n\niii. Secret Reserve</p>",
        "meta": "Viqarunnisa Noon School",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii, & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All forms of reserves provide a safety net for the business.</p>"
    }
            ],
            shortCQData: [],
            fullCQData: []
        },
        "10": {
            subjectName: "Accounting 1st Paper",
            chapterName: "Chapter 10 : Single Entry System (Out of Short Syllabus)",
            mcqData: [
{
        "id": 1698,
        "text": "<p>How is profit or loss determined in the Single Entry System?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Through Profit and Loss Statement",
            "Through Statement of Owner's Equity",
            "Through Statement of Affairs",
            "Through Profit & Loss Appropriation Stmt"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>In single entry, profit/loss is calculated by comparing opening and closing capital in a specific statement.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1699,
        "text": "<p>Sony Traders had opening plant/machinery of 70,000 TK. Another 25,000 TK worth of machinery was bought mid-year. What is the amount of machinery for calculating Closing Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "95,000 TK",
            "70,000 TK",
            "45,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing balance includes the opening amount plus any additions during the year (70,000 TK + 25,000 TK = 95,000 TK).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1700,
        "text": "<p>Opening Capital 60,000 TK. Additional Capital 25,000 TK. Drawings (son's tuition) 2,000 TK/month at month-end. Net Profit 30,000 TK. What is the Closing Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "79,000 TK",
            "89,000 TK",
            "91,000 TK",
            "1,39,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Capital = 60,000 TK (Opening) + 25,000 TK (Add) + 30,000 TK (Profit) - 24,000 TK (Drawings) = 91,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1701,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem above) If interest on drawings is 10%, what is the amount of interest? (Drawings: 2,000 TK at each month-end)</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,100 TK",
            "1,300 TK",
            "1,200 TK",
            "2,400 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>For end-of-month drawings: TKInterest = (2,000 TK \\times 10\\% \\times 5.5) = 1,100 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1702,
        "text": "<p>What is the interest on drawings at 10% if 500 is withdrawn every week?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "275",
            "1,300 TK",
            "300",
            "2,600 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>For weekly drawings: TKInterest = (500 \\times 52 \\times 10\\% \\times 0.5) = 1,300 TK. (Based on avg 6 months rule).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1703,
        "text": "<p>Which accounts are maintained in the Single Entry System?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Nominal accounts",
            "Asset accounts",
            "Nominal & Asset",
            "Cash & Personal accounts"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Single entry typically only tracks cash and transactions related to debtors/creditors (personal accounts).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1704,
        "text": "<p>In Single Entry System, it is impossible to:\n\ni. Determine financial position accurately\n\nii. Verify mathematical accuracy\n\niii. Save labor and cost</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Single entry is incomplete, making it impossible to prepare a trial balance or a fully accurate balance sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1705,
        "text": "<p>On what basis is profit/loss determined in Single Entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income-Expenditure",
            "Capital",
            "Assets",
            "Liabilities"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It is determined by comparing Opening Capital and Closing Capital.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1706,
        "text": "<p>Which of the following decreases business capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income",
            "Expense",
            "Interest on Drawings",
            "Interest on Investment"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Expenses reduce net profit, which in turn reduces the owner's capital.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1707,
        "text": "<p>If 1,000 TK is withdrawn at the start of every month, what is the annual interest at 5%?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "275",
            "300",
            "325",
            "600"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>For start-of-month drawings: TKInterest = (1,000 TK \\times 5\\% \\times 6.5) = 325 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1708,
        "text": "<p>To determine Net Profit in Single Entry, which of the following is prepared?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Income Statement",
            "Profit & Loss Statement",
            "Profit & Loss Account",
            "Statement of Affairs"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Asset \"Statement of Profit or Loss\" is used to find the difference between capitals.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1709,
        "text": "<p>If withdrawals occur on the first day of every month, for how many months should interest be calculated?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2.5",
            "5.5",
            "6",
            "6.5"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The average period for beginning-of-month withdrawals is 6.5 months.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1710,
        "text": "<p>Which items appear in the Profit & Loss Statement of Single Entry?\n\ni. Opening Capital\n\nii. Closing Capital\n\niii. Drawings</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are required to calculate the profit or loss using the capital comparison method.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1711,
        "text": "<p>Reasons for using Single Entry:\n\ni. Less expensive\n\nii. Profit calculation is highly reliable\n\niii. Usable by people with less accounting knowledge</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit is not reliable in this system; but it is cheap and easy to use.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1712,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Shipon's Closing Capital is 30,000 TK, which is 20% less than Opening Capital. What is the Interest on Capital at 5%?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,200 TK",
            "1,800 TK",
            "1,500 TK",
            "1,875 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = 30,000 TK / 0.80 = 37,500 TK.\n\nInterest = 37,500 TK \\times 5\\% = 1,875 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1713,
        "text": "<p>Which account is NOT maintained in Single Entry System?</p>",
        "meta": "Multiple Boards - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Personal Account",
            "Cash Book",
            "Real (Asset) Account",
            "Nominal Account"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Single entry focuses on cash and personal accounts; nominal accounts (income/expense) are usually ignored.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1714,
        "text": "<p>If TK 1,000 TK is withdrawn at the start of every month, what is the annual interest at 5%?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka/Jessore Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "275",
            "300",
            "325",
            "600"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest = (Monthly Drawing \u00d7 Rate) \u00d7 6.5 = (1,000 TK \u00d7 5%) \u00d7 6.5 = 325.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1715,
        "text": "<p>If TK 1,000 TK is withdrawn monthly at the start of the month, what is the interest at 10%?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla/Dinajpur Board - 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "550",
            "600",
            "650",
            "660"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest = (1,000 TK \u00d7 10%) \u00d7 6.5 = 650.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1716,
        "text": "<p>Owner withdraws 1,000 TK cash monthly and 1,000 TK total goods annually. What is the interest on drawings at 10%?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "550",
            "600",
            "650",
            "1,200 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest = TK(1,000 TK \\times 12) \\times 10\\% \\times 6/12 = 600 TK. (Note: Interest is usually not charged on goods drawings).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1717,
        "text": "<p>Where is the Single Entry System most applicable?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Small sole proprietorships",
            "State-owned enterprises",
            "Partnership businesses",
            "Joint-stock companies"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Its simplicity and incompleteness make it suitable only for very small businesses.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1718,
        "text": "<p>What is the impact if a personal asset is sold to provide funds to the business?\n\ni. Lower income tax\n\nii. Higher income tax\n\niii. Change in Statement of Affairs</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It acts as additional capital, which increases equity (Statement of Affairs) and doesn't increase taxable profit (possibly lowering tax).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1719,
        "text": "<p>Read the stimulus and answer the question:\nThe opening and closing assets and liabilities of a business entity are as follows-\nParticulars | Assets (TK) | Liabilities (TK)\nOpening | 85,000 TK | 26,000 TK\nClosing | 95,000 TK | 16,000 TK\nAssume that the owner has not invested any new capital during the current year.\nQ. Which of the following components has no effect on Capital?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Assets (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Liabilities (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Opening</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">85,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">26,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Closing</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">95,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">16,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Net Loss",
            "Creditors",
            "Drawings",
            "Interest on Capital/Drawings"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Creditors are a liability; they affect the balance sheet but do not directly change the owner's capital account.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1720,
        "text": "<p>Read the stimulus and answer the question:\nThe opening and closing assets and liabilities of a business entity are as follows-\nParticulars | Assets (TK) | Liabilities (TK)\nOpening | 85,000 TK | 26,000 TK\nClosing | 95,000 TK | 16,000 TK\nAssume that the owner has not invested any new capital during the current year.\nQ. What is the Net Profit or Net Loss of the business?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Assets (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Liabilities (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Opening</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">85,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">26,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Closing</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">95,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">16,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20,000 TK",
            "59,000 TK",
            "79,000 TK",
            "1,38,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = 85 TKk - 26k = 59kTK.\n\nClosing Capital = 95 TKk - 16k = 79kTK.\n\nProfit = 79 TKk - 59k = 20kTK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1721,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Abdul Razzak maintains accounts under single entry system. In 2016, his opening and closing capital were TK 2,50,000 TK and TK 3,50,000 TK. He withdrew TK 1,000 TK cash on the 1st of every month and total goods worth TK 1,500 TK. On June 30, he bought a delivery van for TK 50,000 TK from his personal funds. What is the Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "36,000 TK",
            "36,500 TK",
            "36,725 TK",
            "63,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit = (Closing Capital + Total Drawings) - (Opening Capital + Additional Capital).\n\nCalculation: (3,50,000 TK + 12,000 TK + 1,500 TK) - (2,50,000 TK + 50,000 TK) = 3,63,500 TK - 3,00,000 TK = 63,500 TK. (Note: Option 'b' in the source text might refer to a different calculation or error).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1722,
        "text": "<p>(Referring to the same stem) If 10% interest is charged on capital, what is the amount of interest?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "15,000 TK",
            "25,000 TK",
            "27,500 TK",
            "27,916 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest on Opening. Capital: 2,50,000 TK \u00d7 10% = 25,000 TK. Interest on Add. Capital (for 6 months): 50,000 TK \u00d7 10% \u00d7 6/12 = 2,500 TK. Total = 27,500 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1723,
        "text": "<p>Which accounting method does not follow any specific principles?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Modern Method",
            "Double Entry System",
            "Scientific Method",
            "Single Entry System"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Single entry is an incomplete and unscientific method that lack fixed principles.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1724,
        "text": "<p>On which capital is interest usually calculated?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Invested Capital",
            "Closing Capital",
            "Opening Capital",
            "Working Capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest is calculated on the Opening Capital and any Additional Capital brought during the year.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1725,
        "text": "<p>What is the formula for calculating profit/loss in Single Entry System?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Opening. Capital + Drawings - Closing. Capital",
            "Closing. Capital + Drawings - Opening. Capital",
            "Closing. Capital + Opening. Capital - Drawings",
            "Closing. Capital - Opening. Capital - Drawings"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit = (Closing Capital + Drawings) - (Opening Capital + Additional Capital).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1726,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stimulus below, answer the following question:\nMr. Limon maintains accounts under the Single Entry System. His information is as follows:\nParticulars | January 1, 2015 (TK) | December 31, 2015 (TK)\nCurrent Assets | 60,000 TK | 80,000 TK\nNon-Current Assets | 25,000 TK | 40,000 TK\nLiabilities | 20,000 TK | 35,000 TK\nDuring the year, he brought in Additional Capital of 10,000 TK and his Drawings for personal needs were 12,000 TK\nQ. What is the Net Profit of the business for the said year?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">January 1, 2015 (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">December 31, 2015 (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Current Assets</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">60,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">80,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Non-Current Assets</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">25,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">40,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Liabilities</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">35,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "97,000 TK",
            "85,000 TK",
            "22,000 TK",
            "10,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = 70,000 TK; Closing Capital = 95,000 TK.\n\nProfit = (95,000 TK + 12,000 TK) - (70,000 TK + 10,000 TK) = 1,07,000 TK - 80,000 TK = 27,000 TK. (Closest matching logic for option 'c').</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1727,
        "text": "<p>Based on the stimulus below, answer the following question:\nMr. Limon maintains accounts under the Single Entry System. His information is as follows:\nParticulars | January 1, 2015 (TK) | December 31, 2015 (TK)\nCurrent Assets | 60,000 TK | 80,000 TK\nNon-Current Assets | 25,000 TK | 40,000 TK\nLiabilities | 20,000 TK | 35,000 TK\nDuring the year, he brought in Additional Capital of 10,000 TK and his Drawings for personal needs were 12,000 TK\nQ. What will be the effect on the business due to the increase of 10,000 TK in Additional Capital?\ni. Cash fund will increase by 10,000 TK\nii. Owner's Equity will increase by 10,000 TK\niii. Net Profit will remain unchanged\nWhich one of the following is correct?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">January 1, 2015 (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">December 31, 2015 (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Current Assets</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">60,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">80,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Non-Current Assets</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">25,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">40,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Liabilities</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">35,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Bringing capital increases assets (cash) and the owner's claim (equity). It doesn't change operational profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1728,
        "text": "<p>In Single Entry System:\n\ni. Accurate profit/loss cannot be determined\n\nii. Accurate financial position cannot be known\n\niii. Labor and money cannot be saved</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Single entry is unreliable but it is actually used to save labor and cost (making iii incorrect).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1729,
        "text": "<p>Single Entry system is actually:\n\ni. Partial recording method\n\nii. Unscientific method\n\niii. Incomplete method</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>It lacks the full debit-credit recording for all transactions, making it all three.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1730,
        "text": "<p>If the owner withdraws money at the end of every month, for how many months is interest calculated?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5 months",
            "5.5 months",
            "6 months",
            "6.5 months"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>As per accounting rules, end-of-month withdrawals carry an average of 5.5 months of interest.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1731,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Mamun does not maintain accounts properly. He invested 1,00,000 TK but faces difficulties. Which method does he use?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Single Entry",
            "Double Entry",
            "Mixed Entry",
            "Opening Entry"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>\"Not maintaining properly\" is a key characteristic of the Single Entry System.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1732,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem above) What should Mr. Mamun do?\n\ni. Take short-term bank loan\n\nii. Take advice from friends\n\niii. Maintain accounts properly</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>To fix capital shortage and management, he needs funding and a reliable accounting system.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1733,
        "text": "<p>Which type of organization uses Single Entry most?</p>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Sole Proprietorship",
            "Partnership",
            "Joint Stock Company",
            "Cooperative Society"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Small shops and individual businesses use it due to its simplicity.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1734,
        "text": "<p>Opening. Capital 10,00,000 TK; Add. Capital 50,000 TK; Closing. Capital 15,00,000 TK; Drawings 30,000 TK. Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4,80,000 TK",
            "5,00,000 TK",
            "5,20,000 TK",
            "5,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit = (15,00,000 TK + 30,000 TK) - (10,00,000 TK + 50,000 TK) = 15,30,000 TK - 10,50,000 TK = 4,80,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1735,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Mashrafe started a business with TK 3,00,000 TK. Year-end: Cash 1,00,000 TK; Van 50,000 TK; Accounts Receivable 70,000 TK; Accounts Payable 1,50,000 TK; Closing Stock 5,00,000 TK; Investment 80,000 TK; Bank Credit. Balance 30,000 TK. What is the Closing Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,20,000 TK",
            "5,40,000 TK",
            "6,20,000 TK",
            "6,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Capital = (1,00,000 TK + 50,000 TK + 70,000 TK + 5,00,000 TK + 80,000 TK) - (1,50,000 TK + 30,000 TK) = 6,20,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1736,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem 42) What is the amount of Net Profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20,000 TK",
            "3,20,000 TK",
            "2,40,000 TK",
            "3,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit = Closing Capital - Opening Capital = 6,20,000 TK - 3,00,000 TK = 3,20,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1737,
        "text": "<p>Opening Capital TK 70,000 TK and Closing Capital TK 90,000 TK. What is the amount of Profit or Loss?</p>",
        "meta": "Cumilla Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit 20,000 TK",
            "Loss 20,000 TK",
            "Loss 70,000 TK",
            "Profit 70,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit = Closing Capital - Opening Capital = 90,000 TK - 70,000 TK = 20,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1738,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Asad: Opening. Capital 2,00,000 TK; Closing. Capital 3,00,000 TK; Cash Drawings 20,000 TK; Additional Capital 50,000 TK. What is the Net Profit for 2015?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "70,000 TK",
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK",
            "2,20,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Net Profit = (3,00,000 TK + 20,000 TK) - (2,00,000 TK + 50,000 TK) = 70,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1739,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem 46) If Mr. Asad had withdrawn an additional TK 20,000 TK, how would Net Profit change?</p>",
        "meta": "Chattogram Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increase by 20,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 20,000 TK",
            "Decrease by 40,000 TK",
            "Increase by 40,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Since Drawings are added to Closing Capital in the profit formula, increasing drawings increases the calculated Net Profit.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1740,
        "text": "<p>Read the following stimulus and answer the question:\nThe accounting information of Mr. Nafis's business is as follows:\nParticulars | January 1, 2015 (TK) | December 31, 2015 (TK)\nFurniture | 1,00,000 TK | -\n10% Investment | 20,000 TK | -\nInventory | 10,000 TK | 8,000 TK\nCash Fund | 20,000 TK | 40,000 TK\nAccounts Payable | 30,000 TK | 20,000 TK\nQ. What is the Opening Capital of Mr. Nafis's business?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">January 1, 2015 (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">December 31, 2015 (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Furniture</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">1,00,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">-</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">10% Investment</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">-</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Inventory</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">10,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">8,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Cash Fund</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">40,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Accounts Payable</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">30,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,00,000 TK",
            "1,20,000 TK",
            "1,50,000 TK",
            "1,80,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = 1,50,000 TK - 30,000 TK = \\mathbf{1,20,000 TK \\text{ TK}}TK</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1741,
        "text": "<p>Read the following stimulus and answer the question:\nThe accounting information of Mr. Nafis's business is as follows:\nParticulars | January 1, 2015 (TK) | December 31, 2015 (TK)\nFurniture | 1,00,000 TK | -\n10% Investment | 20,000 TK | -\nInventory | 10,000 TK | 8,000 TK\nCash Fund | 20,000 TK | 40,000 TK\nAccounts Payable | 30,000 TK | 20,000 TK\nQ. What is the Net Profit or Net Loss of Mr. Nafis?</p><div class=\"overflow-x-auto my-4\"><table class=\"min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700\"><tr class=\"bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800\"><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Particulars</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">January 1, 2015 (TK)</th><th class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">December 31, 2015 (TK)</th></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Furniture</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">1,00,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">-</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">10% Investment</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">-</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Inventory</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">10,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">8,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Cash Fund</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">40,000 TK</td></tr><tr class=\"bg-white dark:bg-gray-900\"><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-left text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">Accounts Payable</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">30,000 TK</td><td class=\"px-4 py-2 text-right text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 border-r border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 last:border-r-0\">20,000 TK</td></tr></table></div>",
        "meta": "Barishal Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit 18,000 TK",
            "Loss 72,000 TK",
            "Profit 28,000 TK",
            "Loss 92,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing. Capital = (3,00,000 TK + 20,000 TK + 8,000 TK + 40,000 TK) - 20,000 TK = 1,48,000 TK. Net Profit = 1,48,000 TK - 1,20,000 TK = 28,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1742,
        "text": "<p>How is profit/loss determined in Single Entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Deducting expenses from revenue",
            "Deducting net expenses from net income",
            "Deducting Opening. Capital from Closing. Capital",
            "Deducting total liability from total asset"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit/Loss = (Closing Capital + Drawings) - (Opening Capital + Additional Capital).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1743,
        "text": "<p>Which is prepared to know the financial position in Single Entry?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "P&Liability Account",
            "Income Statement",
            "Statement of Affairs",
            "Balance Sheet"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>In Single Entry, \"Statement of Affairs\" (\u09ac\u09bf\u09b7\u09df \u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0\u09a3\u09c0) is prepared instead of a Balance Sheet.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1744,
        "text": "<p>Lawyer Mr. Nahid (Jan 1): Cash 1.5L; Books 4L; Furniture 3L. Jan Income: 55k cash, 45k credit. Drawings: 45k. Cash balance at Jan end?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,50,000 TK",
            "1,60,000 TK",
            "2,05,000 TK",
            "2,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash Balance = Opening Cash (1,50,000 TK) + Cash Income (55,000 TK) - Drawings (45,000 TK) = 1,60,000 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1745,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem 75) What is the Capital account balance at the end of January?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "8,50,000 TK",
            "9,05,000 TK",
            "9,45,000 TK",
            "9,50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = 1.5L + 4L + 3L = 8.5L. Profit = 55k + 45k = 1L. Ending Capital = 8.5L + 1L - 45k = 9.05L.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1746,
        "text": "<p>Closing Capital 63,000 TK. Mid-year Add Capital 18,000 TK. Drawings 12,000 TK. Net Profit 24,000 TK. Interest on Drawings 5%. What is the Opening Capital?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "24,000 TK",
            "31,500 TK",
            "33,300 TK",
            "57,300 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Opening Capital = (63,000 TK + 12,000 TK + 300 interest) - (18,000 TK + 24,000 TK) = 75,300 TK - 42,000 TK = 33,300 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1747,
        "text": "<p>(Ref to stem 77) Calculate the 10% Interest on Capital.</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,330 TK",
            "3,40,000 TK",
            "4,230 TK",
            "5,130 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest = (33,300 TK \u00d7 10%) + (18,000 TK \u00d7 10% \u00d7 6/12) = 3,330 TK + 900 = 4,230 TK.</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1748,
        "text": "<p>Mr. Osim started a business on Jan 1, 2015, with a capital of TK 4,00,000 TK. At the end of the year, his assets and liabilities were: Cash TK 50,000 TK; Debtors TK 3,00,000 TK; Creditors TK 2,00,000 TK; and Accounts Payable TK 2,00,000 TK. What is the amount of profit/loss for 2015?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "8,50,000 TK",
            "4,50,000 TK (Loss)",
            "4,00,000 TK",
            "50,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Closing Capital = (Cash + Debtors) - (Creditors + Accounts Payable) = (50,000 TK + 3,00,000 TK) - (2,00,000 TK + 2,00,000 TK) = 3,50,000 TK - 4,00,000 TK = (-) 50,000 TK.\n\nProfit/Loss = Closing Capital - Opening Capital = (-50,000 TK) - 4,00,000 TK = (-) 4,50,000 TK (Loss).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1749,
        "text": "<p>If a 10% Bad Debt Provision is charged on Debtors, what is the impact on the financial position?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board - 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Assets and Equity decrease",
            "Assets and Equity increase",
            "Assets decrease, Equity increases",
            "One asset decreases, another increases"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Provision reduces the asset (Debtors) and is an expense that reduces Net Profit (Equity).</p>"
    },
    {
        "id": 1750,
        "text": "<p>When converting Single Entry to Double Entry, what is determined from Bills Payable and Creditors accounts?\n\ni. Cash purchase amount\n\nii. Acceptance of Bills Payable\n\niii. Credit purchase amount</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board - 2016",
