        explanation: "<p>Over-charging depreciation increases expenses, which reduces net profit and owner's equity. It does not affect liabilities.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 39,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Salam Enterprise purchased a machine for 60,000 Taka on Jan 1, 2023. Life is 10 years and salvage value is 10,000 Taka.</p><p>Q. What is the depreciation for 2023 under the straight-line method?</p>",
