{
        id: 76,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2'>Roni Ltd. purchased office equipment for 10,00,000 Taka, paid 10% VAT, and 20,000 Taka carriage. Life is 10 years, salvage value is 70,000 Taka.</p><p>Q. What is the annual depreciation under the straight-line method?</p>",
        meta: "Mymensingh Board · 2023",
        type: "board",
        options: ["95,000 Taka", "1,00,000 Taka", "1,05,000 Taka", "1,10,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 2,
        explanation: "<div class='text-xs space-y-1'><p>Total Cost = 10,00,000 + 1,00,000 (VAT) + 20,000 = 11,20,000.</p><p>Depreciable Value = 11,20,000 - 70,000 = 10,50,000.</p><p>Annual Dep = 10,50,000 / 10 = <strong>1,05,000 Taka</strong>.</p></div>"
    },
    {
        id: 77,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Roni Ltd. cost: 11,20,000. Straight-line dep: 1,05,000. If 20% Reducing Balance was used instead in Year 1...</p><p>Q. How will the financial statements change?</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Operating profit decreases by 1,19,000<br>ii. Fixed assets decrease by 1,19,000<br>iii. Owner's Equity decreases by 1,19,000</p>",
        meta: "Mymensingh Board · 2023",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 3,
        explanation: "<p>RB Dep = 11,20,000 × 20% = 2,24,000. Extra expense = 1,19,000. This higher expense reduces profit, asset book value, and equity by that amount. All are correct.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 78,
        text: "<p>Which of the following is NOT considered in straight-line depreciation?</p>",
