    {
        id: 92,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2'>Padma Co. machine depreciable value 1,80,000, salvage value 20,000. Rate is 10%.</p><p>Q. What is the purchase price (acquisition cost) of the machine?</p>",
        meta: "Chittagong Board · 2022",
        type: "board",
        options: ["1,60,000 Taka", "1,80,000 Taka", "2,00,000 Taka", "2,20,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 2,
        explanation: "<p>Purchase Price = Depreciable Value + Salvage Value = 1,80,000 + 20,000 = <strong>2,00,000 Taka</strong>.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 93,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Cost = 2,00,000. Rate = 10%. Year 1 depreciation is 20,000 Taka.</p><p>Q. Which method is the company using?</p>",
        meta: "Chittagong Board · 2022",
        type: "board",
        options: ["Straight-line", "Reducing balance", "Production unit", "Sum-of-years'-digits"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>Under Reducing Balance, Year 1 dep is on the full Cost (2,00,000 × 10% = 20,000). Under SLM, it would be on Depreciable Value (1,80,000 × 10% = 18,000). Thus, it is <strong>Reducing Balance</strong>.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 94,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Sonali Traders purchased a machine on June 30, 2021, for 50,000 Taka. Installation 7,000, Carriage 3,000. Salvage 5,000, Life 5 yrs. Year ends Dec 31.</p><p>Q. What is the 2021 depreciation under the straight-line method?</p>",
        meta: "Barisal Board · 2022",
