    {
        id: 96,
        text: "<p>Which depreciation method uses the formula: <br><span class='font-mono'>r = (1 - <sup>n</sup>√(s/c)) × 100</span> ?</p>",
        meta: "Dinajpur Board · 2022",
        type: "board",
        options: ["Straight-line", "Reducing balance", "Sum-of-years'-digits", "Production unit"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>Reducing Balance Rate, <span class='font-mono font-bold'>r = (1 - <sup>n</sup>&radic;(s/c)) &times; 100</span></p><div class='text-xs mt-2 space-y-1'><p>Where:</p><p>r = Rate of Depreciation (অবচয়ের হার)</p><p>n = Estimated Life (সম্পত্তির আয়ুষ্কাল)</p><p>s = Salvage Value (ভগ্নাবশেষ মূল্য)</p><p>c = Cost (ক্রয়মূল্য)</p></div>"
    },
    {
        id: 97,
        text: "<p>Depreciation is an-</p>",
        meta: "Dinajpur Board · 2022",
        type: "board",
        options: ["Visible expense", "Invisible expense", "Fictitious expense", "Cash expense"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>It is an <strong>Invisible expense</strong> because no physical cash flows out when the asset value is written down.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 98,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Rongdhonu Traders imported a machine for 3,00,000. Duty 30k, Freight 20k, Carriage 10k, Installation 5k, Expert fee 10k.</p><p>Q. What is the total cost of the machine?</p>",
