    {
        id: 116,
        text: "<p>Sold furniture for 15,000 on Dec 31, 2020. Book value was 12,000. Which are correct?</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs'>i. Cash account Dr 15,000<br>ii. Profit on sale Dr 3,000<br>iii. Furniture account Cr 12,000</p>",
        meta: "Dhaka Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>Profit on sale is an <strong>Income</strong> (Credit), not a Debit. i and iii are correct entries.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 117,
        text: "<p>Intangible assets are-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Goodwill<br>ii. Preliminary expenses<br>iii. Patent</p>",
        meta: "Rajshahi Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>Preliminary expenses are <strong>fictitious assets</strong>, while Goodwill and Patents are intangible assets. i and iii are the correct pair.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 118,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Hossain Ent. purchased a machine on Sep 30, 2020, for 80,000. Installation 12,000, carriage 3,000. Life 5 yrs, salvage 5,000.</p><p>Q. What is the 2020 depreciation under the straight-line method?</p>",
        meta: "Rajshahi Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["3,750 Taka", "4,000 Taka", "4,500 Taka", "4,750 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 2,
        explanation: "<div class='text-xs space-y-1'><p>Cost = 95,000. Depreciable Value = 90,000. </p><p>Annual Dep = 18,000. Used for 3 months (Oct-Dec).</p><p>Dep = 18,000 × 3/12 = <strong>4,500 Taka</strong>.</p></div>"
    },
    {
        id: 119,
        text: "<p>In the above stem, what would be the depreciation rate for double reducing balance?</p>",
        meta: "Rajshahi Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["20%", "25%", "30%", "40%"],
        correctAnswer: 3,
        explanation: "<p>(100 / 5) × 2 = <strong>40%</strong>.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 120,
        text: "<p>Depreciation is-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. An internal transaction<br>ii. Charged on fixed asset value<br>iii. A non-cash expense</p>",
        meta: "Rajshahi Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "ii & iii", "i & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 3
    },
    {
        id: 121,
        text: "<p>A company decided to devalue its assets by 10% at year-end. This results in-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Reduced equity<br>ii. Increased expense<br>iii. Reduced profit</p>",
        meta: "Rajshahi Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 3
    },
    {
        id: 122,
        text: "<p>Which depreciation method is most suitable for Leasehold Property, Patents, or Trademarks?</p>",
        meta: "Comilla Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["Machine-hour rate", "Straight-line method", "Reducing balance method", "Depreciation fund method"],
        correctAnswer: 1
    },
    {
        id: 123,
        text: "<p>Depreciation is a-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Cash expense<br>ii. Non-cash expense<br>iii. Revenue expense</p>",
        meta: "Comilla Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 2
    },
    {
        id: 124,
        text: "<p>Factors considered in straight-line depreciation are-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Acquisition cost<br>ii. Estimated life<br>iii. Book value</p>",
        meta: "Comilla Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "i & iii", "ii & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 0,
        explanation: "<p>Straight-line uses cost, not <strong>Book value</strong>, as the basis for the calculation. i and ii are correct.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 125,
        text: "<p>Suma Traders bought a machine for 50,000, paid 5,000 duty, 3,000 carriage, and 1,000 operator's salary. How much should be debited to Machinery?</p>",
        meta: "Comilla Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["50,000 Taka", "55,000 Taka", "58,000 Taka", "59,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 2,
        explanation: "<p>50,000 + 5,000 + 3,000 = <strong>58,000 Taka</strong>. Operator's salary is a recurring revenue expense.</p>"
    },
{
        id: 126,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2'>Suma Traders bought a machine for 50k, paid 5k duty, 3k carriage, and 1k operator salary.</p><p>Q. If the carriage cost (3,00,0 Taka) is debited to the Income Statement instead of being capitalized-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-xs'>i. Asset value will decrease by 3,000<br>ii. Net profit will decrease by 3,000<br>iii. Asset value on the balance sheet will remain unchanged</p>",
        meta: "Comilla Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "ii & iii", "i & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 0,
        explanation: "<p>Carriage is a capital cost. Treating it as an expense overstates expenses (reducing profit) and understates the asset cost. i and ii are correct.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 127,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Mr. Delta cost: 5,00,000, Installation: 20,000. Life 10 yrs, salvage value 20,000. Straight-line method used.</p><p>Q. What is the annual depreciation amount?</p>",
        meta: "Chittagong Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["48,000 Taka", "50,000 Taka", "52,000 Taka", "54,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<p>Depreciable Value = (5,00,000 + 20,000) - 20,000 = 5,00,000. Annual Dep = 5,00,000 / 10 = <strong>50,000 Taka</strong>.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 128,
        text: "<p>In the above stem, if Reducing Balance (20%) was used instead of Straight-line, by how much more would the asset value decrease on the balance sheet in the first year?</p>",
        meta: "Chittagong Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["42,000 Taka", "46,000 Taka", "50,000 Taka", "54,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 3,
        explanation: "<div class='text-xs space-y-1'><p>RB Dep = 5,20,000 × 20% = 1,04,000.</p><p>SL Dep = 50,000. </p><p>Difference = 1,04,000 - 50,000 = <strong>54,000 Taka</strong>.</p></div>"
    },
    {
        id: 129,
        text: "<p>Depreciation is a-</p><p class='ml-4 my-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400'>i. Cost allocation process<br>ii. Capital expenditure<br>iii. Non-cash expense</p>",
        meta: "Sylhet Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["i & ii", "ii & iii", "i & iii", "i, ii & iii"],
        correctAnswer: 2,
        explanation: "<p>Depreciation is a <strong>revenue expense</strong> and a cost allocation process, not a capital expenditure. i and iii are correct.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 130,
        text: "<p>Read the following stem and answer the question:</p><p class='italic my-2 border-l-4 border-sky-400 pl-3 bg-sky-50 dark:bg-sky-900/10 py-2 text-[13px]'>Alam Ent. bought a machine on July 1, 2018, for 60,000. Life 10 yrs, salvage 10,000. Straight-line method used.</p><p>Q. What is the depreciation for the year 2018?</p>",
        meta: "Sylhet Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["7,000 Taka", "6,000 Taka", "5,000 Taka", "2,500 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 3,
        explanation: "<p>Annual Dep = 5,000. For 6 months (July-Dec) = 5,000 × 6/12 = <strong>2,500 Taka</strong>.</p>"
    },
    {
        id: 131,
        text: "<p>In the above stem, if 20% Reducing Balance was used, what would be the depreciation for the year 2019?</p>",
        meta: "Sylhet Board · 2021",
        type: "board",
        options: ["14,000 Taka", "10,800 Taka", "10,000 Taka", "6,000 Taka"],
        correctAnswer: 1,
        explanation: "<div class='text-xs space-y-1'><p>2018 Dep (6 mo) = 60,000 × 20% × 6/12 = 6,000.</p><p>BV end of 2018 = 54,000. </p><p>2019 Dep (Full yr) = 54,000 × 20% = <strong>10,800 Taka</strong>.</p></div>"
    },
    {
