        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Liquidity is reduced when cash is tied up in long-term assets or uncollected receivables.</p>",
        "id": 3567
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Rahman is a banker. He wants to invest TK 7 lakh. Out of that money, he wants to keep TK 5 lakh as an FDR in a bank and purchase shares of Jamuna Oil Company with the remaining TK 2 lakh.\n\n\n\nQ: Which principle is Mr. Rahman following in his investment?</p>",
