        "id": 3619
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Azad, instead of investing his savings in one company, invested in three companies. That is, he purchased shares of three companies from the secondary stock market.\n\n\n\nQ: Which principle of finance did Mr. Azad follow in his investment?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Liquidity and Profit",
            "Risk and Profit",
            "Portfolio Principle",
            "Time Value of Money"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Spreading investment across multiple companies is a classic application of the Portfolio/Diversification Principle.</p>",
        "id": 3620
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: As a result of this type of investment by Mr. Azad, in terms of receiving income—</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increase risk",
            "Decrease risk",
            "Be risk-free",
            "Remain unchanged"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Diversification reduces unsystematic risk, though it cannot eliminate systematic (market) risk entirely.</p>",
        "id": 3621
    },
    {
