        "explanation": "<p>In modern finance, the ability to generate and manage \"Cash Flow\" is the true measure of financial efficiency.</p>",
        "id": 3641
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>An investor controls risk by following which of the following?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Risk and Profit Policy",
            "Portfolio Diversification Policy",
            "Liquidity and Profit Policy",
            "Social Welfare Policy"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Portfolio diversification is the standard technical method for managing and controlling investment risk.</p>",
        "id": 3642
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Through which method can profit be increased?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Reducing dividends",
            "Reducing cash flow",
            "Taking loans",
            "Reducing costs"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Reducing operating and financial costs is the most direct way to increase the net profit of a firm.</p>",
        "id": 3643
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Undistributed profit: i. Acts as a source of funds, ii. Is used for reinvestment, iii. Is in the interest of shareholders.</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Retained earnings are a cheap internal source of funds that grow the company, benefiting shareholders in the long run.</p>",
        "id": 3644
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Functions of finance include: i. Dividend decision, ii. Investment decision, iii. Financing decision.</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These are the three fundamental pillars of financial management.</p>",
        "id": 3645
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The relationship between return (income) and risk is—</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Negative",
            "Positive",
            "Proportional",
            "Downward"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>There is a positive correlation; higher risk levels are expected to yield higher returns.</p>",
        "id": 3646
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Hanif is the owner of a firm. Last year his income was TK 1 crore 50 lakh. He kept TK 50 lakh as liquidity or cash and deposited the remaining TK 1 crore in the bank.\n\n\n\nQ: Which principle should Mr. Hanif follow for keeping cash on hand to manage current operations?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Risk and Profit",
            "Portfolio",
            "Liquidity and Profit",
            "All of the above"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Liquidity and Profitability principle helps decide the optimal balance of cash to keep on hand versus investing.</p>",
        "id": 3647
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: If Mr. Hanif keeps all of his income in the bank, then—\n\n\ni. Liquidity will decrease\n\n\nii. Profitability will increase\n\n\niii. Probability of bankruptcy will increase</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Keeping all cash in a bank account (instead of on-hand for bills) lowers immediate liquidity and raises the risk of defaulting on daily payments.</p>",
        "id": 3648
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>\"Expenditure first, Income later\" applies to which type of finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Personal",
            "Diligent",
            "Public (Government)",
            "Business"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Public finance is unique because the government determines its budget expenses first and then finds sources of income.</p>",
        "id": 3649
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Distributing profit among shareholders is which type of financial decision?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fund Collection",
            "Short-term Asset Management",
            "Fund Distribution (Dividend)",
            "Capital Budgeting"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Distributing earnings is specifically known as the \"Dividend Decision\" or \"Fund Distribution.\"</p>",
        "id": 3650
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the mix/control of Equity capital and Debt capital called?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Capital Management",
            "Capital Structure",
            "Capital Budgeting",
            "Cost of Capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Capital Structure refers to the specific mix of debt and equity used to finance a firm's overall operations and growth.</p>",
        "id": 3651
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Mamun is a restaurant owner. Last year he earned a profit of TK 50 lakh. He kept TK 20 lakh as working capital and invested the remaining amount in fish and poultry farms.\n\n\n\nQ: The decision to keep TK 20 lakh as working capital is consistent with which principle of finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Risk and Profit",
            "Liquidity and Profit",
            "Portfolio",
            "Dividend"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the Liquidity-Profitability tradeoff; keeping cash ensures bills are paid, but limits potential investment returns.</p>",
        "id": 3652
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: As a result of Mr. Mamun's investment in fish and poultry farms—\n\n\ni. Risk has decreased\n\n\nii. Expected profit will be achieved\n\n\niii. Risk has increased</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>By diversifying into two different sectors, he reduces specific risk and improves the chance of earning stable profits.</p>",
        "id": 3653
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the core subject matter of finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board · 2023",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Labor",
            "Planning",
            "Fund",
            "Production"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Finance is essentially the science and art of managing \"funds.\"</p>",
        "id": 3654
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the main objective of public finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh Board · 2023",
