        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Wealth maximization is the modern ultimate goal because it considers the time value of money and risk.</p>",
        "id": 3661
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>With which branch of economics does finance have a closer relationship?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Microeconomics",
            "Macroeconomics",
            "Consumer Behavior",
            "Personal Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Finance is deeply connected to Macroeconomics as it involves financial markets, interest rates, and economic policies.</p>",
        "id": 3662
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Considerations in finance: i. Determining amount of money, ii. Determining sources of money, iii. Collection and proper use of money.</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>These steps encompass the entire cycle of financial management.</p>",
        "id": 3663
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Agrani Ltd. operates its business by taking a loan of TK 50,000 at a 10% interest rate from Sunmoon Bank and makes a profit of TK 10,000. Following the decision of the Board of Directors, the company distributes the entire profit proportionally among the shareholders. The following year, the organization faces a cash crisis while trying to pay wages.\n\n\n\nQ: Which principle of finance did Agrani Ltd. fail to follow, leading to a cash crisis in paying wages?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Risk and Profit",
            "Liquidity and Profit",
            "Time value of money",
            "Diversification"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>By distributing all cash as dividends, they failed to maintain enough liquidity to cover operating expenses like wages.</p>",
        "id": 3664
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: The decisions taken by Agrani Ltd. in the stem are related to:\n\n\ni. Financing\n\n\nii. Investment\n\n\niii. Dividend</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Borrowing is a Financing Decision (i) and distributing profit is a Dividend Decision (iii).</p>",
        "id": 3665
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What does wealth maximization mean in finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Increasing Net Present Value",
            "Increasing fund collection",
            "Increasing net profit",
            "Increasing fixed capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Wealth maximization is achieved by maximizing the Net Present Value (N<code>PV</code>) of the firm's projects, which boosts share price.</p>",
        "id": 3666
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is social responsibility in finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Balancing risk and profit",
            "Protecting investor interests",
            "Profit maximization",
            "Wealth maximization"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Acting in the interest of stakeholders like investors is a core social/ethical responsibility.</p>",
        "id": 3667
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is meant by the liquidity and profitability principle?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Maintaining adequate liquid assets",
            "High liquidity, low investment",
            "Low liquidity, high investment",
            "Investing in multiple securities"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>It refers to the strategy of finding the right balance between having enough cash (liquidity) and investing for profit.</p>",
        "id": 3668
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Business finance is: i. Collecting money, ii. Short-term investment, iii. Long-term investment.</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Business finance covers the acquisition of funds and their allocation across both current and fixed assets.</p>",
        "id": 3669
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Ms. Nuha is the financial manager of a company. She takes a loan of TK 50,00,000 from a bank at 7% interest and invests it in a profitable project. At the end of the year, she earns a profit of TK 7,00,000 from that project.\n\n\n\nQ: Which principle of finance did Ms. Nuha adopt?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Debt policy",
            "Risk and Profit principle",
            "Liquidity and Profitability",
            "Portfolio policy"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>She balanced the cost/risk of debt against the potential return of the project.</p>",
        "id": 3670
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: The decisions taken by Ms. Nuha are:\n\n\ni. Investment decision\n\n\nii. Financing decision\n\n\niii. Dividend decision</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Taking a loan is a Financing Decision (ii) and putting it in a project is an Investment Decision (i).</p>",
        "id": 3671
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Objectives of portfolio investment: i. Increase profit, ii. Decrease risk, iii. Market control.</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Portfolio investment focuses on maximizing returns for a given level of risk through diversification; it does not aim for market control.</p>",
        "id": 3672
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the core subject matter of finance?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fund",
            "Planning",
            "Production",
            "Labor"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Finance essentially deals with the mobilization and management of \"funds.\"</p>",
        "id": 3673
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is it called when investment is made in multiple profitable projects?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Time value of money principle",
            "Liquidity principle",
            "Portfolio principle",
            "Suitability principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Portfolio Principle involves spreading investments across different assets to minimize unsystematic risk.</p>",
        "id": 3674
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a source of internal financing?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Industrial Bank",
            "Commercial Bank",
            "Commercial Paper",
            "Income Tax"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Tax-related funds or retained surpluses are considered internal sources compared to external bank loans.</p>",
        "id": 3675
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is NOT considered in wealth maximization?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Share price increase",
            "Amount of risk",
            "Short-term profit",
            "Cash flow"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Wealth maximization is a long-term goal that considers risk and timing, unlike profit maximization which focuses on short-term gains.</p>",
        "id": 3676
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Russel is thinking of starting a business in his local area by investing TK 4,00,000. He has 7/8 employees to run the business. As an honest businessman, he is thinking about obtaining a trade license and paying taxes regularly.\n\n\n\nQ: In the language of finance, what is Mr. Russel's activity called in the stem?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Investment activity",
            "Borrowing activity",
            "Financing activity",
            "Social activity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Allocating capital to start a business with the expectation of future returns is an Investment activity.</p>",
        "id": 3677
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\n\n\nQ: If Mr. Russel's business becomes profitable, what will the government receive?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
