    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Nazrul Ltd. operates a business by taking a loan of TK 50,000 at 10% interest from Moon Bank Ltd. and makes a profit of TK 10,000. Following the decision of the Board of Directors, the entire profit is distributed proportionally among the shareholders. The following year, the company faces a shortage of cash while trying to purchase raw materials.\n\nQ: Due to which principle of finance not being followed did Nazrul Ltd. face problems in purchasing raw materials?</p>",
