        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit is the difference between revenue and expense; maximizing this gap is the goal of profit maximization.</p>",
        "id": 3731
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Ariz is the financial manager of a large firm. He always tries to achieve a goal that emphasizes maximizing the gap between the firm's income and expenditure.\n\n\nQuestion: Which of the following are the limitations of the goal followed by Mr. Ariz (Profit Maximization) for not considering them?\n\ni. Risk\n\nii. Cash flow\n\niii. Timing of earning profit\n\nWhich one is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit maximization is a traditional goal that focuses only on accounting profit. It is criticized because it fails to consider the uncertainty of risk, the actual cash flow of the business, and the time value of money (timing).</p>",
        "id": 3732
    },
