            "Portfolio Principle",
            "Dividend Principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the Portfolio/Diversification principle, used to spread risk across different assets.</p>",
        "id": 3801
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The objectives of public finance are— i. Social welfare, ii. Business expansion, iii. Proper use of resources</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Government finance aims for public good and resource allocation; business expansion is a private sector goal.</p>",
        "id": 3802
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the easiest medium of exchange?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cheque",
            "Bill of Exchange",
            "Money",
            "Letter of Credit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Money (currency) is the most widely accepted and liquid medium of exchange.</p>",
        "id": 3803
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Indirect roles of finance in macroeconomic development are—\n\ni. Increasing government revenue\n\nii. Reducing cost of capital\n\niii. Coordination between deficit and surplus parties</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Finance facilitates the flow of funds from surplus units (savers) to deficit units (investors), which drives production. As businesses grow and profit, they pay more taxes, thus increasing government revenue.</p>",
        "id": 3804
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>In the case of wealth maximization, the following are considered—\n\ni. Time value of cash flow\n\nii. Qualitative aspect of net cash flow (Risk)\n\niii. Quantitative aspect of net cash flow (Amount)</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Wealth maximization is superior because it considers the total amount of cash, when it is received (TVM), and the uncertainty or risk involved (quality).</p>",
        "id": 3805
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which principle is followed to reduce risk?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Dividend Principle",
            "Liquidity & Profit",
            "Portfolio & Diversification",
            "Risk & Profit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Diversifying or creating a portfolio is the standard financial method to minimize unsystematic risk.</p>",
        "id": 3806
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is finance applicable to import and export trade called?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2017",
