        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Revenue income refers to the funds generated by the government through taxes, duties, and fees.</p>",
        "id": 3813
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The objectives of public finance are—\n\ni. Social welfare\n\nii. Business expansion\n\niii. Proper use of resources</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Public finance focuses on public good and efficient resource allocation; business expansion is typically a private sector goal.</p>",
        "id": 3814
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the primary objective of business finance?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Supplying money",
            "Reducing business risk",
            "Wealth maximization",
