        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The 1970s focused on capital asset pricing models and managing risk through portfolio diversification.</p>",
        "id": 3819
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: A production firm exports products and wants to set up a new plant outside Dhaka. This requires significant funds.\n\nQ: For financing, the firm can—\n\ni. Sell shares\n\nii. Issue debentures\n\niii. Take bank loans</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Large-scale expansion can be funded through equity (shares), long-term debt (debentures), or commercial bank loans.</p>",
        "id": 3820
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: What will be the result of the financial decision taken in the light of the stem?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Dividends will decrease",
            "Profit and risk will increase",
            "Firm will face losses",
            "Considered a loan defaulter"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Expanding into a new plant aims for higher profitability but also increases the firm's financial and operational risk.</p>",
        "id": 3821
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Business finance refers to—\n\ni. Collecting funds for business\n\nii. Using funds for a few months\n\niii. Taking decisions related to fund distribution</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Business finance covers the whole cycle of procurement (i) and allocation/distribution (iii), not just a short-term use.</p>",
        "id": 3822
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>How is public (government) finance characterized?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Exp. > Income",
            "Exp. = Income",
            "Exp. ≥ Income",
            "Exp. < Income"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Governments often follow a deficit budget policy where planned expenditure exceeds expected revenue to drive development.</p>",
        "id": 3823
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which is most important for government revenue collection?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Tax",
            "Import Duty",
            "Grants",
            "Export"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Taxes (Income tax, VAT, etc.) are the largest and most consistent source of revenue for any state.</p>",
        "id": 3824
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Pran Ltd. exports products and wants to set up a new plant outside Dhaka.\n\nQ: To finance this, the firm can—\n\ni. Issue shares\n\nii. Issue debentures\n\niii. Issue commercial papers</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Setting up a new plant is a long-term investment. Shares and debentures are long-term sources; commercial papers are short-term.</p>",
        "id": 3825
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: What will be the result of the financial decision taken?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Profit & risk will decrease",
            "Firm will face loss",
            "Profit & risk will increase",
            "Default on debt"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Expansion typically targets higher profits but simultaneously increases operational and financial risk.</p>",
        "id": 3826
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which is a subject of Macroeconomics?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
