        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Macroeconomics deals with economy-wide phenomena like total (aggregate) demand and supply.</p>",
        "id": 3827
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Under which decision does retaining profit for wealth growth fall?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Financing",
            "Investment",
            "Liquidity",
            "Dividend"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Deciding whether to pay out profits or keep them as retained earnings is a Dividend decision.</p>",
        "id": 3828
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>When paying dividends, what is considered?\n\ni. Shareholders' expectations\n\nii. Liquidity\n\niii. Amount of retained earnings</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three factors influence the payout: the need for cash (ii), the need for future growth (iii), and keeping owners happy (i).</p>",
        "id": 3829
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Investment decision is a combination of which two?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Risk & Profit",
            "Collection & Financing",
            "Working Capital & Capital Budgeting",
            "Capital Budgeting & Dividend"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Investment involves allocating funds for current operations (Working Capital) and long-term assets (Capital Budgeting).</p>",
        "id": 3830
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Max Ltd. needs 50 Lakh for a new project and plans to raise it via shares or loans. What is this called?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Financing decision",
            "Investment decision",
            "Asset management",
            "Cash management"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Determining the mix of debt and equity to raise funds is a Financing Decision.</p>",
        "id": 3831
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Offsetting a loss in one project with profit from another falls under which principle?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Liquidity",
            "Profit",
            "Diversification",
            "Risk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the core of the Portfolio/Diversification principle—balancing risks across multiple assets.</p>",
        "id": 3832
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the reason for keeping sufficient cash in hand?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Tackle liquidity crisis",
            "Future purchases",
            "Extra investment",
            "Show solvency"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Maintaining cash ensures the business can meet its immediate short-term obligations and avoid insolvency.</p>",
        "id": 3833
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Shapla Ltd. took a loan for a blanket business. It made a profit but faced a loss the next year due to a mild winter.\n\nQ: Which principle did they fail to follow?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Liquidity & Risk",
            "Portfolio Diversification",
            "Risk & Profit",
            "Time Value of Money"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>By only selling one seasonal product, they didn't diversify to protect against unexpected weather patterns.</p>",
        "id": 3834
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: Shapla Ltd.'s decisions are related to—\n\ni. Financing, ii. Investment, iii. Dividend</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Taking a loan (i), starting a business (ii), and distributing profits (iii) cover all three main functions.</p>",
        "id": 3835
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What happens to a business if too much liquidity (cash) is kept?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Profit increases",
            "Profit decreases",
            "Capital increases",
            "Capital decreases"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Idle cash earns no return; hence, excessive liquidity leads to lower overall profitability.</p>",
        "id": 3836
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The objectives of portfolio investment are—\n\ni. Increase profit\n\nii. Reduce risk\n\niii. Control market</p>",
        "meta": "Bogra · -",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Portfolio investment aims to optimize returns while minimizing unsystematic risk. Market control is not a financial objective of a portfolio.</p>",
        "id": 3837
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the principle called where a loss in one project is offset by the profit of another?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Profit principle",
            "Risk principle",
            "Diversification principle",
            "Liquidity principle"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the core of the Portfolio or Diversification principle. Spreading investments ensures that the total capital is protected if one sector fails.</p>",
        "id": 3838
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Retaining profit for wealth growth is part of which financial function?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Investment",
            "Dividend distribution",
            "Asset management",
            "Preservation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Determining how much profit to distribute as dividends versus how much to retain for reinvestment is a Dividend Decision.</p>",
        "id": 3839
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Limitations of Profit Maximization include—\n\ni. Ignores timing of profit\n\nii. Ignores cash flow\n\niii. Ignores expenses</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit maximization is criticized because it does not consider the Time Value of Money (when profit is earned) or the actual Cash Flow available.</p>",
        "id": 3840
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>As a social responsibility, financial management performs—\n\ni. Quality product production\n\nii. Creating a safe workplace\n\niii. Providing low wages</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Social responsibility includes being fair to consumers and employees. Providing \"low wages\" is a failure of social responsibility.</p>",
        "id": 3841
    }], shortCQData: [], fullCQData: [] },
