        "text": "What do you mean by Non-Bank Financial Institutions (NBFIs)?",
        "answer": "1. NBFIs are financial institutions that provide banking-like services (such as loans or insurance) but do not hold a full banking license or accept traditional demand deposits.\n\n2. Examples in Bangladesh include IDLC Finance and IPDC, which focus on specialized lending and investment.",
        "meta": "Notre Dame College · 2026",
        "type": "college"
    },
    {
