    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch2-short-b-021",
        "text": "What is Money Laundering? Explain.",
        "answer": "1. Money laundering is the illegal process of concealing the origins of money obtained through criminal activities to make it appear legitimate.\n\n2. It typically involves three stages: placement, layering, and integration to bypass the legal financial system.",
        "meta": "Adamjee Cantonment College · 2026",
