    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch2-short-b-022",
        "text": "Why are Treasury Bills issued? Explain.",
        "answer": "1. Treasury bills are issued by the government to meet short-term budget deficits and manage liquidity in the economy.\n\n2. They also serve as a tool for the central bank to control the money supply through open market operations.",
