                "answer": "1. Maturity: The money market deals with short-term instruments (up to 1 year), while the capital market deals with long-term instruments (above 1 year).\n\n2. Risk: Money market instruments carry lower risk and liquidity, whereas capital market instruments carry higher risk and potential for long-term growth."
