        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>EIR measures the true annual interest rate by accounting for the frequency of compounding (m) within a year.</p>",
        "id": 3938
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The discounting method—i. Is related to Present Valueii. Is the opposite of compoundingiii. Is a process to determine the amount of discount</p>",
