            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Discounting finds the Present Value (<code>PV</code>) by reversing compounding (<code>FV</code>). It determines the value, not just a \"discount amount.\"</p>",
        "id": 3939
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Rakib needs TK 5,00,000 after 5 years for a project. He wants to deposit money at 9% interest for 5 years.Q: How much must Mr. Rakib deposit now?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,01,406 Tk",
            "3,12,972 Tk",
            "3,24,966 Tk",
            "3,30,338 Tk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Using <code>PV</code>=(1+i)n<code>FV</code>​:<code>PV</code>=(1+0.09)5500,000​=324,965.7</p>",
        "id": 3940
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)Q: If the interest rate is 10%, how much must Mr. Rakib deposit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2025",
