    {
        "text": "<p>Stimulus:Mr. 'M' wants to deposit 10,000 Taka in a fixed deposit account at a bank. 'P Bank' offers to pay him 20,000 Taka in 4 years for that amount.Question: If 'P Bank' provides bi-monthly compounding (every two months) interest—i. It will take more than 4 years to get 20,000 Taka.ii. It will take less than 4 years to get 20,000 Taka.iii. The number of compounding periods in a year ($m$) will be 6.</p>",
