            "If the number of compounding periods is $365$ (Daily)"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>The more frequent the compounding ($m$), the higher the EAR. Daily ($365$) is highest here.</p>",
        "id": 4050
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>In finance, Discounting means—\n\ni. A discount rate\n\nii. Technique for <code>PV</code>\n\niii. Opposite of Compounding</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>(Repeat of Q19/88) Discounting covers all three aspects.</p>",
        "id": 4051
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Emel invests TK 5,00,000 in Janata Bank for 12 years at 9% interest.\n\nQ: According to Rule 72, in how many years will it double?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6 years",
            "7.2 years",
            "8 years",
            "9 years"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$n = 72 \\div 9 = 8$ years.</p>",
        "id": 4052
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: If the bank gives quarterly interest, what is the EIR?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2.25%",
            "3%",
            "9.27%",
            "9.31%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$EIR = (1 + \\frac{0.09}{4})^4 - 1 = (1.0225)^4 - 1 \\approx 9.31\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 4053
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Why is there a difference between the value of money today and in the future?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest + Principal",
            "Capital Cost",
            "Interest Rate",
            "Compounding"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Interest Rate is the price of time; it is the fundamental reason for the value difference.</p>",
        "id": 4054
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which factor is adjusted to determine the Effective Interest Rate?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "No. of compounding periods",
            "Tenure",
            "Inflation",
            "Depreciation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>(Repeat of Q2/Q8) $m$ is the variable adjusted in the EIR formula.</p>",
        "id": 4055
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is it called if equal money is deposited or withdrawn every year?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Annual Annuity",
            "Compounding",
            "Present Value",
            "Future Value"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The general term for a series of equal payments is an Annuity.</p>",
        "id": 4056
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Shamim lent TK 50,000 to his friend Mr. Bashar for 5 years at 12% compound interest.\n\nQ: How much will Mr. Bashar pay after 5 years?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "56,000 Tk",
            "62,720 Tk",
            "78,676 Tk",
            "88,117 Tk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p><code>FV</code> = 50,000(1.12)^5 = 88,117.08$.</p>",
        "id": 4057
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: If interest is calculated twice a year (semi-annually), what is the total amount at the end?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "87,500 Tk",
            "88,542 Tk",
            "89,500 Tk",
            "89,542 Tk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p><code>FV</code> = 50,000(1 + \\frac{0.12}{2})^{2 \\times 5} = 50,000(1.06)^{10} = 89,542.38$.</p>",
        "id": 4058
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If Mr. Arif wants to receive TK 2,000 every month forever at 11% bank interest, how much must he deposit now?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "18,181.81",
            "72,727.27",
            "1,09,090.90",
            "2,18,181.81"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Monthly Perpetuity: <code>PV</code> = \\frac{\\text{Monthly Amount}}{\\frac{i}{12}} = \\frac{2,000}{0.11/12} = \\frac{2,000}{0.00916} = 2,18,181.81$.</p>",
        "id": 4059
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is used to determine in how much time an investment will double?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Rule 72",
            "Rule 69",
            "Annuity",
            "Perpetuity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Rule 72 is the most common standard for doubling time. (Note: Rule 69 is also used, but 72 is the primary choice in general contexts).</p>",
        "id": 4060
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Imran took a TK 1,00,000 loan at 8% for 4 years. He pays installments at the beginning of each year.\n\nQ: How much interest is paid in the 1st installment?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2022",
