        "id": 4068
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Compounding is involved in determining which of the following?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cash Flow",
            "Future Value",
            "Present Value",
            "Simple Interest"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Compounding = finding <code>FV</code>.</p>",
        "id": 4069
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>For which frequency will the Future Value be the highest?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Monthly",
            "Quarterly",
            "Semi-annual",
            "Annual"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Higher frequency ($m=12$) leads to more interest-on-interest, thus highest <code>FV</code>.</p>",
        "id": 4070
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>In the case of Compound Interest—\n\ni. Interest is calculated on the principal plus interest (total amount).\nii. Interest is calculated only on the principal amount.\niii. Interest from the previous year is treated as principal.</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Statement i is correct: This is the core definition of compounding. You earn interest on the \"Interest-Total\" ($A = P + I$), not just the original sum.Statement ii is incorrect: This describes Simple Interest. In compound interest, the base amount changes every period.Statement iii is correct: In each new period, the interest earned in the previous period is added to the principal to form the \"new principal\" for the next calculation.Summary for your preparation:To distinguish these easily for the exam:Simple Interest: $I = Pnr$ (Interest is always based on the initial $P$).Compound Interest: $CI = P(1+i)^n - P$ (Interest grows because the base increases every year).</p>",
        "id": 4071
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Ripon took a loan of TK 15,00,000 at 8% for 10 years.\n\nQ: How much must he pay in total at the end? (Compounded)</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "28,38,387 Tk",
            "50,38,387 Tk",
            "32,38,387 Tk",
            "34,38,387 Tk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p><code>FV</code> = 1,500,000(1.08)^{10} = 3,238,387$.</p>",
        "id": 4072
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: How much extra money must Mr. Ripon pay as interest?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "14,38,387 Tk",
            "15,38,387 Tk",
            "16,38,387 Tk",
            "17,38,387 Tk"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest $= <code>FV</code> - <code>PV</code> = 32,38,387 - 15,00,000 = 17,38,387$.</p>",
        "id": 4073
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>For a single cash flow, the Present Value (<code>PV</code>) will increase if—</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "m increases",
