            "Simple Int.",
            "Nominal Int."
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The standard definition of compound interest.</p>",
        "id": 4075
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Characteristics of an Annuity are—\n\ni. Equal cash flows\n\nii. Equal time intervals\n\niii. Specific time period</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>An annuity must be equal payments, regular intervals, for a fixed number of years.</p>",
        "id": 4076
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>In the case of Simple Interest—</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Higher interest earned",
            "Interest grows every year",
            "Interest on Int+Principal",
            "Calculated on Principal"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Simple interest is always calculated only on the original amount (principal).</p>",
        "id": 4077
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Taher is a farmer. He wants to lease land for 5 years. Owner's terms: Lump sum TK 2,00,000 OR TK 25,000 in 1st year, decreasing by TK 2,000 each following year.\n\nQ: What type of cash flow is Taher's proposal?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2022",
