        "id": 4087
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is provided in a Loan Amortization Schedule?\n\ni. Installment amount\n\nii. Interest amount\n\niii. Principal amount</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>It shows the breakdown of each payment into its core components.</p>",
        "id": 4088
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>According to the 'Rule of 72'—\n\ni. Multiplying by the term (years) gives the interest rate.\nii. Dividing by the term (years) gives the interest rate.\niii. Dividing by the interest rate gives the term (years).</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>The Rule of 72 is a quick way to estimate how long it will take for an investment to double in value at a fixed annual rate of interest.To find the Interest Rate ($i$): Divide 72 by the number of years ($n$).$$\\text{Interest Rate} \\approx \\frac{72}{n}$$(This confirms statement ii).To find the Term/Years ($n$): Divide 72 by the interest rate ($i$).$$\\text{Number of Years} \\approx \\frac{72}{i}$$(This confirms statement iii).Why statement i is incorrect:Multiplying the term by another number doesn't provide the interest rate in this specific rule; it is strictly a division-based shortcut.Quick Exam Tip:If a question says an investment doubles in 8 years, the interest rate is $72 \\div 8 = 9\\%$.If the interest rate is 12%, the investment will double in $72 \\div 12 = 6$ years.</p>",
        "id": 4089
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Compounding process is used for which of the following?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Present Value",
            "Future Value",
            "Growth",
            "Inflation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Compounding is the engine that drives Future Value.</p>",
        "id": 4090
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If the frequency of compounding ($m$) increases, which value increases?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Present Value",
            "Future Value",
            "Annual Annuity",
            "Depreciation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>More compounding cycles = more interest-on-interest = higher <code>FV</code>.</p>",
        "id": 4091
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which is the formula for Effective Interest Rate (EIR)?</p>",
        "meta": "Mymensingh · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "$EIR = (1 + i)^n - 1$",
            "$EIR = (1 + \\frac{i}{m})^m - 1$",
            "$EIR = (1 + \\frac{i}{m})^{mn} - 1$",
            "$EIR = (1 + \\frac{i}{m})^n - 1$"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The formula uses the interest rate ($i$) and the frequency per year ($m$).</p>",
        "id": 4092
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the current value of money to be received in the future called?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Present Value",
            "Future Value",
            "Annuity",
            "Perpetuity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the basic definition of Present Value.</p>",
        "id": 4093
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which interest is paid on the Interest + Principal amount?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2021",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Simple Interest",
            "Net Interest",
            "Compound Interest",
            "Total Interest"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Compound interest is the only one that \"stacks\" interest on previous interest.</p>",
        "id": 4094
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the process of determining Present Value called?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2021",
