    {
        "text": "<p>What is the formula for <code>FV</code> (Lump Sum) with annual compounding?</p>",
        "meta": "Ctg · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "$FV = PV(1 + \\frac{r}{m})^{nm}$",
            "$FV = PV(1 + r)^n$",
            "$PV = FV(1 + r)^n$",
            "$PV = FV(1 + \\frac{r}{m})^{nm}$"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>When interest compounds only once per year, you do not need to divide the rate by $m$ or multiply the years by $m$. Options (c) and (d) are actually structures used for calculating Present Value, not Future Value. Option (a) is the formula for multiple compounding periods per year (like monthly or quarterly).</p>",
        "id": 4176
    },
