        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Forever/Infinite flow is the definition of Perpetuity (চিরস্থায়ী বৃত্তি).</p>",
        "id": 4217
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>At which interest rate will the Present Value (<code>PV</code>) be the lowest?</p>",
        "meta": "Ctg · 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Quarterly",
            "Bi-monthly",
            "Weekly",
            "Monthly"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Higher compounding frequency ($m$) leads to a lower Present Value. Weekly ($m=52$) is the highest here.</p>",
        "id": 4218
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>For mixed cash flows occurring at the start of each year, what will the value of $n$ be for the 1st year's <code>FV</code>?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Equal to total term",
            "Less than total term",
            "More than total term",
            "Zero"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>If paid at the start, the 1st installment earns interest for the entire duration (e.g., in a 5-year project, it earns interest for 5 years).</p>",
        "id": 4219
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>For a single cash flow, the Present Value (<code>PV</code>) will increase if:</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Compounding ($m$) increases",
            "Future Value decreases",
            "Interest rate decreases",
            "Time ($n$) increases"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p><code>PV</code> is inversely related to interest. If the rate drops, the value today increases.</p>",
        "id": 4220
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Present and Future value will be equal—\n\ni. If tenure is zero\n\nii. If interest rate is zero\n\niii. If annual compounding is one</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Without time or interest, value remains constant. Option (iii) is wrong because annual compounding still adds interest.</p>",
        "id": 4221
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the current value of money to be received in the future called?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2016",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Liquidity",
            "Present Value",
            "Interest Rate",
            "Perpetuity"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard definition of Present Value (<code>PV</code>).</p>",
        "id": 4222
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The Discounting method is—\n\ni. Related to Present Value\n\nii. Opposite of Compounding\n\niii. Process of determining the discount amount</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Discounting pulls <code>FV</code> back to <code>PV</code> (i), reverses compounding (ii), and uses the discount rate to find the reduction (iii).</p>",
        "id": 4223
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>(Duplicate Question in Board Archive)</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Same as above.</p>",
        "id": 4224
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Azim wants to buy a TK 1,00,000 computer in 5 years. Bank A offers 8% annual interest. Bank B offers 8% semi-annual interest.\n\nQ: The method to find the required deposit is:</p>",
        "meta": "Combined · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Discounting",
            "Compounding",
            "Growth",
            "Transfer"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Finding \"how much to deposit now\" for a future goal is Discounting.</p>",
        "id": 4225
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: (Same as above)\n\nQ: Which of the following is correct for Mr. Azim?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Janata (Annual) deposit is higher",
            "Pubali (Semi-annual) deposit is higher",
