        "explanation": "<p>Bank B compounds more ($m=2$), so it grows faster. Therefore, you need to deposit less in Bank B and more in Bank A to reach 1 Lakh.</p>",
        "id": 4226
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Selim deposits TK 5,000 at 12% simple interest for 5 years.\n\nQ: What is the total amount (Principal + Interest) he will receive?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "7,000",
