        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Installment = Principal Part + Interest Part. (ii) is incorrect as one installment doesn't hold the total loan interest.</p>",
        "id": 4236
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Arif buys a 3 Lakh motor bike. He takes a 5-year loan for half (1.5 Lakh) at 9%.\n\nQ: If paid at the start, what is the 1st year's principal repayment?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "33,579",
            "35,379",
            "37,593",
            "34,769"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>After calculating the Annuity Due (<code>PV</code>A_{due}$) installment, the first year's principal is derived by subtracting interest.</p>",
        "id": 4237
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>When is the Effective Annual Rate (EAR) equal to the Nominal Rate?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal · 2015",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "If $m=2$",
            "If $i=1\\%$",
            "If $i=0\\%$",
            "If $m=1$"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>When interest is compounded only once a year, the effective and nominal rates are identical.</p>",
        "id": 4238
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>To determine Future Value (<code>FV</code>), you need:\n\ni. Number of years\n\nii. Interest rate\n\niii. Present value</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p><code>FV</code> = <code>PV</code>(1+i)^n$ requires all three variables.</p>",
        "id": 4239
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Stem: Mr. Haider (age 50) decides to save TK 6,000 annually at 10% compound interest.\n\nQ: How much will he have at age 60 (after 10 years)?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
