        "explanation": "<p>Ordinary Annuity (সাধারণ বার্ষিক বৃত্তি) is paid at the end.</p>",
        "id": 4241
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Abul deposits TK 50,000 at the start of each year for 5 years at 7% interest. Total at the end?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,07,664",
            "3,06,678",
            "3,05,678",
            "3,04,678"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p><code>FV</code>A_{due} = 50,000 \\times [ \\frac{(1.07)^5 - 1}{0.07} ] \\times 1.07 = 3,07,664.5$.</p>",
        "id": 4242
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is obtained by subtracting the Present Value (<code>PV</code>) from the Future Value (<code>FV</code>) of a lump sum?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Interest",
            "Principal",
            "Total Amount",
            "Net Capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The growth in value (<code>FV</code> - <code>PV</code>) represents the Interest earned.</p>",
        "id": 4243
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>EAR is higher than the Nominal Rate because—\n\ni. Interest is calculated periodically\n\nii. Interest is calculated on initial deposit\n\niii. Interest is calculated on the total (Principal+Interest)</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Compounding (interest on interest) drives the EAR higher than the stated nominal rate.</p>",
        "id": 4244
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If the Nominal Rate is 12%, what is the periodic rate for monthly compounding?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1%",
            "12%",
            "4%",
            "3%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Periodic Rate $= 12\\% \\div 12 = 1\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 4245
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>In how many years will an amount triple at 12% interest rate?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "6.96",
            "9.69",
            "10.23",
            "6"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Using the log formula: $n = \\log(3) \\div \\log(1.12) \\approx 9.69$.</p>",
        "id": 4246
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Azam pays TK 13,310 for a TK 10,000 loan after 3 years. What is the annual compound rate?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10%",
            "12%",
            "13%",
            "9%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>$10,000(1+i)^3 = 13,310$ leads to $i = 0.10$ or $10\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 4247
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the contractual annual interest rate between lender and borrower called?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Nominal Rate",
            "Effective Rate",
            "Simple Rate",
            "Compound Rate"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>The stated/contractual rate is the Nominal Interest Rate.</p>",
        "id": 4248
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If the rate is 12.67% and compounding is monthly, what is the EAR?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore · 2014",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "12.67%",
            "13.43%",
            "14.43%",
            "14.67%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$EAR = (1 + 0.1267/12)^{12} - 1 \\approx 13.43\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 4249
    }], shortCQData: [], fullCQData: [] },
        "4": { subjectName: "Finance 1st Paper", chapterName: "Chapter 4 : Financial Analysis", mcqData: [{
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a current asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Retained Earnings",
            "Accounts Receivable",
            "Accounts Payable",
            "Prepaid Expenses"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current assets are resources expected to be converted to cash within one year. Accounts Receivable is the primary answer.</p>",
        "id": 4250
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What occurs at the Break-Even Point (BEP)?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Profit Maximization",
            "Sales Maximization",
            "Cost Maximization",
            "Income and expenses are equal"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>At the BEP, Total Revenue (TR) equals Total Cost (TC), resulting in zero profit or loss.</p>",
        "id": 4251
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If unit variable cost is 120, selling price is 200, and total fixed cost is 1,20,000, what is the BEP in units?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "375",
            "600",
            "1,000",
            "1,500"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{1,20,000}{200 - 120} = 1,500$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4252
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Old furniture cost 20,000 with 12,000 accumulated depreciation. If sold for 11,000, what is the gain or loss?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "3,000",
            "11,000",
            "12,000",
            "20,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Book Value = $$20,000 - 12,000 = 8,000$$. Gain = $$11,000 - 8,000 = 3,000$$.</p>",
        "id": 4253
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Financing activities include: (i) Buying furniture (ii) Issuing shares (iii) Dividend payment. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Furniture purchase is an Investing activity. Issuing shares and dividends are Financing activities.</p>",
        "id": 4254
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The level of sales where no profit or loss occurs is called?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Contribution Ratio",
            "Margin of Safety",
            "Break-Even Point",
            "Total Cost Ratio"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>This is the fundamental definition of the Break-Even Point.</p>",
        "id": 4255
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a current asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Outstanding Expenses",
            "Accounts Receivable",
            "Accounts Payable"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Bank Overdraft and Outstanding Expenses are current liabilities.</p>",
        "id": 4256
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Saju's toy factory: Price 120, variable cost 100, and fixed cost 20,000. What is the Break-Even Point?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "167 units",
            "200 units",
            "500 units",
            "1,000 units"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{20,000}{120 - 100} = 1,000$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4257
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Saju's toy factory: Price 120, variable cost 100, and fixed cost 20,000. To earn 5,000 profit, how many units must be sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "750 units",
            "1,000 units",
            "1,250 units",
            "1,500 units"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$\\frac{20,000 + 5,000}{120 - 100} = 1,250$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4258
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is included in operating activities?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Depreciation",
            "Issuing Shares",
            "Repayment of Debt",
            "Dividend Payment"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Depreciation is a non-cash adjustment used in the indirect method of operating cash flows.</p>",
        "id": 4259
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>A firm's cash flow includes: (i) Operating (ii) Financing (iii) Investing. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are standard components of a Cash Flow Statement.</p>",
        "id": 4260
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an example of cash outflow?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Annual Annuity",
            "Tax Refund",
            "Royalty Receipt",
            "Cash Payment of Tax"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Paying tax in cash reduces the cash balance, representing an outflow.</p>",
        "id": 4261
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Tanzim is a businessman. To get an idea of the possible sales of his organization in 2019, he asked the salesperson for the sales records of the last few years. Year,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018\nSales (BDT),\"1,50,000\",\"1,55,000\",\"1,60,000\",\"1,62,000\",\"1,60,035*\" Which type of financial analysis is represented by Mr. Tanzim's activity in the stimulus?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4.95%",
            "4.80%",
            "7.01%",
            "6.69%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Note: Specific sales figures for calculation were not provided in source text.</p>",
        "id": 4262
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>\"Mr. Tanzim is a businessman. To get an idea of the possible sales of his organization in 2019, he asked the salesperson for the sales records of the last few years. Year,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018\nSales (BDT),\"\"1,50,000\"\",\"\"1,55,000\"\",\"\"1,60,000\"\",\"\"1,62,000\"\",\"\"1,60,035*\"\" Which type of financial analysis is represented by Mr. Tanzim's activity in the stimulus?\"</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Ratio",
            "Horizontal",
            "Vertical",
            "Gross Profit"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Comparing financial figures over multiple time periods is Horizontal analysis.</p>",
        "id": 4263
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Working capital is required for: (i) Buying raw materials (ii) Paying wages (iii) Paying rent. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Working capital covers all day-to-day operational expenses.</p>",
        "id": 4264
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>PQS Ltd: Import price 80, sell price 100, annual fixed cost 1,00,000. At what volume will income and expenses be equal?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,000",
            "556",
            "1,250",
            "5,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{1,00,000}{100 - 80} = 5,000$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4265
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>PQS Ltd: Import price 80, sell price 100, fixed cost 1,00,000. Ways to reach BEP faster: (i) Reduce fixed cost (ii) Reduce price (iii) Reduce variable cost.</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Reducing costs lowers BEP; reducing price increases the number of units needed.</p>",
        "id": 4266
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the difference between total sales and total variable cost?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Contribution Margin",
            "Margin of Safety",
            "Profit Margin",
            "Total Margin"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Contribution Margin = Sales - Variable Costs.</p>",
        "id": 4267
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The distance between actual sales and the break-even point is called?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Margin of Safety",
            "Income Distance",
            "Cost Distance",
            "Surplus Distance"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Margin of Safety is the cushion a business has above its BEP.</p>",
        "id": 4268
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Palash Ltd: Selling price 90, unit variable cost 50, fixed cost 1,80,000. What is the break-even sales in units?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000",
            "3,600",
            "4,500",
            "6,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{1,80,000}{90 - 50} = 4,500$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4269
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Palash Ltd. produces toys. Sales price is 90, variable cost (material/labor) is 50, and fixed cost is 1,80,000. How many units must be sold to earn a profit of 1,20,000?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "7,500",
            "8,000",
            "8,500",
            "9,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Units = \\frac{Fixed Cost + Target Profit}{Unit Contribution} = \\frac{1,80,000 + 1,20,000}{90 - 50} = \\frac{3,00,000}{40} = 7,500$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4270
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a current asset?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Machinery",
            "Cash",
            "Furniture",
            "Shares"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash is the most liquid current asset. Machinery and Furniture are fixed assets.</p>",
        "id": 4271
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>How many methods are there to prepare a Cash Flow Statement?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1",
            "2",
            "3",
            "4"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>There are two methods: the Direct Method and the Indirect Method.</p>",
        "id": 4272
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is an operating cash inflow?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Cash sale of machinery",
            "Cash sale of products",
            "Cash sale of shares",
            "Depreciation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Sale of products is a core business operation. Sale of machinery is investing; sale of shares is financing.</p>",
        "id": 4273
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Nuha Ltd. sells 10,000 pens. Sales price is 12, variable cost is 8, and fixed cost is 24,000. At what volume will profit be zero?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2,000",
            "3,000",
            "6,000",
            "10,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Profit is zero at BEP. $$BEP = \\frac{24,000}{12 - 8} = 6,000$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4274
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Nuha Ltd. sells 10,000 pens. Sales price is 12, variable cost is 8, and fixed cost is 24,000. What is the annual profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "16,000",
            "24,000",
            "40,000",
            "64,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Profit = (Sales \\t\t\times Contribution) - Fixed Cost = (10,000 \\t\t\times 4) - 24,000 = 16,000$$.</p>",
        "id": 4275
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Characteristics of Variable Cost: (i) Changes with production/sales (ii) Total cost changes (iii) Unit variable cost remains constant. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are defining traits of variable costs in a relevant range.</p>",
        "id": 4276
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the ideal standard for the Quick Ratio (Liquidity)?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined Board · 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1:2",
            "1:1",
            "2:1",
            "1:3"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The standard ideal Quick/Liquid ratio is 1:1.</p>",
        "id": 4277
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>An organization has annual sales of 10,00,000, fixed cost 2,50,000, and variable cost 6,50,000. What is the net profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined Board · 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "80,000",
            "1,00,000",
            "1,20,000",
            "1,40,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Profit = 10,00,000 - (6,50,000 + 2,50,000) = 1,00,000$$.</p>",
        "id": 4278
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Safin's factory sells bats at 70 each. Unit variable cost is 40 and annual fixed cost is 40,000. What is the profit if 2,000 units are sold?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined Board · 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "8,000",
            "12,000",
            "16,000",
            "20,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Profit = [2,000 \\t\t\times (70 - 40)] - 40,000 = 60,000 - 40,000 = 20,000$$.</p>",
        "id": 4279
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Safin's factory sells bats at 70 each. Unit variable cost is 40 and annual fixed cost is 40,000. How many units must be sold to earn 14,000 profit?</p>",
        "meta": "Combined Board · 2018",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1,200",
            "1,800",
            "2,000",
            "2,400"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Units = \\frac{40,000 + 14,000}{70 - 40} = \\frac{54,000}{30} = 1,800$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4280
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a variable cost?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Employee salary",
            "Purchase of raw materials",
            "Office rent",
            "Depreciation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Raw material cost varies directly with the volume of production.</p>",
        "id": 4281
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Subtracting Interest and Tax from EBIT (Earnings Before Interest and Tax) yields:</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Net Profit",
            "Average Profit",
            "Interim Profit",
            "Cash Inflow"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>EBIT minus Interest equals <code>EBT</code>; <code>EBT</code> minus Tax equals Net Income (Profit).</p>",
        "id": 4282
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>ABC Co: 20,000 units sold, price 50, variable cost 30, fixed cost 2,00,000. What is the Margin of Safety in Taka?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4,00,000",
            "5,00,000",
            "6,00,000",
            "7,00,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP (units) = \\frac{2,00,000}{20} = 10,000$$. $$MoS (units) = 20,000 - 10,000 = 10,000$$. $$MoS (Taka) = 10,000 \\t\t\times 50 = 5,00,000$$.</p>",
        "id": 4283
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>ABC Co: 20,000 units sold, price 50, variable cost 30, fixed cost 2,00,000. What is the BEP in units?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "10,000",
            "11,000",
            "12,000",
            "13,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{2,00,000}{50 - 30} = 10,000$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4284
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a current liability?</p>",
        "meta": "Dhaka Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Accounts Receivable",
            "Bills Payable",
            "Inventory",
            "Prepaid Expenses"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Bills Payable is a short-term obligation. Others are current assets.</p>",
        "id": 4285
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Receiving cash from the sale of plant/machinery is which type of activity?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Operating",
            "Investing",
            "Financing",
            "Non-cash"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Activities related to long-term assets are classified as Investing Activities.</p>",
        "id": 4286
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Alpha Chemicals has fixed costs of 1,00,000. Capacity is 20,000 units, but it produces 10,000 units. Unit variable cost is 10. What is the unit fixed cost at 10,000 units?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "5",
            "10",
            "15",
            "20"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Unit Fixed Cost = \\frac{Total Fixed Cost}{Actual Units} = \\frac{1,00,000}{10,000} = 10$$.</p>",
        "id": 4287
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Alpha Chemicals has fixed costs of 1,00,000. Capacity is 20,000 units. Unit variable cost is 10. If 20,000 units are produced, what is the total cost per unit?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "20",
            "15",
            "10",
            "5"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Total Unit Cost = \\frac{1,00,000}{20,000} + 10 = 5 + 10 = 15$$.</p>",
        "id": 4288
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Features of financial statements: (i) Expressible in numbers (ii) Geometric comparison possible (iii) Expressible in money. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Financial statements must be quantitative and expressed in a monetary unit. \"Geometric comparison\" is not a standard core feature.</p>",
        "id": 4289
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Zaman produces 1,000 units. Variable cost is 5,000, fixed cost is 4,000, and total sales are 10,000. What is the Break-Even Point (BEP) in Taka?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "700 TK",
            "800 Units",
            "850 TK",
            "8,000 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Unit Price = 10, Variable Cost/Unit = 5. $$BEP (Units) = \\frac{4,000}{10 - 5} = 800$$. $$BEP (Taka) = 800 \\t\t\times 10 = 8,000$$. (Note: Option D should be 8,000 based on logic).</p>",
        "id": 4290
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Zaman produces 1,000 units. Variable cost is 5,000, fixed cost is 4,000, and total sales are 10,000. What is the Margin of Safety in units?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "100",
            "200",
            "300",
            "400"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Actual Sales (1,000) - BEP Sales (800) = 200$$ units.</p>",
        "id": 4291
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>A Cash Flow Statement is prepared using: (i) Income Statement (ii) Retained Earnings Statement (iii) Comparative Balance Sheet. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard preparation requires the Income Statement and Comparative Balance Sheets.</p>",
        "id": 4292
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Miss Swarna's chip factory has weekly sales of 1,25,000 packets. Variable cost per packet is 16, selling price 30, and fixed cost 5,60,000. What is the BEP in packets?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "34,000",
            "36,000",
            "38,000",
            "40,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$BEP = \\frac{5,60,000}{30 - 16} = \\frac{5,60,000}{14} = 40,000$$ packets.</p>",
        "id": 4293
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Miss Swarna's chip factory: Sales 1,25,000 packets, VC 16, Price 30, Fixed Cost 5,60,000. What is the Margin of Safety Ratio?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
