        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$MoS Ratio = \\frac{1,25,000 - 40,000}{1,25,000} = \\frac{85,000}{1,25,000} = 68\\%$$.</p>",
        "id": 4294
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which party measures distributable cash flow through \"Free Cash Flow\"?</p>",
