            "Accounts Payable",
            "Prepaid Insurance",
            "Outstanding Salary",
            "Unearned Service Revenue"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Prepaid expenses are current assets. Others listed are current liabilities.</p>",
        "id": 4319
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a Quick (Acid-Test) Asset?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Inventory",
            "Bank Balance",
            "Bank Overdraft",
            "Prepaid Expenses"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Quick assets = Current Assets - (Inventory + Prepaid Expenses). Bank balance is highly liquid.</p>",
        "id": 4320
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>On 31st Dec: Accounts Receivable 40k, Cash 30k, Bills Receivable 30k, Inventory 20k, Creditors 35k, Bills Payable 25k. What is the Total Current Assets?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "1,80,000",
            "1,55,000",
            "1,20,000",
            "1,45,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Assets = $$40,000 + 30,000 + 30,000 + 20,000 = 1,20,000$$ TK.</p>",
        "id": 4321
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>On 31st Dec: AR 40k, Cash 30k, BR 30k, Inventory 20k, Creditors 35k, Bills Payable 25k. What is the Current Ratio?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "2:3",
            "2:1",
            "2.5:1",
            "3:1"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Current Assets (120k) / Current Liabilities (35k + 25k = 60k) = $$1,20,000 / 60,000 = 2:1$$.</p>",
        "id": 4322
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the most significant component of current assets in terms of liquidity?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Bank Balance",
            "Debtors",
            "Machinery",
            "Cash"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash is the most liquid asset and the core component of current assets.</p>",
        "id": 4323
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Current assets of a business include: (i) Cash (ii) Bank Deposit (iii) Bills Receivable. Which is correct?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
