        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>Cash entering the business is called an Inflow; cash leaving is an Outflow.</p>",
        "id": 4329
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What happens in terms of cash flow when Debtors (Accounts Receivable) increase?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
