        "meta": "Cantonment College, Jessore · 2026",
        "type": "college"
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-short-b-032",
        "text": "Why is maintaining working capital at an optimal level a responsibility of a financial manager?",
        "answer": "1. Excessive working capital ties up funds unproductively, while insufficient working capital leads to liquidity crises.\n\n2. An optimal level ensures operational efficiency and maximum profitability.",
        "meta": "Cantonment College, Jessore · 2026",
        "type": "college"
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-short-a-033",
        "text": "What is mid-term financing?",
        "answer": "Mid-term financing refers to the sourcing of funds for a period usually ranging from one to five years.",
        "meta": "Cantonment Public School & College, Mymensingh · 2026",
        "type": "college"
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-short-b-033",
        "text": "What do you mean by re-order level?",
