            },
            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the EOQ for Sigma Company.",
                "answer": "1. Data: $A = 6,000 \\times 12 = 72,000; O = 100; C = 2$.\n\n2. Formula: $EOQ = \\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\times A \\times O}{C}}$.\n\n3. Calculation: $\\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\times 72,000 \\times 100}{2}} =$ 2,683 units."
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "Evaluate the current status of both companies based on total inventory cost.",
                "answer": "1. Sigma Total Cost: $(\\frac{72,000}{2683} \\times 100) + (\\frac{2683}{2} \\times 2) = 2,683 + 2,683 =$ TK 5,366.\n\n2. Beta EOQ: $\\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\times 50,000 \\times 80}{3}} = 1,633$ units.\n\n3. Beta Total Cost: $(\\frac{50,000}{1633} \\times 80) + (\\frac{1633}{2} \\times 3) = 2,450 + 2,450 =$ TK 4,900.\n\n4. Conclusion: Beta Co. is in a better position as its total inventory cost is lower than Sigma Co."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-cq-030",
        "stem": "Alam Ltd. purchased goods worth TK 10,00,000 from Bogra Shari Ghar under terms 2/15, net 60. The manager decided to take a bank loan at 18% to take the discount. Later, the supplier extended the payment period by 10 days.",
        "meta": "Govt. Azizul Haque College, Bogra · 2026",
        "type": "college",
        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is commercial paper?",
