            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the cost of trade credit for Alam Ltd.",
                "answer": "1. Data: $CD = 2\\%; CP = 60; DP = 15$.\n\n2. Formula: $Ktc = \\frac{CD}{100 - CD} \\times \\frac{360}{CP - DP} \\times 100$.\n\n3. Calculation: $\\frac{2}{98} \\times \\frac{360}{45} \\times 100 =$ 16.33%."
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "How will the change in payment time affect Alam Ltd.'s loan decision?",
                "answer": "1. Initial Cost: 16.33%. Bank Loan: 18%. (Bank loan was initially a bad decision as $18\\% > 16.33\\%$).\n\n2. New CP: $60 + 10 = 70$ days.\n\n3. New Ktc: $\\frac{2}{98} \\times \\frac{360}{70 - 15} \\times 100 =$ 13.36%.\n\n4. Conclusion: The extension reduces the cost of trade credit further. The manager should definitely avoid the bank loan and stick with the trade credit."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-cq-031",
        "stem": "Mr. Sojib can take trade credit under terms 2/25, net 45, or issue 120-day commercial paper. Each commercial paper has a face value of TK 100 and a selling price of TK 95.",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Govt. College · 2026",
        "type": "college",
        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is short-term financing?",
