            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the cost of the commercial paper.",
                "answer": "1. Data: $FV = 100$; $SV = 95$; $MP = 120$.\n\n2. Formula: $Kcp = \\frac{FV - SV}{SV} \\times \\frac{360}{MP} \\times 100$.\n\n3. Calculation: $\\frac{100 - 95}{95} \\times \\frac{360}{120} \\times 100 =$ 15.79%."
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "Which one should Mr. Sojib accept: trade credit or commercial paper? Comment.",
                "answer": "1. CP Cost: 15.79% (from C).\n\n2. Trade Credit Cost: $CD = 2\\%; CP = 45; DP = 25$.\n\n3. Calculation: $\\frac{2}{98} \\times \\frac{360}{20} \\times 100 =$ 36.73%.\n\n4. Conclusion: Sojib should choose commercial paper because its cost (15.79%) is much lower than the cost of giving up the discount (36.73%)."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch5-cq-032",
        "stem": "Shonchoi Co. sells 800 fans monthly. Each fan costs TK 2,000, carrying cost is TK 1, and ordering cost is TK 100. Sopnil Co. sells 15,000 lights annually with ordering cost of TK 50 and carrying cost of TK 3.",
        "meta": "Cantonment College, Jessore · 2026",
        "type": "college",
        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is trade credit?",
