            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "\"The total inventory cost of Sopnil Co. is higher than Shonchoi Co.\"—Evaluate this statement.",
                "answer": "1. Shonchoi Cost: $(\\frac{9,600}{1386} \\times 100) + (\\frac{1386}{2} \\times 1) = 693 + 693 =$ TK 1,386.\n\n2. Sopnil EOQ: $\\sqrt{\\frac{2 \\times 15,000 \\times 50}{3}} = 707$ units.\n\n3. Sopnil Cost: $(\\frac{15,000}{707} \\times 50) + (\\frac{707}{2} \\times 3) = 1,061 + 1,061 =$ TK 2,122.\n\n4. Conclusion: The statement is correct. Sopnil Co.'s cost (TK 2,122) is higher than Shonchoi's (TK 1,386)."
            }
        ]
    },
