        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>All three are standard methods for calculating the return or yield on bond investments.</p>",
        "id": 4467
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Syed bought a bond with a face value of 2,000 at a market price of 720. Maturity is 10 years and coupon rate is 7%. What is the Yield to Maturity (YTM)?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "19.70%",
            "20.21%",
            "21.17%",
            "24.22%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$YTM = \\frac{I + (FV-SV)/n}{(FV+SV)/2} = \\frac{140 + (2000-720)/10}{(2000+720)/2} \\approx 20.21\\%$$.</p>",
        "id": 4468
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The logic for Mr. Syed buying the bond is: (i) Guaranteed interest (ii) Guarantee of receiving invested money (iii) Gaining company ownership.</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Bondholders are creditors, not owners; they get fixed interest and principal repayment.</p>",
        "id": 4469
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>A bond that never matures (non-redeemable) is called a:</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong Board · 2025",
