        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Zero-coupon bonds provide returns via a deep discount at purchase rather than annual interest.</p>",
        "id": 4583
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Navana Securities issued a perpetual bond (<code>FV</code> 1,000) with a 15% coupon. What type of bond is this?</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Perpetual Bond",
            "Coupon Bond",
            "Treasury Bond",
            "Zero Coupon Bond"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Since no maturity period is mentioned and a coupon exists, it is treated as a perpetual (irredeemable) bond.</p>",
        "id": 4584
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Regarding Navana's bond (Int 15%, K 12%): (i) Annual interest is 120 (ii) Current value is 1,250 (iii) Investment is profitable.</p>",
        "meta": "Rajshahi Board · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Interest is 150. Value = $$150 / 0.12 = 1250$$. Since value > price (implicit par), it is profitable.</p>",
        "id": 4585
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which of the following is a source of long-term financing?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2022",
