    {
        "text": "<p>RFL Pipe issued a 10-year bond with a 2,000 face value and 12% coupon. What is the name of this bond?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Coupon Bond",
            "Treasury Bond",
            "Corporate Bond",
            "Mortgage Bond"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Bonds issued by private companies/corporations are called corporate bonds.</p>",
        "id": 4701
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Based on RFL Pipe's bond (<code>FV</code> 2,000, Price 1,500, Term 10yr, Coupon 12%), what is the approximate YTM?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "12%",
            "15.50%",
            "16.57%",
            "17.57%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$YTM \\approx \\frac{240 + (2000-1500)/10}{(2000+1500)/2} = \\frac{290}{1750} \\approx 16.57\\%$$.</p>",
        "id": 4702
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Fahim Ltd. issued a 1,200 <code>FV</code> bond with a 12% coupon and 12% discount rate. What is its value?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "1,200 TK",
            "1,320 TK",
            "1,344 TK",
            "1,500 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>When the coupon rate equals the required/discount rate, the bond value always equals the face value.</p>",
        "id": 4703
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Hadi wants to buy a bond: <code>FV</code> 1,000, Coupon 8%, 12-year term. Market rate is 10%. What is the max price (<code>PV</code>)?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "860 TK",
            "864 TK",
            "870 TK",
            "875 TK"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p><code>PV</code> = 80 \\t\t\times [1 - (1+0.10)^{-12}]/0.10 + 1000 / (1.10)^{12} \\approx 863.73 \\approx 864$ TK.</p>",
        "id": 4704
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Why did Mr. Hadi buy common shares? (i) Dividends (ii) Capital Gain (iii) To become a director.</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
