        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p><code>PV</code> = 2000 / (1.10)^7 \\approx 1026$ TK.</p>",
        "id": 4717
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>1,000 <code>FV</code> bond, 12% coupon, 10yr term, price 800. What is the YTM?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "20.55%",
            "15.55%",
            "11.55%",
            "9.90%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$YTM \\approx \\frac{120 + (1000-800)/10}{(1000+800)/2} = \\frac{140}{900} \\approx 15.55\\%$$.</p>",
        "id": 4718
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>A 1,000 <code>FV</code> bond has a 12% coupon, price 800. If the maturity period decreases to 6 years: (i) YTM will be 17.03% (ii) Annual interest will decrease (iii) Investment will be profitable.</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$$YTM \\approx \\frac{120 + (1000-800)/6}{(1000+800)/2} \\approx 17.03\\%$$. Annual interest (Coupon) remains 120, but shorter time to gain the discount makes it more profitable.</p>",
        "id": 4719
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Methods for measuring returns from a bond include: (i) Yield to Maturity (ii) Yield to Call (iii) Coupon Rate.</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>YTM and YTC are standard measures of total return. Coupon rate is just a fixed rate, not a method of measuring actual performance or yield.</p>",
        "id": 4720
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Financing collected for the purpose of acquiring fixed assets and investments is obtained from:</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Short-term sources",
            "Mid-term sources",
            "Long-term sources",
            "Current capital"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Long-term assets like land, buildings, and machinery are strategically funded through long-term capital sources.</p>",
        "id": 4721
    }], shortCQData: [], fullCQData: [] },
        "7": { subjectName: "Finance 1st Paper", chapterName: "Chapter 7 : Cost of Capital", mcqData: [{
        "text": "<p>Opportunity cost is associated with which type of capital?</p>",
