    {
        "id": "fin1-ch7-short-b-023",
        "text": "What is optimal capital structure? Explain.",
        "answer": "Optimal capital structure is the specific mix of debt and equity that minimizes a company's weighted average cost of capital (WACC) while maximizing the overall market value of the firm. It represents the point where the benefit of low-cost debt (tax shield) is balanced against the financial risk associated with high leverage.",
        "meta": "Adamjee Cantonment College, Dhaka · 2026",
