    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch7-short-b-024",
        "text": "Why is it necessary to calculate the cost of capital? Explain.",
        "answer": "Calculating the cost of capital is essential for several reasons:\n\n1. Investment Decisions: It acts as a hurdle rate to evaluate if a project's return exceeds its cost.\n\n2. Capital Structure: It helps in determining the optimal mix of debt and equity to minimize overall costs.\n\n3. Performance Evaluation: It helps management assess if the company is generating enough value for its investors.",
