            {
                "label": "b",
                "text": "What is meant by preferred stock?",
                "answer": "Preferred stock is a type of security that has characteristics of both common stock and debt. It grants shareholders a fixed dividend and priority over common stockholders in the payment of dividends and the distribution of assets during liquidation."
            },
            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "What is the cost of common stock capital of Meghna Company? Calculate.",
                "answer": "Calculation of Cost of Common Stock ($K_e$):\n\nCurrent Market Price ($P_0$) = 200 Taka\n\nCurrent Dividend ($D_0$) = 15 Taka\n\nGrowth Rate ($g$) = 5% or 0.05\n\nExpected Dividend ($D_1$) = $D_0(1+g) = 15(1+0.05) = 15.75$ Taka\n\nFormula: $K_e = (\\frac{D_1}{P_0} + g) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = (\\frac{15.75}{200} + 0.05) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = (0.07875 + 0.05) \\times 100 = 12.875\\%$\n\nAnswer: 12.875%"
