    {
        "id": "fin1-ch7-cq-019",
        "stem": "Magpie Ltd. declared a dividend of 2 Taka per share last year, which will increase at a rate of 6% every year. Currently, each share of the company is selling for 150 Taka. On the other hand, the capital structure of Rainbow Ltd. consists of common stock, preferred stock, and debt capital. The weights and after-tax costs are as follows:\n\n*table\n| Source of Capital | Weight | After-tax Cost |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| Common Stock | 70% | 14% |\n| Preferred Stock | 10% | 11% |\n| Debt Capital | 20% | 6% |\n\nNotably, Rainbow Ltd. invests in a project with an expected return of 13%.",
