                "label": "d",
                "text": "Analyze whether the investment decision of Rainbow Ltd. was logical.",
                "answer": "Step 1: Calculate Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) for Rainbow Ltd.\n\nWeight of Common Stock ($W_e$) = 0.70; Cost ($K_e$) = 14%\n\nWeight of Preferred Stock ($W_p$) = 0.10; Cost ($K_p$) = 11%\n\nWeight of Debt ($W_d$) = 0.20; Cost ($K_d$) = 6%\n\nFormula: WACC = $(W_e \\times K_e) + (W_p \\times K_p) + (W_d \\times K_d)$\n\nWACC = $(0.70 \\times 14\\%) + (0.10 \\times 11\\%) + (0.20 \\times 6\\%)$\n\nWACC = $9.8\\% + 1.1\\% + 1.2\\% = 12.1\\%$\n\nStep 2: Analysis\n\n- Expected Return on Project = 13%\n\n- Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) = 12.1%\n\nConclusion: The investment decision is logical. Since the expected return (13%) is greater than the cost of capital (12.1%), the project will generate a positive net surplus, thereby increasing the value of the firm and the wealth of the shareholders."
            }
