        "type": "college",
        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is optimal capital structure?",
                "answer": "Optimal capital structure is the specific mix of debt and equity that minimizes the company's cost of capital while maximizing the market value of the firm."
            },
            {
                "label": "b",
                "text": "Does retained earnings have flotation cost? Explain.",
                "answer": "No, retained earnings do not have flotation costs. Flotation costs are expenses incurred when issuing new securities (like stocks or bonds) to the public. Since retained earnings are internal funds already held by the company, no new securities are issued, and thus no flotation costs are involved."
            },
            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the cost of common stock and preferred stock of the company.",
                "answer": "1. Cost of Common Stock ($K_e$):\n\nCurrent Dividend ($D_0$) = 20 Taka\n\nGrowth Rate ($g$) = 3% or 0.03\n\nExpected Dividend ($D_1$) = $D_0(1+g) = 20(1+0.03) = 20.60$ Taka\n\nMarket Price ($P_0$) = 200 Taka\n\nFlotation Cost ($FC$) = 2% of 200 = 4 Taka\n\nNet Sale Value ($NSV$) = $200 - 4 = 196$ Taka\n\nFormula: $K_e = (\\frac{D_1}{NSV}) + g = (\\frac{20.60}{196}) + 0.03 = 0.1051 + 0.03 = 13.51\\%$\n\n2. Cost of Preferred Stock ($K_p$):\n\nDividend ($D_p$) = $150 \\times 13\\% = 19.50$ Taka (Note: Dividend is usually calculated on face value; here, if market price is 150 and rate is 13%, we use current valuation).\n\nNet Sale Value ($NSV$) = $150 - (2\\% \\text{ of } 150) = 150 - 3 = 147$ Taka\n\nFormula: $K_p = \\frac{D_p}{NSV} = \\frac{19.50}{147} = 13.27\\%$\n\nAnswers: $K_e = 13.51\\%$, $K_p = 13.27\\%$"
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "Calculate the Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) of 'United Leasing' in light of the stem and evaluate the rationality of the financial manager's decision.",
                "answer": "Step 1: Calculate After-tax Cost of Debt ($K_d$)\n\n$K_d = I(1 - T) = 14\\% \\times (1 - 0.35) = 9.1\\%$\n\nStep 2: Determine Weights ($W$)\n\nTotal Capital = 5,00,000 + 2,00,000 + 3,00,000 = 10,00,000\n\n$W_e = 0.50$, $W_p = 0.20$, $W_d = 0.30$\n\nStep 3: Calculate WACC\n\nWACC = $(K_e \\times W_e) + (K_p \\times W_p) + (K_d \\times W_d)$\n\nWACC = $(13.51\\% \\times 0.50) + (13.27\\% \\times 0.20) + (9.1\\% \\times 0.30)$\n\nWACC = $6.755\\% + 2.654\\% + 2.73\\% = 12.139\\%$\n\nEvaluation: The calculated WACC is 12.14%, whereas the overall cost mentioned in the stem is 14%. Since the actual weighted cost (12.14%) is lower than the projected or existing threshold (14%), the company is operating efficiently. The financial manager's decision to maintain this structure is rational as it keeps the cost of funding lower than the stated overall cost."
            }
        ]
