        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is capital structure?",
                "answer": "Capital structure refers to the specific mix of long-term debt and equity used by a firm to finance its overall operations and growth."
            },
            {
                "label": "b",
                "text": "Common stock capital has a cost' - Explain.",
                "answer": "Common stock capital has a cost because shareholders expect a return on their investment in exchange for the risk they take. This is an opportunity cost for the company, as it represents the rate of return the firm must earn to satisfy its investors and maintain the share price."
            },
            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the cost of common stock capital of the company.",
                "answer": "Calculation of Cost of Common Stock ($K_e$):\n\nGiven,\n\nMarket Price ($P_0$) = 200 Taka\n\nNext year's dividend ($D_1$) = 15 Taka\n\nGrowth rate ($g$) = 4% or 0.04\n\nFormula:\n\n$K_e = (\\frac{D_1}{P_0} + g) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = (\\frac{15}{200} + 0.04) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = (0.075 + 0.04) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = 0.115 \\times 100 = 11.5\\%$\n\nAnswer: 11.5%"
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "Calculate the Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) of the organization.",
                "answer": "Step 1: Calculate individual costs\n\n1. Cost of Common Stock ($K_e$) = 11.5% (from Part C)\n\n2. Cost of Preferred Stock ($K_p$) = 8%\n\n3. After-tax Cost of Debt ($K_d$):\n\nInterest ($I$) = 10%\n\nTax Rate ($T$) = 40% or 0.40\n\n$K_d = I(1 - T) = 10\\% \\times (1 - 0.40) = 6\\%$\n\nStep 2: Determine Weights ($W$)\n\nTotal Capital = 10,00,000 Taka\n\n$W_e = 5,00,000 / 10,00,000 = 0.5$\n\n$W_p = 2,00,000 / 10,00,000 = 0.2$\n\n$W_d = 3,00,000 / 10,00,000 = 0.3$\n\nStep 3: Calculate WACC\n\nWACC = $(K_e \\times W_e) + (K_p \\times W_p) + (K_d \\times W_d)$\n\nWACC = $(11.5\\% \\times 0.5) + (8\\% \\times 0.2) + (6\\% \\times 0.3)$\n\nWACC = $5.75\\% + 1.6\\% + 1.8\\% = 9.15\\%$\n\nAnswer: 9.15%"
            }
