        "meta": "Safiuddin Sarker Academy and College, Tongi, Gazipur · 2026",
        "type": "college",
        "questions": [
            {
                "label": "a",
                "text": "What is cost of capital?",
                "answer": "Cost of capital is the minimum rate of return a company must earn on its investments to satisfy its investors and maintain its market value."
            },
            {
                "label": "b",
                "text": "What impact does flotation cost have on the cost of newly issued shares? Explain.",
                "answer": "Flotation cost increases the cost of newly issued shares. When a company issues new shares, it incurs expenses like underwriting fees and brokerage. These costs reduce the net proceeds received from the sale, which in turn increases the effective percentage cost of that capital for the firm."
            },
            {
                "label": "c",
                "text": "Calculate the cost of common stock and the cost of debt capital for Alpha Ltd.",
                "answer": "1. Cost of Common Stock ($K_e$):\n\nDividend ($D_0$) = 10 Taka\n\nGrowth ($g$) = 5% or 0.05\n\nPrice ($P_0$) = 120 Taka\n\n$D_1 = D_0(1+g) = 10(1+0.05) = 10.5$\n\n$K_e = (\\frac{D_1}{P_0} + g) \\times 100$\n\n$K_e = (\\frac{10.5}{120} + 0.05) \\times 100 = 13.75\\%$\n\n2. Cost of Debt ($K_d$):\n\nInterest ($I$) = 16%\n\nTax ($T$) = 40% or 0.40\n\n$K_d = I(1 - T) = 16(1 - 0.40) = 9.6\\%$"
            },
            {
                "label": "d",
                "text": "Calculate the average cost of capital according to the manager's advice and give your opinion.",
                "answer": "Step 1: New Capital Mix\n\n50% of Debt (4,00,000) converted to Common Stock.\n\nNew Common Stock = 20,00,000 + 4,00,000 = 24,00,000\n\nPreferred Stock = 12,00,000\n\nRemaining Debt = 4,00,000\n\nTotal = 40,00,000\n\nStep 2: Weights\n\n$W_e = 24/40 = 0.6$; $W_p = 12/40 = 0.3$; $W_d = 4/40 = 0.1$\n\nStep 3: New WACC\n\nWACC = $(13.75 \\times 0.6) + (10 \\times 0.3) + (9.6 \\times 0.1)$\n\nWACC = $8.25 + 3.0 + 0.96 = 12.21\\%$\n\nOpinion: The manager's advice is not beneficial. The current WACC is 11.8%, but after converting debt to equity, it increases to 12.21%. Debt is cheaper (9.6%) than equity (13.75%); reducing the cheaper source increases the overall cost."
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "fin1-ch7-cq-033",
        "stem": "The capital structure of Alpha Ltd. is as follows:\n\n*table\n| Source of Capital | Amount (Taka) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| Common Stock (100 Taka each) | 20,00,000 |\n| 10% Preferred Stock | 12,00,000 |\n| 16% Debt Capital | 8,00,000 |\n| **Total** | **40,00,000** |",
