        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p><code>IRR</code> is the rate where N<code>PV</code>=0. If the discount rate exceeds <code>IRR</code>, the N<code>PV</code> becomes negative.</p>",
        "id": 4824
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>XYZ Co. buys a machine for 1,00,000. Annual CFAT is 30,000 for 5 years. Cost of capital 10%. N<code>PV</code>?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur Board · 2025",
