    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Based on Fardin's project (1,20,000 investment), what is the Payback Period (PBP)?</p>",
        "meta": "Comilla Board · 2025",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "4 years",
            "4.1 years",
            "4.25 years",
            "4.8 years"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Yr 4 cum. is 1,14,000. Remaining: 6,000. $$PBP = 4 + (6,000 / 60,000) = 4.1$$ (Wait, calc: $$1,20k - 1,14k = 6k / 60k = 0.1$$). So, 4.1 years.</p>",
        "id": 4849
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which is considered the ideal/standard method of capital budgeting?</p>",
