        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$PBP = 4,00,000 / 1,00,000 = 4$$ years.</p>",
        "id": 4936
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Cash inflow 1,00,000. Depreciation 10,000. Net Profit After Tax? (Assuming 0% tax)</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "60,000",
            "70,000",
            "90,000",
            "1,10,000"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>$$CFAT = EAT + Depreciation$$, so EAT = 1,00,000 - 10,000 = 90,000$.</p>",
        "id": 4937
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Required for PBP method: (i) Discount rate (ii) Cash inflows (iii) Initial investment.</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Traditional PBP does not require a discount rate.</p>",
        "id": 4938
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Initial Inv 50,000. Profitability Index (PI) = 1. What is the N<code>PV</code>?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2022",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30,000",
            "50,000",
            "60,000",
            "0"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$PI = PV \\text{ Inflow} / Inv$$. If $$PI=1$$, PV \\text{ Inflow} = 50,000$$. $$NPV = 50,000 - 50,000 = 0$.</p>",
        "id": 4939
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Objectives of capital budgeting: (i) Modernization (ii) New projects (iii) R&D.</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2022",
