        "id": 5058
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Probable cash flows of a project are as follows:\nYear 0: (50,000) TK\nYear 1: TK 30,000\nYear 2: TK 40,000\nYear 3: TK 50,000, What is the Payback Period (PBP) of the project?</p>",
        "meta": "Dinajpur · 2019",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "1",
            "1.5",
            "2.5",
            "3"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Since the cash flows are uneven, we use the Cumulative Cash Flow method:Year 0: (50,000) — Initial InvestmentYear 1: Cumulative = -50,000 + 30,000 = (20,000)Year 2: Cumulative = -20,000 + 40,000 = +20,000The payback occurs between Year 1 and Year 2.$$\\text{PBP} = \\text{Year before full recovery} + \\left( \\frac{\\text{Unrecovered amount at start of year}}{\\text{Cash flow during the year}} \\right)$$$$\\text{PBP} = 1 + \\left( \\frac{20,000}{40,000} \\right) = 1 + 0.5 = \\mathbf{1.5 \\text{ years}}$$</p>",
        "id": 5059
    },
