        "explanation": "<p>Need 16k after Yr 3 (96k). $$PBP = 3 + (16,000 / 40,000) = 3.4$$ years.</p>",
        "id": 5068
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Nilanjana Ltd. wants to select the best project from two mutually exclusive projects. Cost of capital is 10%. Information for the projects is as follows:\nProject A (ক):\nInitial Investment: TK 30,000\nAnnual Cash Inflow (Years 1-5): TK 10,000\nN<code>PV</code>: TK 7,908\n\nProject B (খ):\nInitial Investment: TK 50,000\nAnnual Cash Inflow (Years 1-5): TK 15,000\nN<code>PV</code>: TK 6,862\n\nQuestion: What is the approximate Average Rate of Return (ARR) of the first project?</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "30%",
            "33%",
            "60%",
            "26.67%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>-</p>",
        "id": 5069
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>(Following the above stem) Between Project A & B: (i) A is acceptable (high PBP) (ii) A is acceptable (low PBP) (iii) B is rejected (low N<code>PV</code>).</p>",
        "meta": "Chittagong · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Standard rules: Lower PBP and higher N<code>PV</code> are preferred.</p>",
        "id": 5070
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Dinar Trading deciding between two projects belongs to which function?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "Fund Distribution",
            "Fund Collection",
            "Capital Budgeting",
            "Current Asset Mgmt"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Evaluation of long-term projects is capital budgeting.</p>",
        "id": 5071
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Dinar Trading: Project A (Inv 2L). Inflows: 100k, 70k, 60k, 50k, 30k. PBP?</p>",
        "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "2.3 years",
            "2.5 years",
            "3.0 years",
            "3.5 years"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Yr 2 cumulative = 170k. Need 30k more. $$PBP = 2 + (30k/60k) = 2.5$$ years.</p>",
        "id": 5072
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Investment 2,00,000. Average Net Profit 60,000. What is the ARR?</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "12.50%",
            "25%",
            "40%",
            "60%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$$Avg\\ Inv = 2,00,000/2 = 1,00,000$$. $$ARR = (60k/100k) \\t\times 100 = 60\\%$$.</p>",
        "id": 5073
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Limitations of ARR: (i) Ignores risk (ii) Ignores cash flows (iii) Ignores TVM.</p>",
        "meta": "Barisal Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>ARR uses accounting profit and doesn't consider time value or risk.</p>",
        "id": 5074
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>What is the primary technique of discounted cash flow methods?</p>",
        "meta": "Jessore Board · 2017",
        "type": "board",
        "options": [
            "ARR",
            "NPV",
            "IRR",
            "PBP"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>N<code>PV</code> is the primary and most robust discounted technique.</p>",
        "id": 5075
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Mr. Kabir invested 80 Lakh for 5 years. Average investment?</p>",
