        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>Systematic (Market) risk is macro-economic and uncontrollable.</p>",
        "id": 5371
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which asset is best for a risk-averse investor?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Asset A",
            "Asset B",
            "Asset C",
            "Asset D"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>The asset with the lowest Coefficient of Variation (CV) is always the best choice.</p>",
        "id": 5372
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Expected return per unit of risk is represented by:</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Coefficient of Var",
            "Std Deviation",
            "Co-variance",
            "Beta"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>CV measures risk per unit of return ($\\sigma / \\bar{R}$).</p>",
        "id": 5373
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>The term $(R_i - \\bar{R})$ represents:</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Deviation from return",
            "Deviation from mean",
            "Std Dev deviation",
            "Risk deviation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>It signifies how much each actual return deviates from the average (mean).</p>",
        "id": 5374
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Based on the historical data for 'Kalbela Ltd.': 2022 (13%) and 2023 (17%), what is the Expected Rate of Return?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "13%",
            "14%",
            "15%",
            "16%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>-</p>",
        "id": 5375
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Based on the historical data for 'Kalbela Ltd.': 2022 (13%) and 2023 (17%), What is the Standard Deviation?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "2.83%",
            "2.93%",
            "3.03%",
            "3.13%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Calculated as $\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sum(R_i - \\bar{R})^2}{n-1}}$ for historical data.</p>",
        "id": 5376
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Which is the best strategy for evaluating multiple projects?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "Expected Return",
            "Std Deviation",
            "Variance",
            "Coeff. of Variation"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>CV is the best relative measure for projects with different returns.</p>",
        "id": 5377
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If Std Deviation is 2% and CV is 8, what is the Expected Return?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "50%",
            "25%",
            "75%",
            "55%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$8 = (2 / \\bar{R}) \\times 100 \\rightarrow \\bar{R} = 200 / 8 = 25\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 5378
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>If Expected Return is 13% and Std Deviation is 34%, what is the CV?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "38.23%",
            "261.53%",
            "267.53%",
            "621.53%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 1,
        "explanation": "<p>$CV = (34 / 13) \\times 100 = 261.53\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 5379
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Objectives of Portfolio Investment: (i) Increase Profit (ii) Decrease Risk (iii) Market Control.</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "i & ii",
            "i & iii",
            "ii & iii",
            "i, ii & iii"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 0,
        "explanation": "<p>Portfolios aim for risk reduction and efficient profit growth.</p>",
        "id": 5380
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Abir Ltd: $R_f$ 7.5%, $R_m$ 12%, Beta 1.5. What is the Market Risk Premium?</p>",
        "meta": "- · -",
        "type": "-",
        "options": [
            "3%",
            "3.50%",
            "4%",
            "4.50%"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": 3,
        "explanation": "<p>$Risk\\ Premium = R_m - R_f = 12\\% - 7.5\\% = 4.5\\%$.</p>",
        "id": 5381
    },
    {
        "text": "<p>Abir Ltd: $R_f$ 7.5%, $R_m$ 12%, Beta 1.5. What is the Expected Rate of Return?</p>",
        "meta": "College · -",
        "type": "college",
        "options": [
            "14.25%",
            "7.50%",
